\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxvii{%
Allah said: cast it down, O Musa!\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxviii{%
So he cast it down, and lo! it was a serpent running along.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxix{%
Allah said: take hold of it, and fear not; We shall restore it to its former state.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxx{%
And press thy hand to thy side, it will come forth white, without hurt, as anot her sign.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxi{%
That We may shew thee of Our Signs the greatest.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxii{%
Go thou unto Fir'awn; verily he hath waxen exorbitant.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxiii{%
He said: my Lord! expand for me my breast.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxiv{%
And ease for me by affair.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxv{%
And loose a knot from my tongue.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxvi{%
That they may understand my Speech.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxvii{%
And appoint for me a minister from my household.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxviii{%
Harun, my brother.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxix{%
Strengthen by him my back.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxx{%
And associate him in my affair.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxi{%
That We may hallow Thee oft.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxii{%
And may make mention of Thee oft.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxiii{%
Verily Thou! Thou art of us ever a Beholder.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxiv{%
He said: surely thou art granted thy petition, O Musa!\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxv{%
And assuredly We conferred a benefit on thee anot her time.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxvi{%
When We inspired unto thy mother that which We inspired,\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxvii{%
Saying! cast him in the ark, and cast him into the river, and the river will throw him on the bank, and then an enemy of Mine and an enemy of his will take him up. And I cast on thee love from Me in order that thou mayest be formed under Mine eye.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxviii{%
What time thy sister was walking along and saying: shall I direct you unto one who will take care of him! Thus We returned thee to thy mother that she might cool her eyes and she might not grieve. And thou slewest a person, but We delivered thee from sorrow, and We tried thee with several trials. Then thou tarriedst for years among the people of Madyan then thou camest according to fate, O Musa!\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmccclxxxix{%
And formed thee for Myself.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxc{%
Go thou and thy brother with My signs, and slacken not in remembrance of Mine.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxci{%
Go ye twain unto Fir'awn, verily he hath waxen exorbitant,\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcii{%
Then say to him a gentle saying; haply he may be admonished or he may fear.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxciii{%
The twain said: O our Lord! verily we fear that he may hasten against us or wax exorbitant.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxciv{%
He said; fear not; verily I shall be With you twain: I shall hear and see.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcv{%
So go to him, and say: verily we are two apostles of thy Lord, so let go with us the Children of Isra'il, and torment them not; surely we have come unto thee with a sign from thy Lord: and peace be upon him who followeth the guidance.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcvi{%
Verily We! it hath been revealed unto us that the torment will be for him who belieth and turneth away.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcvii{%
He said: who is the Lord of you twain, O Musa!\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcviii{%
Musa said: our Lord is He who vouchsafed unto everything its creation, then guided it.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcccxcix{%
He said: then what happened to the former generations?\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcd{%
Musa said: the knowledge there of is with my Lord in the Book; my Lord erreth not, nor He forgetteth.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdi{%
Who hath appointed for you the earth as a bed, and hath opened for you therein pathways, and hath sent down from the heaven water, and thereby We have brought forth kinds of plants, various.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdii{%
Eat and pasture your cattle: verily therein are signs for men of sagacity.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdiii{%
Thereof We created you, and thereunto We return you, and therefrom We shall bring You forth once again.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdiv{%
And assuredly We shewed him Our signs, all of them, but he belied and refused.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdv{%
He said: art thou come unto us that thou mayest drive us out of our land by thy magic, O Musa!\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdvi{%
So We shall surely bring unto thee a magic the like thereof; so Make between us and thee an appointment which neither we nor thou shall fail in some open space.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdvii{%
Musa said: your appointment is the gala day, and that the people be gathered in the forenoon.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdviii{%
Then Firawn turned away, devised his stratagem; thereafter he came.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdix{%
Musa said unto them: woe unto you! fabricate not against Allah a lie, lest he extirpate you with a torment, and surely He who fabricateth, loseth.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdx{%
Then they wrangled about their affair among themselves, and kept secret their private counsel.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxi{%
They said: verily these two are magicians, intending to drive you forth from your land by their magic and to do away with your superior way.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxii{%
Wherefore devise your stratagem, and then come in a row; and prospered to-day is he who overcometh.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxiii{%
They said: either thou cast down, or we shall be the first to cast down.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxiv{%
He said: nay, cast ye down. And lo! their cords and their staves were made to appear to him by their magic as though they were running.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxv{%
Then a kind of fear in his soul Musa felt.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxvi{%
We said: fear not! verily thou! thou shalt be the superior.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxvii{%
And cast thou down that which is in thy right hand: it shall swallow up that which they have wrought; They have wrought only a magician's stratagem; and the magician prospereth not wheresoever he cometh.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxviii{%
Then the magicians were cast down prostrate; they said: we believe in the Lord of Musa and Harun.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxix{%
Fir'awn said; believed ye in him ere I gave you leave! verily he is your chief who hath taught you magic. So I will surely cut off your hands and feet on the opposite sides, and will surely crucify you on the trunks of palm-trees, and ye shall surely know whichever of us is severer in torment and more lasting.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxx{%
They said: we shall by no means prefer thee to that which hath come to us of the evidences, and to Him Who hath created us; so decree thou whatsoever thou shalt decree; thou canst only decree in respect of the life of this world.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxi{%
Verily we! we have believed in our Lord, that he may forgive us our faults, and that to which thou hast constrained us in the way of magic; and Allah is Best and Most Lasting.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxii{%
Verily whosoever cometh unto his lord as a Culprit, for him is Hell wherein he will neither die nor live.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxiii{%
And whosoever cometh unto Him as a believer, and he hath done righteous works---then these! for them are ranks high.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxiv{%
Gardens Everlasting whereunder rivers flow: abiders therein; that is the meed of him who hath purified himself.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxv{%
And assuredly We revealed unto Musa, saying: depart in night with my bondmen, and make for them in the sea a parth dry: thou Shalt fear neither overtaking, nor shalt thou be afraid.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxvi{%
Then Fir'awn followed them with his hosts; and there came upon them of the sea that which came upon them.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxvii{%
And Fir'awn led his nation astray, and guided them not.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxviii{%
O Children of Israel; We delivered you from your enemy, and treated with you on the right side of the mount and sent down upon you the manna and the quails.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxix{%
Saying: eat of the clean things wherewith We have provided you, and wax not exorbitant in respect thereof, lest My wrath alight on you; and upon whomsoever My wrath alighteth, he surely perisheth.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxx{%
And verily I am the Most Forgiving unto whomsoever repenteth and believeth and worketh righteously, and thereafter letteth himself remain guided.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxi{%
And what hath made thee hasten from thy people, O Musa?\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxii{%
He said: those! they are close on my footstep, and hastened to Thee, O my Lord; that Thou mightest be wellpleased.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxiii{%
He said: verily We have tempted thy people after thee, and the Samiri hath led them astray.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxiv{%
So Musa returned unto his people, indignant and sorrowful. He said: O my people! promised there not your Lord unto you an excellent promise! Lasted then the covenant too long for you, or desired ye that the wrath from your Lord should alight on you, so that ye failed to keep my appointment?\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxv{%
They said: we failed not to keep thy appointment of our own authority, but we were laden with burthens of the people's ornaments; then we threw them, and Thus Samiri cast down.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxvi{%
And he produced for them a calf: a body with a low. Then they Said: this is your god and the god of Musa, and that he forgat.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxvii{%
Observed they not that it returned not unto them a word, and owned not for them hurt or profit?\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxviii{%
And assuredly Harun had said unto them afore: O my people! ye are only being tempted thereby; and verily your Lord is the Compassionate; so follow me and obey my command.\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxxxix{%
They said: we shall by no means cease to be assiduous to it until there returneth to us Musa.\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxl{%
Musa said: O Harun! what prevented thee, when thou sawest them going astray.\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxli{%
That thou followedst me not! Hast thou disobeyed my command?\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlii{%
Harun said: O my mother's son! hold me not by my beard nor by my head verily feared that thou wouldst say, thou hast caused a division among the Children of Israel and hast not guarded my Word.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxliii{%
Musa said: what was thy object, O Samiri?\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxliv{%
He said: l saw that which they saw not; so I seized a handful from the footstep of the messenger, and then cast it; Thus my soul embellished the affair to me.\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlv{%
Musa said: begone thou! verily it shall be thine in life to say no contact; and verily thine is an appointment which thou shalt by no means fail. And look at thy god to which thou hast been assidauous; we shall surely burn it, and we shall scatter it into the sea a wide scattering.\qt@no{(97)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlvi{%
Your God is only Allah, the One other than whom there is no god. He comprehendeth everything in knowledge.\qt@no{(98)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlvii{%
Thus We recount unto thee some tidings of that which hath preceded; and surely We have vouchsafed unto thee from before Us an admonition.\qt@no{(99)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlviii{%
Whosoever turnoth away therefrom--verily they shall bear on the Day of Judgment a burthen,\qt@no{(100)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxlix{%
As abiders therein. And vile will load! them on the Day of Judgment as a load!\qt@no{(101)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdl{%
The Day whereon the trumpet will be blown into, and We shall gather the culprits on that Day blear-eyed,\qt@no{(102)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdli{%
Mutterin among themselves: ye tarried not save ten days.\qt@no{(103)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlii{%
We are the Best Knower of that which they will say, when the best of them in judgment Will say: ye tarried not save for a day.\qt@no{(104)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdliii{%
And they ask thee regarding the mountains; so say thou: my Lord will scatter them with a total scattering.\qt@no{(105)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdliv{%
Then He shall leave it a plain, level.\qt@no{(106)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlv{%
Wherein thou shalt not see any crookedness or ruggedness.\qt@no{(107)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlvi{%
That Day they shall follow the caller for Whom there shall be no crookedness; and voices Shall be humbled for the Compassionate; so that thou shalt not hear ought except pattering\qt@no{(108)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlvii{%
That Day intercession will Profit not except him for whom the Compassionate giveth leave, and of whom He approveth the Word.\qt@no{(109)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlviii{%
He knoweth that which is before them and that which is behind them, and they, encompass it not with their knowledge.\qt@no{(110)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlix{%
And downcast will be faces before the Living, the Self- subsisting, and disappointed will be he who beareth a wrong.\qt@no{(111)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlx{%
And whosoever worketh of the righteous works, and is a believer, he will not fear Wrong or begrudging\qt@no{(112)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxi{%
And Thus We have sent it down, an Arabic Recitation, and have propounded variously therein of the threats, that haply they may fear, or that it may generate in them some admonition.\qt@no{(113)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxii{%
Exalted is Allah, the True King! And hasten thee not with the Qur'an before there is finished to thee the revelation thereof, and say thou: O my Lord! increase me in knowledge!\qt@no{(114)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxiii{%
And assuredly We covenanted with Adam aforetime, then he forgat, and We found not in him steadiness.\qt@no{(115)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxiv{%
And recall what time We said to the angels: prostrate yourselves before Adam. They fell prostrate, but Iblis did not; he refused.\qt@no{(116)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxv{%
Then We said: Adam! verily this is an enemy unto thee and thine spouse; so let him not drive forth you twain from the Garden, lest thou be destressed.\qt@no{(117)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxvi{%
Verily it is thine that thou shalt not hunger therein nor go naked.\qt@no{(118)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxvii{%
Nor that thou shalt thirst therein nor shall suffer from the sun.\qt@no{(119)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxviii{%
Then the Satan whispered unto him; he said: Adam! shall direct thee to the tree of eternity and a dominion that ageth not!\qt@no{(120)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxix{%
Then the twain ate thereof; so there became disclosed to them their shame, and they began sewing upon them selves some of the leaves of the Garden, so Adam disobeyed his Lord, and erred,\qt@no{(121)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxx{%
Thereafter his Lord accepted him, and relented toward him, and guided him.\qt@no{(122)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxi{%
He said: get ye twain down therefrom together: some of you an enemy unto some others; then if there cometh unto you from Me guidance, whosoever followeth My guidance shall neither go astray nor be distressed.\qt@no{(123)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxii{%
And whosoever turneth away from My admonition, for him verily will be a livelihood shrunken, and We shall raise him up on the Day of Judgment sightless.\qt@no{(124)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxiii{%
He will say: O my Lord! why hast Thou gathered me sightless whereas surely I have been a seer.\qt@no{(125)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxiv{%
Allah will say: Thus came Our signs Unto thee and thou ignoredst them; so that wise today thou shalt be ignored.\qt@no{(126)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxv{%
Thus We requite him who trespasseth and believeth not in the signs of his Lord, and surely the torment of the Hereafter is most severe and most lasting.\qt@no{(127)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxvi{%
Hath it not served as guidance to them how many a generation We have destroyed before them, amidst whose dwellings they Walk! Verily therein are signs for men of sagacity.\qt@no{(128)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxvii{%
And had not a word from thy Lord gone forth, and a term determined, it must necessarily have come.\qt@no{(129)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxviii{%
So bear thou patiently that which they say, and hallow the praise of thy Lord before the rising of the sun and before the setting thereof. And hallow Him in part of the night and the ends of the day, haply thou wilt be pleased.\qt@no{(130)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxix{%
And strain not thine eyes after that which We have given classes of them to enjoy: the splendour of the life of the World, that We might try them therein; and the provision of thy Lord is the best and most lasting.\qt@no{(131)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxx{%
And command thy household for prayer, and persevere thou therein; We ask not of thee any provision; we Who provide thee; and the happy end is for piety.\qt@no{(132)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxi{%
And they Say: wherefore bringeth he not unto us a sign from his Lord? Hath not there came unto them the evidence of that which is in the former Scriptures?\qt@no{(133)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxii{%
And had We destroyed them With a torment before it, surely they would have said: O our Lord why sent not Thou Unto us an apostle that we might have followed Thy signs before we were disgraced and humiliated.\qt@no{(134)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxiii{%
Say thou: everyone Is on the watch; so watch, and anon ye shall know who are the fellows of thee even path and who hath let himself be guided.\qt@no{(135)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxiv{%
\basmalahen There hath approached unto mankind their reckoning, while they in neglect are turning away.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxv{%
There cometh not unto them a fresh admonition from their Lord but they listen to it while they are playing.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxvi{%
In sport being their hearts. And those who do wrong keep secret their private discourse this is but a human being like unto yourselves; will ye then betake yourselves to magic while ye know?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxvii{%
The Prophet said: my Lord knoweth the word in the heavens and the earth, and He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxviii{%
Aye! they say: a medley of dreams; aye! he hath fabricated it; aye! he is a poet; so let him bring us a sign even as the ancients were sent with.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdlxxxix{%
Not a city before them which We destroyed believed; will they then believe?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxc{%
And We sent not before thee but men unto whom We revealed; so ask the people of the Admonition if ye know not.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxci{%
And We made them not bodies not eating food; nor were they to be abiders.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcii{%
Then We made good unto them the premise; so We delivered them and those whom We willed, and We destroyed the extravagant.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxciii{%
And assuredly We have sent down unto you a Book wherein is admonition for you; will ye not then reflect?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxciv{%
And how many a city have We overthrown which were doing wrong, and We caused to grow up thereafter anot her nation!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcv{%
Then when they perceived Our violence, lo! they were from it fleeing.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcvi{%
Flee not, and return unto that wherein ye luxuriated and your habitations, haply ye will be questioned.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcvii{%
They said: woe unto us! verily we have been wrong-doers.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcviii{%
And this ceased not to be their cry until We made them a harvestreaped, extinguished.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcdxcix{%
And We created not the heaven and the earth and that which is in between in play.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmd{%
Had We intended that We should choose a sport, surely We would choose it from before Us--if We were ever going to do that.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdi{%
Aye! We hurl truth against false hood, so that it braineth it, and lo! it vanisheth; and to you be the woe for that which ye utter!\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdii{%
And His is whosoever is in the heavens and the earth; and those nigh unto Him are not too stiff-necked for His worship nor are they weary.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdiii{%
And they hallow Him night and day, and they flag not.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdiv{%
Have they taken gods from the earth who raise the deed?\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdv{%
Had there been in between the twain gods except Allah surely the twain would have gone to ruin. Hallowed be Allah, the Lord of the Throne, from that which they utter!\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdvi{%
He shall be questioned not as to that which He doth, while they shall be questioned.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdvii{%
Have they taken gods beside Him? Say thou: forth with your proof This is an admonition unto those with me and an admonition unto those before me. But most of them knew not the truth, and so they are averters.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdviii{%
And We sent not before thee an apostle but We revealed unto him that there is no god but I, so worship Me.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdix{%
And they say; the Compaionate hath taken a son. Hallowed be He! aye! they are bondmen honoured.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdx{%
They precede Him not in words, and by His command they work.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxi{%
He knoweth whatsoever is before them and whatsoever is behind them; and they intercede not except for him whom He approveth, and in awe of Him they are fearful.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxii{%
And whosoever of them should say: verily I am a god beside Him, such a one We shall requite with Hell; Thus We requite the wrong- doers.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxiii{%
Have not these who disbelieve considered that the heavens and the earth were closed up, then We rent them? And We have made of water everything living; will they not then believe?\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxiv{%
And We have placed in the earth firm mountains lest it should move away with them, and We placed therein Passages for paths, that haply they may be guided.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxv{%
And We have made the heaven a roof, safe, and from the signs there of they are averters.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxvi{%
And He it is Who hath created the night and the day, and the sun and the moon, each in an orb floating.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxvii{%
And We appointed not for any human being before thee immortality; if thou then diest, are they to be immortals?\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxviii{%
Every soul is going to taste of death, and We shall prove you with evil and good as a temptation; and unto Us ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxix{%
And when those who disbelieve behold thee they only take thee up for mockery: is this he who mentioneth your gods? while in the mention of the compassionate they are themselves blasphemers.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxx{%
Man was created of hast, surely I shall show you MY signs, so ask Me not to hasten.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxi{%
And they say: when cometh this torment if ye are truth- tellers!\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxii{%
If only those who disbelieve have known of the time when they shall not be able to ward off from their faces the Fire nor from their backs, nor shall they be succoured!\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxiii{%
Aye! it would come upon them on a sudden and shall dumbfound them; they shall not be able to avert it, nor shall they be respited.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxiv{%
And assuredly mocked were the apostles before thee, then there surrounded those of them Who scoffed that whereat they had been mocking!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxv{%
Say thou: who guardeth you by night and by day from the Compassionate! O Yet from the remembrance of their Lord they avert themselves!\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxvi{%
Have they gods who defend them beside Us? They are not able to succour themselves, and against Us they cannot be kept company with.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxvii{%
Aye! We let these people and their fathers enjoy until there grew long upon them the life. Behold they not that We come unto the land diminishing it by the borders thereof? Shall they then be the victors?\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxviii{%
Say thou: I only warn you by the revelation; and the deaf hearken not unto the call when they are warned.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxix{%
And if a breath of the torment of thy Lord were to touch them, they will say: woe unto us! we have been wrong-doers.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxx{%
And We shall set balances of justice for the Day of Judgment; then no soul shall be wronged at all; and if it be but the weight of a grain of mustard-seed We shall bring it; and We suffice as Reckoners.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxi{%
And assuredly We vcuchsafed unto Musa and Harun the distinction and illumination and an admonition for the God-fearing.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxii{%
These who fear their Lord unseen, and who are of the Hour fearful.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxiii{%
And this is an admonition blest, which We have sent down! will ye then be the rejectors thereof?\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxiv{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed un to lbrahim his rectitude aforetime, and him We had ever known.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxv{%
Recall what time he said unto his father and his people what are these images to which ye are cleaving?\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxvi{%
They said: we found our fathers the worshippers thereof.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxvii{%
He said: assuredlY ye, ye and your fathers, have been in error manifest.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxviii{%
They said: hast thou come unto us with the truth, or art thou of those who sport?\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxxxix{%
He said: Aye! your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth Who created them, and as to that I am of the witnesses.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxl{%
And by Allah I shall surely devise a plot against your idols after ye turned away backward.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxli{%
Then he made them fragments, all except the big one of them, that haply unto it they may return.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlii{%
They said: who hath wrought this to our gods? verily he is of the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxliii{%
They said: We heard a youth speak of them, who is called Ibrahim.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxliv{%
They said: bring him then before the eyes of the people, haply they may bear witness.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlv{%
They said: art thou the one who hath wrought this unto our gods, O Ibrahim?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlvi{%
He said: rather he hath wrought it: this big one of them: so question them, if they ever speak.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlvii{%
They then turned to themselves, and said: verily ye it is who are the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlviii{%
Thereafter they were made to turn over upon their heads, saying, assuredly thou knowest that they speak not.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxlix{%
He said: worship ye, then, beside Allah, that which profiteth you not at all, nor it hurteth you\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdl{%
Fie upon you and upon that which ye worship beside Allah! Will ye not then reflect?\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdli{%
They said: burn him, and succour your gods, if ye will be doing.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlii{%
We said: O fire! be thou cool and peace unto Ibrahim\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdliii{%
And they intended to do him an evil, but We made them the worst losers.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdliv{%
And We delivered him and Lut to the land wherein We had placed Our blessings for the worlds.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlv{%
And We bestowed upon him ls-haq and Ya qub as a grandson; and each one We made righteous.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlvi{%
And We made them leaders, guiding by Our command; and We revealed unto them the doing of good deeds and the establishment of prayer, and the giving of poor-rate; and of Us they were the worshippers.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlvii{%
And Lut! We vouchsafed unto him judgment and knowledge, and We delivered him out of the city which had been working foul deeds; verily they were a people evil, wicked.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlviii{%
And We caused him to enter into Our mercy; verily he was of the righteous.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlix{%
And Nuh! recall what time he cried aforetime; so we answered him and delivered him and his house hold from a calamity mighty.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlx{%
And We succoured him against the people who belied Our signs; verily they were a people evil, so we drowned them all.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxi{%
And Daud and Sulaiman! recall what time they gave judgment regarding the tillage when certain people's sheep had pastured therein at night; and of the judgment concerning them We were the Witnesses.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxii{%
So We gave the understanding thereof unto Sulaiman; and unto each We vouchsafed judgment and knowledge. And We so subjected the mountains that they shall hallow us along with Daud, and also the birds; and We were the doers.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxiii{%
And We taught him the art of making the coats of mail for you that it may protect you from your violence; are ye then thankful?\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxiv{%
And unto Sulaiman We subjected the wind, strongly raging, running at his command toward the land wherein We had placed Our blessing; and of evrything We are the knowers.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxv{%
And of the satans were some who dove for him, and worked a work beside that; and of them We were the Watchers.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxvi{%
And Ayyub! recall what time he cried unto his Lord: verily hurt hath touched me, and Thou art the Most Merciful of the mercifuls.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxvii{%
So We answered him and We removed that which was with him of the hurt, and We vouchsafed unto him his household and the like thereof along with them, as a mercy from us and a remembrance unto the worshippers.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxviii{%
And Isma'il and ldris and Zul-Kifl! each were of the patient.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxix{%
And We caused them to enter into our mercy, verily they are of the righteous.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxx{%
And Zun-nun! recall what time he departed in anger and imagined that We could not straiten him, then he cried in the darknesses, that: there is no god but Thou! hallowed be Thou! verily I have been of the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxi{%
So We answered him, and We delivered him from the distress, and Thus do We deliver the believers.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxii{%
And Zakariyya! recall what time he cried unto his Lord: my Lord! leave me not solitary, though Thou art the best of heirs.\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxiii{%
So We answered him, and We bestowed on him Yahya and We made sound for him his spouse. Verily they Were wont to vie with one anot her in good deeds and to call upon us with longing and dread, and they were ever before us meek.\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxiv{%
And she who guarded her chastity! Then We breathed into her of Our spirit, and made her and her son a sign unto the worlds.\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxv{%
Verily this community of yours is a single community, and I am your Lord; so worship Me.\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxvi{%
And they cut up their affair among them:, all are unto Us returners.\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxvii{%
Whosoever worketh righteous works, and he is a believer, there shall be no denial of his endeavour; and We are for him the Writers.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxviii{%
And a ban is laid on every town which We have destroyed, that they Shall not return.\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxix{%
Until when Ya'juj and Ma'juj are let out, and from every mound they are trickling down.\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxx{%
And there shall approach the true promise; and lo! the eyes of those who disbelieved shall be staring: woe unto us! surely we have been in neglect thereof; aye! we have been the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(97)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxi{%
Verily ye and whatsoever ye worship beside Allah shall be firewood for Hell: thereunto ye shall go down.\qt@no{(98)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxii{%
Had these been gods, they would not have gone down thereunto; and all of them therein shall be abiders.\qt@no{(99)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxiii{%
Theirs therein shall be roaring, and therein they shall hear not.\qt@no{(100)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxiv{%
Verily those for whom the good reward hath preceded from Us, they therefrom shall be kept far away.\qt@no{(101)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxv{%
They shall not hear the least sound thereof, and in that felicity which their souls desire they shall be abiders.\qt@no{(102)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxvi{%
The Great Terror shall grieve them not, and the angels will meet them: this is Your Day which ye were ever promised-\qt@no{(103)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxvii{%
The Day whereon We shall roll up the heaven like as the rolling up of a scroll for books. Even as We began the first creation, We shall restore it: a promise binding upon Us; verily We have been the Doers.\qt@no{(104)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxviii{%
And assuredly We have prescribed in the Scripture after the admonition, that: the land! there shall inherit it My bondmen righteous.\qt@no{(105)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdlxxxix{%
Verily in this in a preaching for a people who are worshippers.\qt@no{(106)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxc{%
And We have not sent thee except as a mercy unto the Worlds.\qt@no{(107)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxci{%
Say thou: this only hath been revealed unto me, that your god is only One God. submit ye then?!\qt@no{(108)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcii{%
Then if they turn away, say thou: I have proclaimed unto you all alike, and I know not whether nigh or far is that which ye are promised,\qt@no{(109)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxciii{%
Verily He knoweth that which is public in speech, and He knoweth that which ye hide.\qt@no{(110)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxciv{%
And know not; haply it may be a trial for you, and an enjoyment for a season.\qt@no{(111)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcv{%
He saith: my Lord! judge Thou with truth. And our Lord is the Compassionate Whose help is to be sought against that which ye utter.\qt@no{(112)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcvi{%
\basmalahen Mankind! fear your Lord; verily the quake of the Hour shall be a thing mighty.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcvii{%
The Day whereon ye behold it, every suckling woman shall forget that which she suckleth, and every burthened woman shall lay down her burthen; and thou shalt behold mankind as drunken, whereas drunken they will be not, but the torment of Allah shall be severe.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcviii{%
And of mankind is he who disputeth respecting Allah without knowledge, and followeth any Satan froward.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdxcix{%
Against whom it is prescribed, that: whosoever befriendeth him, him he shall lead astray and shall guide him on to the torment of the Flame.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdc{%
O Mankind! if ye be in doubt respecting the Resurrection, then We have created you of the dust, then of a drop, then of clot, then of a piece of flesh, formed and unformed, that We might manifest unto you Our power. And We settle in the wombs that which We will until a term determined. Then We bring you forth as babes, then We let you reach your maturity. And of you is he who dieth, and of you is he who is brought back to the most abject age, so that after knowing he knoweth not aught. Andthou beholdest the earth withered up, and when We send down thereon water, it stirreth and swelleth, and it groweth every luxuriant kind of growth.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdci{%
That, because Allah! He is The Truth, and He quickeneth the dead, and verily He is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcii{%
And because the Hour is coming- there is no doubt thereof-- and because Allah will raise up those who are in the graves.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdciii{%
And of mankind is he who disputeth respecting Allah without knowledge or guidance or a Book luminous.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdciv{%
Bending his neck, that he may lead astray from the way of Allah; his shall be humiliation in the world, and We shall make him taste on the Day of Judgment the torment of Burning.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcv{%
That is because of that which thy hands have sent forth, and verily Allah is not a wronger of His bondmen.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcvi{%
And of mankind is he who worshippeth Allah as on edge; if there befalleth him good, he in contented therewith, and if there befalleth him a trial, he turneth round on his face; he loseth the world and the Hereafter: that indeed is a loss manifest!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcvii{%
He calleth upon that, beside Allah, which can neither hurt him nor profit him! that! it is a straying far-off.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcviii{%
He calleth upon him whose hurt is nearer than his profit: surely ill the patron! ill the comrade!\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcix{%
Verily Allah shall cause those who believe and work righteous works to enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow; verily Allah doth whatsoever He intendeth.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcx{%
Whosoever hath been imagining that Allah shall not make him victorious in the world and the Hereafter, let him stretch a cord up to the heaven and let him cut it, and let him look if his stratagem can do away that whereat he enrageth.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxi{%
And Thus We have sent it down as evidences, and verily Allah guideth whomsoever He intendeth.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxii{%
Verily those who believe and those who are Judaised and the Sabians and the Nazarenes and the Magians and those who associate - verily Allah will decide between them on the Day of Judgment; verily Allah is over everything a Witness.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxiii{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah unto Him adore whosoever is in the heavens and on the earth, and the sun, and the moon, and the mountains, and the trees and the beasts, and many of mankind! And many are there on whom due is the torment. And whomsoever Allah despiseth, none can honour; verily Allah doth whatsoever He willeth.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxiv{%
These twain are opponents who contended respecting their Lord; then as for those who disbelieved, cut out for them shall be raiments of frre: poured out over their head shall be hot water.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxv{%
Molten thereby shall be that which is in their bellies and also their skins.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxvi{%
And for them shall be maces of iron.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxvii{%
So oft as they would seek to go forth therefrom, because of anguish, they shall be sent back therein, and taste the torment of Burning.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxviii{%
Verily Allah will cause those who believe and work righteous works to enter Gardens whereunder the rivers flow, wherein they will be bedecked with brace lets of gold and with pearls, and their garment therein shall be of silk.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxix{%
And they have been guided unto goodly speech, and they have been guided to the path of the Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxx{%
Verily those who disbelieve and hinder others from the path of Allah and from the Sacred Mosque which We have appointed for mankind, equal in respect thereunto are the dweller therein and the stranger. And whosoever will seek profanity therein wrongfully, We shall make him taste of a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxi{%
And recall what time We settled Ibrahim in the place of the House, Saying: associate not thou with Me aught, and purify My House for these who circumambulate and those who stand up and those who bow and make prostration.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxii{%
And proclaim thou among mankind the pilgrimage; they shall come unto thee on foot and on any lean mount, coming from every deep defile.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxiii{%
That they may witness the benefits to them and may mention the name of Allah on the days known over the beast cattle wherewith He hath provided them. So eat thereof, and feed the hungry poor.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxiv{%
Thereafter let them end their unkemptnesss and fulfil their vows and circumambulate the ancient House.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxv{%
Thus it is. And whosoever suspecteth the sacred ordinances of Allah, it shall be better for him with his Lord. And allowed unto you are the cattle, save that which hath been rehearsed unto you; so avoid the pollution of the idols, and avoid the word of falsehood.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxvi{%
Reclining unto Allah, not associating aught with Him. And whosoever associateth aught with Allah, it is as though he had fallen from the heaven and the birds had snatched him, or the wind had blown him to a place remote.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxvii{%
Thus it is. And whosoever respecteth the rites of Allah, then verily it is from piety of the hearts.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxviii{%
For you in them are benefits for a term appointed, and thereafter the destination is toward the ancient House.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxix{%
And unto every community We appointed a ritual, that they mention the name of Allah over the beast cattle wherewith He hath provided them: and your God is One God, so unto Him submit. And bear thou glad tidings unto the humble-\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxx{%
Those---whose hearts, when Allah is mentioned, are filled with awe and who patiently endure that which befalleth them, and these who establish the prayer and of that wherewith We have provided them expend.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxi{%
And the camels! We have appointed them for you among the landmarks of Allah; for you is good therein; so mention the name of Allah over them, standing in rows. Then when they fall down on their sides, eat thereof and feed the contented and suppliant. Thus We have subjected them to you, that haply ye may return thanks.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxii{%
Their flesh reacheth not Allah nor their blood: but it is Piety from you that reacheth Him. Thus He hath subjected them to you, that ye may magnify Allah for He hath guided you; and bear thou glad tidings unto the welldoers.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxiii{%
Verily Allah will repel from those who believe: verily Allah loveth not any treacherous, ingrate.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxiv{%
Permitted are those who are fought against, because they have been oppressed, and verily to succour them Allah is potent\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxv{%
Those who have been driven forth from their abodes without justice, except because they say: our Lord is Allah. And were it not for Allah's repelling of someby means of others, cloisters and churches, synogogues and mosques wherein the name of Allah is mentioned much, would have been pulled down. Surely Allah shall succour whosoever succoureth Him; verily Allah is strong, Mighty\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxvi{%
Those who if We establish them in the earth, shall establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and command that which is reputable and restrain that which is disreputable and unto Allah is the end of all affairs.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxvii{%
And if they belie thee, then surely there have belied before them the people of Nuh and the 'Aad and the Thamud.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxviii{%
And the people of Ibrahim and the people of Lut.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxxxix{%
And the denizens of Madyan. And belied was Musa. I gave rein to the infidels; then took hold of them; so how hath been My wrath!\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxl{%
How many a city have We destroyed, while it was a wrong- doer--and it lieth overturned on its roofs, -and how many a well abandoned and how many a castle fortifred!\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxli{%
Have they not marched forth in the land, so that there might become unto them hearts to understand with or ears re hear with? Verily it is not the sights that are blinded but blinded are the hearts that are in the breasts.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlii{%
And they ask thee to hasten on the torment, whereas Allah shall not fail His promise. And verily a day with thy Lord is as a thousand years of that which ye compute.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxliii{%
And how many a city did give reins to, While it wronged itself, then took hold of it! and unto Me is the return.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxliv{%
Say thou: mankind! I am unto you only a warner manifest.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlv{%
Then those who believe and work righteous works--for them is forgiveness and a provision honourable.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlvi{%
And those who endeavour in respect of Our signs to frustrate them- those shall be the fellows of Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlvii{%
And We have sent before thee no apostle or prophet but when he read the Satan cast forth suggestions in respect of his reading; then Allah abolisheth that which the Satan casteth forth; then Allah confirmeth His revelations; and Allah is Knowing. Wise;\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlviii{%
That he may make that which the Satan casteth forth a temptation for those in whose heart is a disease and whose hearts are hardened--and the wrong-doers are in divergence far-off -\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxlix{%
And that those who have been vouchsafed knowledge may know that it is the truth from thy Lord and may believe therein, and so their hearts may submit thereto. And verily Allah is the Guide of those who believe unto a path straight.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcl{%
And those who disbelieve will not cease to be in doubt thereof until the Hour cometh upon them on a sudden, or there cometh upon them the torment of a Barren Day.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcli{%
The dominion on that Day will be Allah's; He shall judge between them; then those who believed and worked righteous works shall be in the Gardens of Delight.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclii{%
And those who disbelieved and belied Our signs--then these! for them will be a torment ignominous.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcliii{%
And those who emigrated in the way of Allah, and thereafter they were slain or they died - surely Allah will provide them with a goodly provision; and verily Allah! He is the Best Provider.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcliv{%
Surely He will make them enter an entrance wherewith they will be well pleased and verily Allah is Knowing, Forbearing.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclv{%
That is so. And whosoever Chastiseth the like of that whereby He was injured, and thereafter he hath been ogain oppressed, surely Allah will succour him: verily Allah is Pardoning, Forgiving.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclvi{%
That is to be because Allah plungeth the night into the day and plungeth the day into the night, and because He is Hearing, Beholding.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclvii{%
That is because Allah! He is the Truth, and because that which they call upon beside Him--it is the false. And verily Allah! He is the High, the Great.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclviii{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah sendeth down water from the heaven and the earth becometh green? Verily Allah is subtile, Aware.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclix{%
His is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth; and verily Allah He is the Self-sufficient, the PraiseWorthy.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclx{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah hath subjected to Himself for you whatsoever is on the earth and the ships running in the sea by His command? And He with holdeth the heaven that it fall not on the earth save by His leave. Verily Allah is, unto mankind, Clement, Merciful.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxi{%
And He it is who gave you life and will thereafter cause you to die, and will thereafter give you life; verily man is ingrate.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxii{%
Unto every community We have appointed a rite which they perform. Let them not therefore contend with thee in the affair; and call them thou unto thy Lord, verily thou art on true guidance.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxiii{%
And if they dispute with thee, say thou: Allah knoweth best that which ye Work.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxiv{%
Allah will judge between you on the Day of Judgment concerning that wherein ye have been differing.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxv{%
Knowest thou of that Allah knoweth whatsoever is in the heaven and the earth? Verily that is in a Book; verily that is for Allah easy.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxvi{%
And they worship, beside Allah, that for which He hath revealed no authority and that whereof they have no knowledge; and for the wrong-doers there shall not be a helper.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxvii{%
And when Our manifest signs are rehearsed unto them, thou recognizest repugnance on the countenaces of those who disbelieve; well- nigh they rush upon these who rehearse unto them Our Signs. Say thou: shall declare unto you something more grievous than that-the Fire--Allah hath promised it to those who disbelieve? An evil destination!\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxviii{%
O Mankind! a similitude is propounded; so hearken thereto. Verily those whom ye call upon beside Allah will by no means create a fly, even though they assembled for that; and if the fly were to snatch away aught from them, they cannot recover it from him: weak the seeker and the sought!\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxix{%
They have not estimated Allah His rightful estimate; verily Allah is strong, Mighty!\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxx{%
Allah chooseth from the angels messengers and also from mankind; verily Allah is Hearing, Beholding.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxi{%
He knoweth whatsoever is before them and whatsoever is behind them; and unto Allah are returned all affairs\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxii{%
O Ye who believe! bow down and prostrate yourselves and worship your Lord, and do the good, that haply ye may thrive.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxiii{%
And strive hard for Allah as is due unto Him hard striving. He hath distinguished you, and hath not placed upon you any narrowness in the religion the faith of your father, Ibrahim. He hath named you Muslim aforetime and in this, that the apostle may be a witness for you, and that ye may be witnesses against mankind. Wherefore establish the prayer and'give the poor-rate, and hold fast by Allah; He is your Patron: an Excellent Patron and Excellent helper!\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxiv{%
\basmalahen Blissful are the believers'-\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxv{%
Those who in their prayer are lowly.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxvi{%
And those who from everything vain turn away.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxvii{%
And those who for the sake of purification are doers.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxviii{%
And those who of their private Parts are guards.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxix{%
Save in regard to their spouses and those whom their right hands own: so they are not blameworthy-\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxx{%
And Whosoever seeketh beyond that, then it is these who are the transgressors\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxi{%
And those who of their trusts and covenant are keepers.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxii{%
And those who of their prayers are observant.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxiii{%
These! they are the inheritors.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxiv{%
Who shall inherit Paradise; therein they shall be abiders.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxv{%
And assuredly We created man of an extract of clay.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxvi{%
Thereafter We made him of a Sperm In a receptacle safe.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxvii{%
-Thereafter We created the sperm a clot; then We created the clot a lump of flesh; then We created the lump of flesh bones; then We clothed the bones with flesh: thereafter We brought him forth as anot her creature. Blest then be Allah, the Best of creators!\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxviii{%
Then verily, thereafter, ye are sure to die.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdclxxxix{%
Then verily on the Day of Judgment ye shall be raised up.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxc{%
And assuredly We created above you seven paths, and of the creation We have not been neglectful.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxci{%
And We sent down from the heaven water in measure, and We caused it to settle in the earth; and verily to take it away We are Able.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcii{%
Then We brought forth for you therewith gardens of date- palm and vines; for you therein are fruits many, and thereof ye eat.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxciii{%
And also a tree that springeth forth from mount Sinai, that groweth oil and is a sauce for the eaters.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxciv{%
And verily in the cattle for you is a lesson. We give you to drink of that which is in their bellies, and for you in them are advantages many, and of them ye eat.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcv{%
And on them and on the ship ye are borne.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcvi{%
And assuredly We sent Nuh unto his people, and he said: O my people! worship Allah; for you there is no god but he; will ye not then fear Him!\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcvii{%
Then said the chiefs of those who disbelieved among his people: this is no other than a human being like unto you, he seeketh to make himself superior unto; and if God had willed, He would save sent down angels; we have not heard of this among our fathers ancient.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcviii{%
He is only a man in whom is madness wherefore await for him for a season.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcxcix{%
Nuh said: my Lord! vindicate me, for they belie me.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcc{%
Then We revealed unto him, saying: build the ark under Our eyes and Our Revelation; then when Our command cometh and the oven boileth over, make way therein of every pair two, and thy household save him thereof against whom there hath already gone forth the word; and address me not in respect of those who have done wrong; verily they are to be drowned.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcci{%
And when thou art settled, thou and those with thee, in the ark, say thou: praise unto Allah who hath delivered us from the wrong doing people.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccii{%
And say thou, my Lord! cause me to land at a landing blest, and thou art the Best of these who bring to land.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcciii{%
Verily in that are signs; verily We have ever been provers.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcciv{%
Then, after them We brought forth anot her generation.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccv{%
Then We sent amongst them an apostle from amongst themselves, saying: worship Allah, for you there is no god but he; will ye then not fear Him?\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccvi{%
And said the chiefs of those who disbelieved among his people and belied the meeting of the Hereafter and whom We had luxuriated in the life of the World: this is no other than a human being like unto you: he eateth of that whereof ye eat, and he drinketh of that which ye drink.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccvii{%
And were ye to obey a human being like you, ye are forthwith to be losers.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccviii{%
Promiseth he unto you that ye, when ye have died and have become dust and bones, ye are to be brought forth?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccix{%
Away! away with that wherewith ye are promised;\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccx{%
There is nought but our life of the world; we die and we live, and we are not going to be raised Up.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxi{%
He is but a man who hath fabricated against God a lie, and in him we are not going to be believers.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxii{%
He said: my Lord! vindicate for they belie me.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxiii{%
Allah said: after a little while they will become regretful.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxiv{%
Then the shout laid hold of them in truth, and We made them a refuse; so away with the wrong-doing people!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxv{%
Then after them We brought forth other generations.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxvi{%
No community can anticipate their term, nor can they lay behind.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxvii{%
Thereafter We sent Our apostles, successively. So oft as there came unto a community their apostle, they belied him, so We made them follow one anot her, and We made them bywords: so away with a people who believe not!\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxviii{%
Thereafter We sent Musa and his brother Harun with Our signs and an authority manifest.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxix{%
Unto Fir'awn and his chiefs, but they grew stiff-necked, and they were a people self-exalting.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxx{%
So they said: shall we believe In two human beings like unto us, while their nation are to us slaves?\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxi{%
Then they belied the twain; so they became of those who were destroyed.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxii{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed unto Musa the Book, that haply they may be guided.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxiii{%
And We made the son of Maryam and his mother a sign; and We sheltered the twain on a height: a quiet abode and running water.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxiv{%
O Ye apostles! eat the good things and work righteously; verily of that which ye work I am the Knower.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxv{%
And verily this religion of yours is one religion, and I am your Lord, so fear Me.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxvi{%
Then they cut their affair among them in regard to the Scriptures: each band in that which is with them rejoicing.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxvii{%
Wherefore leave thou them in their bewilderment for a season.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxviii{%
Deem they that in the wealth and sons wherewith We enlarge them.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxix{%
We are hastening them on to good things? Aye! they perceive not.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxx{%
Verily those who for fear of their Lord are in awe.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxi{%
And those who in the signs of their Lord do believe.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxii{%
And those who with their Lord associate not anyone.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxiii{%
And those who give whatsoever they give, while their hearts are anxious that unto their Lord they are to be retutners\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxiv{%
These are hastening on to good, and they are therein foremost.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxv{%
And We task not any soul except according to its capacity, and with Us is a book speaking with truth, and they will not be wronged.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxvi{%
Aye! their hearts are in bewilderment in respect thereof, and they have works beside that, of which they are workers.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxvii{%
Until when We lay hold of the luxuriant ones of them with the torment, and lo! then they are imploring!\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxviii{%
Implore not to-day; verily ye from Us are not to be succoured.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxxxix{%
Surely My signs have been rehearsed unto you, and upon your heel ye were wont to draw back.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxl{%
Stiff-necked, discoursing thereof by night, reviling.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxli{%
Pondered they not over the Word? or came there unto them that which came not unto their fathers ancient?\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlii{%
Or, is it that they recognised not their apostle, and so of him they become deniers?\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxliii{%
Or, say they: in him is madness? O Aye he brought them the truth, and most of them to the truth are averse.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxliv{%
And were the truth to follow their desires there would have been corrupted the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is therein. Aye! We have come to them with their admonition; so it is from their admonition that they turn away.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlv{%
Or, is it that thou askest of them any maintenance? The maintenance of thy Lord is better, and He is the Best of providers.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlvi{%
And verily thou! thou callest them unto a Path straight.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlvii{%
And verily those who believe not in the Hereafter are from the path deviating.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlviii{%
And though We have mercy on them We may remove whatsoever of hurt is with them, surely they would persist in their exorbitance, wandering perplexed.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxlix{%
And assuredly We took hold of them with the torment, yet they humbled not themselves to their Lord, nor did they entreat.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccl{%
Until when we shall open upon them a portal of severe torment, and lo! thereat they are desparing\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccli{%
And He it is Who brought forth for you hearing and sight and hearts, little thanks ye give!\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclii{%
And He it is Who spread you on the earth, and unto Him ye will be gathered.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccliii{%
And He it is Who quickeneth and causeth to die, and His is the alternation of night and day; will ye not then reflect?\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccliv{%
Aye! they say the like of that which said the ancients.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclv{%
They say: when we are dead, and have become dust and bones, shall we verily be raised up?\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclvi{%
Assuredly this we have been promised--we and our fathers-- aforetime: naught is this but the fables of the ancients.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclvii{%
Say thou: whose is the earth and whosoever is therein, if you know?\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclviii{%
They will surely say: God's. Say thou: will ye not then heed?\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclix{%
Say thou: who is Lord of the seven heavens and Lord of the mighty throne?\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclx{%
They will surely say: God. Say thou: will ye not then fear?\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxi{%
Saythou: in whose hands is the governance of everything, and who sheltereth but from whom none is sheltered, if ye know?\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxii{%
They will surely say: God's. Say thou: how then are ye turned away?\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxiii{%
Aye! We have brought them the truth and verily they are the liars.\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxiv{%
Allah hath not betaken to Himself any son, and there is not along Him any god; else each god would have gone off with that which he had created, and one of them would have exalted himself above the others. Hallowed be Allah above that which they ascribe!\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxv{%
Knower of the unseen and the seen, Exalted is He above that which they associate!\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxvi{%
Say thou; my Lord! if Thou wilt shew me that wherewith they are threatened.\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxvii{%
My Lord! then place me not among the wrong-doing people.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxviii{%
And verily to shew them that wherewith We threaten them We are surely Able.\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxix{%
Repel thou the evil with that which is the best, We are the Best Knower of that which they utter.\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxx{%
And say thou: my Lord! I seek refuge with Thee against the whisperings of the satans;\qt@no{(97)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxi{%
And I seek refuge with Thee, my Lord! lest they may be present with me\qt@no{(98)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxii{%
lt ceaseth not until when death cometh to one of them, and he saith: my Lord! send me back.\qt@no{(99)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxiii{%
That I may work righteously in that which have left. By no means! It is but a word he uttereth; and before them is a barrier until the Day when they shall be raised.\qt@no{(100)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxiv{%
Then when the Trumpet is blown there will be no lineage among them that Day, nor will they ask of each other.\qt@no{(101)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxv{%
Then he whose balances shall be heavy --these! they are the blissful ones.\qt@no{(102)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxvi{%
And he whose balances shall be light--these are they who have lost themselves: in Hell they are abiders.\qt@no{(103)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxvii{%
The Fire will scorch their faces, and therein they shall be grinning.\qt@no{(104)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxviii{%
Have not My revelations been rehearsed unto you, and them ye have been belying?\qt@no{(105)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxix{%
They will say: our Lord! our wretchedness overcame, us, and we have been a people erring.\qt@no{(106)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxx{%
O our Lord! take us forth from it: then if we return, we shall be wrong-doers indeed.\qt@no{(107)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxi{%
He shall say: slink away there unto, and speak not unto Me.\qt@no{(108)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxii{%
Verily there was a party of My bondmen who said: our Lord! we have believed, wherefore forgive us and have mercy upon us, and Thou art the Best of the merciful ones!\qt@no{(109)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxiii{%
Then ye took them mockingly, so that they caused you to forget remembrance of Me, and at them ye were wont to laugh.\qt@no{(110)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxiv{%
Verily I have recompensed them today for they bear patiently, verily they! are the achievers.\qt@no{(111)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxv{%
He will say: how long tarried ye on the earth in number of year?\qt@no{(112)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxvi{%
-They will say we tarried a day or part of a day; ask those who keep count.\qt@no{(113)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxvii{%
He will say: ye tarried a little indeed; would that ye had known that:\qt@no{(114)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxviii{%
Deem ye that We have created youl in vain and that unto Us ye are not to be returned?\qt@no{(115)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcclxxxix{%
So exalted be Allah, the True King! there is no god but he, Lord of the Throne honoured.\qt@no{(116)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxc{%
And whosoever calleth, along with Allah, unto anot her god, of whom he hath no warranty, then his reckoning is only with his Lord; verily thrive will not the infidels.\qt@no{(117)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxci{%
And say thou: my Lord! forgive and have mercy, and Thou art the Best of the merciful ones.\qt@no{(118)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcii{%
\basmalahen This is a chapter which We have sent down, and which We have ordained; and therein We have sent down revelations manifest, that haply ye may be admonished.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxciii{%
The adulteress and the adulterer: scourge each one of the twain with a hundred stripes. And let not tenderness rake hold of you in regarad to the twain in the law of Allah, if ye have come to believe in Allah and the Last Day. And let witness this torment a band of the believers.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxciv{%
The adulterer weddeth not but an adulteress or an associatoress: and the adulteress! --none weddeth her save an adulterer or an associator; and that is forbidden unto the believers.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcv{%
And those who accuse clean wowomen and then bring not four eyewitnesses, Scourge them with eighty stripes and accept not their- testimony for Ever. And these! they are the transgressors\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcvi{%
Excepting those who thereafter shall repent and make amends. Verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcvii{%
And as for those who accuse their wives and there are not for them witnesses except themselves, the testimony of one of them shall be four testimonies by Allah: that verily he is of the truth-tellers\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcviii{%
And the fifth, that the curse of Allah be upon him if he be of the liars.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccxcix{%
And it will revert the chastisement from her if she testifieth by Allah four times that verily he is of the liars.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccc{%
And the fifth that Allah's wrath be upon her if he is of the truthtellers.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccci{%
And had it not been for the grace of Allah and His mercy unto you and that Allah is Relenting, Wise, ye had been lost.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccii{%
Verily those who brought forward the calumny were a small band among Deem it not an evil for you; nay, it was good for you. Unto every one of them shall be that which he hath earned of the sin, and he among them who undertook the bulk of it---for him shall be a torment mighty.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccciii{%
Wherefore, when ye heard it, did not the believing men and believing women imagine best of their own people and say: this is a calumny manifest!\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccciv{%
Wherefore did they not bring four witnesses thereof? Then when they brought not the witnesses, those! with Allah they are the liars.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccv{%
Had there not been Allah's grace upon you and His mercy in the World and the Hereafter, surely there would have touched you for that whcrein ye had rushed, torment mighty--\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccvi{%
When ye were publishing it with your tongues and saying that with your mouths of which ye had no knowledge. Ye deemed it light, and it was with Allah mighty!\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccvii{%
And wherefore, when ye heard it, did ye not say: it is not for us to speak thereof, hallowed be Thou! that is a slander mighty!\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccviii{%
Allah exhorteth you lest ye may ever revert to the like thereof, if ye are believers indeed.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccix{%
And Allah expoundeth unto you the revelations and Allah is Knowing, wise.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccx{%
Verily those who love that in decency should be propagated regarding those who believe, for them shall be a torment afflictive in the world and the Hereafter. And Allah knoweth, and ye know not.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxi{%
And had there not been Allah's grace upon you and His mercy, and that Allah was Tender and Merciful, ye had Perished.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxii{%
O Ye who believe! follow not the footsteps of the Satan. And whosoever followeth the footsteps of the Satan, then he only urgeth to indecency and abomination. And had there not been the grace of Allah upon you and His mercy, not one of you would ever have been cleansed; but Allah cleanseth whomsoever He Will and Allah is Hearing, Knowing.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxiii{%
And let not the owners of affluence and amplitude among you swear off from giving unto the kindred and the needy and the emigrants in the way of Allah; let them pardon and overlook. Love ye not that Allah should forgive you And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxiv{%
verily those who accuse chaste. unknowing, - believing women, shall be cursed in the world and the Hereafter; and for them shall be a torment mighty.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxv{%
On the Day whereon their tongues and their hands and their feet will bear witness against them regarding that which they were wont to work.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxvi{%
On that Day Allah shall pay them in full their recompense, and they shall know that Allah! He is the True, the Manifest.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxvii{%
Vile women are for vile men, and vile men are for vile women, and clean women are for Clean men, and clean men are for clean women; these are quit of that which the people say: for them is forgiveness and a provision honoured.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxviii{%
O Ye who believe! enter not houses other than your own until ye have asked leave and invoked peace on the inmates thereof. That is better for you, haply ye may take heed.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxix{%
Then if ye find no one therein, enter not until leave hath been given you. And if it iaid unto you go back, then go back. It is Cleaner for you, and Allah is of that which ye work knower.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxx{%
No fault it is upon you that ye enter houses uninhabited wherein there is some property for you; and Allah knoweth that which you disclose and that which ye hide.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxi{%
Say thou unto the believers that they shall lower their sights and guard their private parts, that is cleaner for them; verlly Allah is Aware of that which they perform.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxii{%
And say thou unto the believing women that they shall lower their sights and guard their private parts and shall not disclose their adornment except that which appeareth thereof; and they shall draw their scarves over their bosoms; and shall not disclose their adornment except unto their husbands or their fathers or their husbands fathers or their sons or their husbands sons or their brothers or their brothers sons or their sisters sons or their Women or those whom their right hands own or male followers wanting in sex desire or children not acquainted with the privy parts of women; and they Shall not strike their feet so that there be known that which they hide of their adornment. And turn penitently unto Allah ye all, O ye believers, haply ye may thrive!\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxiii{%
And wed the single among you and the fit ones among your male and female slaves; if they are poor, Allah will enrich them of His grace; Allah is Ample, Knowing.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxiv{%
And those who find not means to marry shall restrain themselves until Allah enricheth them of His grace. And from among those whom your right hands own those who seek a writing- write it for them if ye know in them any good, and vouchsafe unto them of the wealth of Allah which He hath vouchsafed unto you. And constrain not your bedmaids to harlotry if they would live chastely, in order that ye may seek the chance gain of the life of the world. And whosoever will constrain them, then verily Allah is--after their constraint--Forgiving, Mercifu1.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxv{%
And assuredly We have sent down unto you revelations illuminating and a similitude for those who passed away before you and an exhortation unto the God-fearing.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxvi{%
Allah is the light of the heavens and the earth: the likeness of His light is as a niche wherein is a lamp; the lamp is in glass; the glass is as though it were a star brilliant; lit from a tree blest, an olive, neither in the east nor in the west; well-nigh its oil would glow forth even though fire touch it not. light upon light. Allah guideth unto His light whomsoever He will: And Allah propoundeth similitudes for mankind: verily Allah is of everything the Knower.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxvii{%
They worship in houses which Allah has bidden to be exalted and His name to be remembered therein; they hallow Him therein in mornings and evenings-\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxviii{%
Men whom neither trafficking nor bargaining diverteth from the remembrance of Allah and the establishment of the prayer and the giving of the poor-rate, fearing a Day whereon upset will be the hearts and sights.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxix{%
That Allah may recompense them the best for that which they worked and may increase unto them of His grace, and Allah provideth for whomsoever He will without measure.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxx{%
And those who disbelieve--their works are like a mirage in a desert which the thirsty deemeth to be water, until when he cometh thereto he findeth not aught, and findeth Allahs with himself, and He payeth him his account in full; and Allah is swift at reckoning.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxi{%
Or, like the darknesses in a sea deep; there covereth it a wave from above it, a wave from above it, above which is a cloud: darknesses one above anot her: when he putteth out his hand well-nigh he seeth it not. And upto whomsoever Allah shall not appoint a light, his shall be no light.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxii{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah --those hallow Him whosoever is in the heavens and the earth and the birds with wings outspread? Surely each one knoweth his prayer and his hallowing; and Allah is the Knower of that which they do.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxiii{%
And Allah's is the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and unto Allah is the return.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxiv{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah driveth a cloud along, then combineth it, then maketh it a heap, and then thou beholdest the fine rain come forth from the interstices thereof? And He sendeth down from the heaven mountains wherein is hail, then afflicteth therewith whomsoever He will, and averteth it from whomsoever He will: wellnigh the flash of His lightening taketh away the sights.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxv{%
Allah turneth the night and the day over and over; verily therein is a lesson for men of insight.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxvi{%
Allah hath created every moving creature of water; of them is one that walketh upon his belly. and of them is one that walketh upon its two feet; and of them is one that walketh upon four. Allah createth whatsoever He listeth; verily Allah is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxvii{%
Assuredly We have sent down revelations illuminating: and Allah guideth whomsoever He listeth unto a path straight.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxviii{%
And they say: we have believed in Allah and in the apostle and we have obeyed; then there backslide a party of them thereafter: and these are not believers.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxxxix{%
And when they are called to Allah and His apostle that he may judge between them, lo! a party of them are averters.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxl{%
And if right had been theirs, they would have come to him readily.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxli{%
Is in their hearts a disease? or doubt they? or fear they that Allah shall misjudge them, as also His apostle? Aye! these are the very wrong-doers!\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlii{%
-The only saying of the believers when they were called to Allah and His apostle thathe might judge between them was that they said: We hear and we obey. And these! they are the very ones blissful.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxliii{%
And whosoever obeyeth Allah and His apostle, and dreadeth Allah and feareth him-these! they are the achievers.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxliv{%
And they swear by Allah with their solemn oaths that, if thou commandest them they will surely go forth. Say thou: swear not, obedience is recognize! verily Allah is Aware of that which ye Work.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlv{%
Say thou: obey Allah and obey the apostle; then if ye turn away, upon him is only that wherewith he hath been laid upon, and upon you is that wherewith ye have been laid upon; if ye obey him, ye will be guided; and naught is upon the apostle except the preaching plain.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlvi{%
Allah hath promised those of you who believe and work the righteous works that he shall make them successors on the earth even as He had made those before them successors, and that he shall surely establish for them their religion which He hath approved for them, and that he shall surely exchange unto them after their fear a security, provided they worship Me, associating not aught with Me; and whosoever will disbelieve thereafter, then those! they are the transgressors.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlvii{%
And establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and obey the apostle, haply ye may be shewn mercy.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlviii{%
Deem not those who disbelieve able to frustrate His Purpose on the earth; and their abode shall be the Fire--an ill retreat!\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxlix{%
O Ye who believe! let those whom your right hands own and those of you who have not attained puberty ask leave of you three times before the dawn prayer, and when ye lay aside your garments noonday, and after the night-prayer: three at times of privacy for you. NO fault there is upon you or upon them beyond these times going round upon you, some of you upon some others. In this wise Allah expoundeth unto you the commandments; and Allah is Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccl{%
And when the children among you attain puberty, then let them ask leave even as those before them asked leave. In this wise Allah expoundeth unto you His commandments; and Allah is Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccli{%
And past child-bearing women who have no hope of wedlock-- upon them it is no fault that they lay aside their outer garments, not flaunting their adornment. And that they should restrain themselves is better for them; Allah is Hearing, Knowing.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclii{%
No restriction is there upon the blind, nor is there the restriction upon a lame, nor is there a restriction upon the sick. nor upon yourselves that ye eat in your houses or the houses of your fathers or the houses of your mothers or the houses of your brothers or the houses of your sisters or the houses of your fathers brothers or the houses of your fathers sisters or the houses of your mothers brothers or the houses of your mothers sisters or from that house where of ye own the keys or from the house of a friend. No fault is there upon you whether ye eat together or in separate groups, Then when ye enter houses, salute each other with a greeting from before Allah, blest and goodly. Thus Allah expoundeth unto you the revelations, haply ye may reflect.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccliii{%
The believers are those alone who have believed in Allah and His apostle, and when they are with him on some affair collecting People together they depart not Until they have asked his leave. Verily those who ask thy leave, those are they who believe in Allah and His apostle. So if they ask thy leave for some business of theirs, give thou leave unto whomsoever of them thou wilt, and ask thou forgiveness of Allah for them. Verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccliv{%
Place not the apostle's calling among you on the same footing as your calling of each other. Of a surety Allah knoweth those who slip away privately; let therefore those who oppose His commandment beware lest there befall them a trial or there befall them a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclv{%
Lo! verily Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth; surely He knoweth that which ye are about and the Day whereon they shall be made to return unto Him; then He shall declare unto them that which they worked; and Allah is of everything the Knower.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclvi{%
\basmalahen Blest be He who hath revealed the Criterion unto His bondman thathe may be unto the worlds a warner.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclvii{%
He whose is the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and who hath not taken a son, and for whom there is not an associate in the dominion, and who hath created everything, and measured it according to a measurement.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclviii{%
And they have taken beside Him gods creating not aught and are themselves created, owning for themselves neither hurt nor benefit, and owning not death nor life nor resurrection.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclix{%
And those who disbelieve, say. this is naught but a falsehood thathe hath fabricated and there have assisted him therein other people. so surelythey have aimed at a wrong and a fraud.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclx{%
And they say: fables of the ancients which he hath had written down, so they are dictated unto him, morning and evening.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxi{%
Say thou; He hath sent it down Who knoweth the secret of the heavens and the earth; verily He is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxii{%
And they say: what aileth this apostle: he eateth food and walketh about the market-places: wherefore is not an angel sent down unto him, so thathe may be along with him a warner '\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxiii{%
Or, whereforeis not there cast down unto him a treasure or he has a garden whereof he may eat! And the wrong-doeray: ye follow only a man bewitched.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxiv{%
Behold how they propound similitudes for thee! so they have strayed and cannot find a way.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxv{%
Blest is He Who, if He willed, shall appoint for them something better than that: gardens whereunder the rivers flow, and appoint for them palaces.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxvi{%
Aye! they belie the Hour; and We have gotten ready for him who belieth the Hour a Flame.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxvii{%
When it beholdeth them from afar, they shall hear it raging and roaring.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxviii{%
And when they are flung into a strait place thereof, bound Up, they shall call therein unto death.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxix{%
Call not to-day for a single death but call for death manifold.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxx{%
Say thou: in that better or Garden of Abidence that hath been promised to the God-fearing! It shall be theirs as a recompense and a retreat.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxi{%
Theirs therein shall be all that they wish for, as abiders; a promise from thy Lord to be asked for.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxii{%
And on the Dav whereon He will gather them and that v; hich they worship beside Allah and will say. are ye the ones who sent astray these My bondmen; or strayed they themselves from the way!\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxiii{%
They will say; hallowed be Thou! it behoved us not that we should take beside Thee any patron, but Thou allovvedest them and their fathers enjoyment Until they forgat the admonition, and they were a people doomed.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxiv{%
So now they belie you in that which ye said; so ye are not able to obtain diversion nor help. And who soever of you doth wrong, him We shall make taste a great torment.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxv{%
And We have not sent before thee ony of the sent ones but verily they ate food and walked about in the market places. And We have made some of you unto some others a temptation; will ye have patience! And thy Lord is ever a Beholder. pART XIX\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxvi{%
And those who fear not the meeting with Usl say: wherefore are not angels sent down unto us or wherefore we see not our Lord! Assuredly they have proven stiff-necked in their souls and have exceeded the bounds with excess great.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxvii{%
The Day whereon they shall behold the angels on that day there will be nea joy for the culprits, and they will say: away! away!\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxviii{%
And We shall set upon that which they worked, and shall make it as dust wind-scattered.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxix{%
Fellows of the Garden shall be on that Day in a goodly abode and a gocdly re pose.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxx{%
And on the Day whereon the heaven shall be rent asunderg from the q clouds and the angelhall be sent downll with a great descending.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxi{%
The dominion on that Day rhall is; be the true dominion, of the Compassionate, l and it shall be anday upon the infidels hard.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxii{%
On the Day when the wrong-doer shall gnaw his hands saying: would that had taken with the apostle a way!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxiii{%
Ah! woe unto me! wouldthat had never taken such a one for a friend!\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxiv{%
Assuredly he misled me from the admonition after it had come unto ine. Verily the Satan is ever unto man a betrayer.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxv{%
And the Apostle will say: my lord! verily my people too k this Qur'an as a thing to be shunned.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxvi{%
And even scals We appointed unto every prophet an enemy from among the culprits. And thine Lord sufficeth as GUide and Helper.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxvii{%
And those who disbelieve say: wherefore is the Qur'an not revealed unto him entire at once! Thus---We reveal- that We may establish thy heart there with; and We have repeated it with a repetition.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxviii{%
And they come not unto thee with a similitude but We bring thee the truth and an excellent interpretation.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdccclxxxix{%
They who shall be gathered prone on their faces unto Hell-- those shall be worst in respect of place and the most astray in respect of path.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxc{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed unto Musa the Book and We placed with him his brother Harun as a minister.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxci{%
Then We said: go ye twain unto a people who have belied Our signs. Then We annihilated them an utter annihilation.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcii{%
And the people of Nuh! When they belied the apostles We drowned them, and made them a sign unto mankind. And We have gotten ready unto the wrong-doers a torment afflictive,\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxciii{%
And the 'Aad and the Thamud and the dwellers of the pass and generations in-between many.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxciv{%
And unto each! We propounded similitude thereunto; and each We ruined an utter ruin.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcv{%
And assuredly they have gone by the township whereon was rained the evil rain. Are they not wont to see it? Aye! they expect not Resurrection.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcvi{%
And when they behold thee, they hold thee up for mockery: is this the one whom Allah hath sent as an apostle\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcvii{%
Well nigh he had led us astray from our gods if we had not persevered towards them. Presently they shall know, When they behold the torment, who, more astray in respect of path.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcviii{%
Hast thou observed him who hath taken as his god his own desire! wilt thou be over him a trustee?\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmdcccxcix{%
Or deemest thou that most of them hear or understand? They are but like unto the cattle; nay, they are even farther astray from the path.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcm{%
Hast thou not observed thine lord-how He hath stretched out the shadow? And if He had willed He would have made it still. Then We have made the sun for it an indication.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmi{%
Then We draw it toward Us with an easy drawing.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmii{%
And it is He who hath made for you the night a covering, and the sleep; repose, and hath made the day a resurrection.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmiii{%
And it is He who sendeth fort the winds as a herald before His mercy and We send down from the heaven water pure.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmiv{%
That We may quicken thereby a dead land, and We give drink thereof to that which We have created of cattle and human beings many.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmv{%
And We set it forth among them, that they may be admonished, but most men begrudge aught save infidelity.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmvi{%
And if We had willed, We would have raised up in each town a warner.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmvii{%
Se obey not thou the infidels, but strive against them therewith with a great striving.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmviii{%
And it is He who hath mixed the two seas: this, sweet ond thirst quenching; that, saltish ond bitter; and hath placed between the twain a barrier and a great partition complete.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmix{%
And it is He who hath created man from water, and then made for him kinship by blood and marriage. And thy Lord is ever potent.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmx{%
And yet they worship, besides Allah, that which can neither benefit them nor hurt them; and the infidel is ever an aider of the devil against his Lord.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxi{%
And We sent thee but as a bearer of glad tidings and warner.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxii{%
Say thou. ask of you no hire for this, save that whosoever will may take unto his Lord a way.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxiii{%
And trust thou in the Living One who dieth not, and hallow His praise; it sufficeth that he of the sins of His bondmen is Aware.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxiv{%
Who created the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in- between them in six days, then He established Himself on the Throne -the Compassionate! so, concernin Him, ask any one informed.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxv{%
And when it is said unto them: prostrate yourselves unto the Compassionate, they say: and what is the Compassionate? Shall we prostrate ourselves unto that which thou commandest us? And it increaseth in them aversion.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxvi{%
Blest be He Who hath placed big stars in the heaven, and hath placed therein a lamp and a moon enlightening.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxvii{%
And it is He Who hath appointed the night and the day a succession, for him who desireth to consider or desireth to be grateful.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxviii{%
And the bondmen of the Compassionate are those Who Walk upon the earth meekly and when the ignorant address them, they say peace\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxix{%
And these who pass the night before their Lord, prostrate and standing up.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxx{%
And these who say: our Lord! avert from us the torment of Hell verily the torment thereof is perishment.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxi{%
Verily ill it is as an abode and as a station.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxii{%
And those who when they expend, are neither extravagant nor sparing, and it is a medium in-between.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxiii{%
And those who call not unto anot her god along with Allah and slay not any soul which Allah hath forbidden, save in justification, and commit not fornication. And Whosoever shall do this, Shall incur the meed.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxiv{%
Multiplied for him shall be the torment on the Day of Resurrection, and he shall therein abide disgraced.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxv{%
Save him who repenteth and believeth and worketh righteous work. Then these! for them Allah shall change their vices into virtues. Verily Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxvi{%
And whosoever repenteth and worketh righteously, then verily he repenteth toward Allah with a true repentance.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxvii{%
And those who witness not falsehood, and when they pass by some vanity pass by with dignity.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxviii{%
And those who, when they are admonished by the commands of Allah, fall not down thereat, deaf and blind.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxix{%
And those who say: our Lord bestow on us coolness of eyes from our wives and our offspring, and make us unto the God-fearing a pattern.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxx{%
Those shall be rewarded with the highest apartment, because they persevered. and therein they shall be met with a greeting and salutation-\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxi{%
Abiders therein: excellent it is as an abode and as a station.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxii{%
Say thou: my Lord careth not for you were it not for your prayer. whereas ye have even belied, so presently this denial shall come as the cleaving punishment.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxiii{%
\basmalahen Ta. Sin Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxiv{%
These are the verses of a Book luminous.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxv{%
Belike thou shalt kill thyself with grief because they become not believers.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxvi{%
If We list, We can send down unto them a sign from the heaven so that their necks would became to it submissive.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxvii{%
And there cometh not unto them any fresh admonition from the Compassionate but they are wont to be there from backsliders.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxviii{%
So they have surely belied; wherefore anon there shall come unto them the truth of that whereat they were wont to mock.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxxxix{%
Observe they not the earth, how much We make to grow therein of every fruitful kind?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxl{%
Verily therein is a sign; yet most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxli{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlii{%
And recall what time thy Lord called unto Musa, saying: go thou unto the wrong-doing people.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxliii{%
The people of Fir'awn; fear they Me not?\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxliv{%
He said: my Lord! verily I fear they shall belie me.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlv{%
And my breast straiteneth, and my tongue moveth not quickly: so send for Harun.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlvi{%
And they have a crime against me, so I fear that they shall slay me.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlvii{%
He said: by no means. so go ye twain with Our signs; verily We shall be with you listening.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlviii{%
So go ye twain unto Fir'awn and say: verily we are the apostles of the Lord of the Worlds,\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxlix{%
Send with us the Children of Isra'il?\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcml{%
Fir'awn said: brought we not thee up amongst us as a child? And thou tarriedst amongst us for many years of thy life?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmli{%
And thou didst that thy deed which thou didst; and thou art of the ingrates.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlii{%
He said: I did it then when I was mistaken.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmliii{%
Then I fled from you when I feared you, and my Lord bestowed on me wisdom and made me one of the sent ones.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmliv{%
And that favour wherewith thou didst oblige me was that thou hadst enslaved the Children of Isra'il?\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlv{%
Fir'awn said. and what is the Lord of the worlds?\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlvi{%
He said: Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in-between, if ye seek to be convinced.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlvii{%
Fir'awn said unto those around him: hear ye not?\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlviii{%
He said: your Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlix{%
Fir'awn said: verily your apostle who hath been sent unto you is mad.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlx{%
He said: Lord of the east and the west and whatsoever is in-between, if ye understand.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxi{%
Fir'awn said: if thou wilt take a god other than me, I shall surely place thee among the prisoners.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxii{%
He said: even though I bring unto thee something manifest?\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxiii{%
Fir'awn said: forth with it then, if thou art of the truth- tellers.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxiv{%
Then he cast down his staff, and lo! it was a serpent manifest.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxv{%
And he drew forth his hand, and lo! it was white unto the beholders.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxvi{%
Fir'awn said unto the chiefs around him: verily this is a magician knowing.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxvii{%
He would drive you out of your land through his magic; what then is it ye command?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxviii{%
They said: put off him and his brother, and send unto the cities callers.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxix{%
Thot they may bring to thee every magician knowing.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxx{%
So the magicians were assembled at a set time on a day made known.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxi{%
And it was said unto the people: are ye going to assemble.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxii{%
Belike we may follow the magicians if they are the winners?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxiii{%
Then when the magicians came, they said unto Fir'awn: will there surely be a big hire for us if we are the winners?\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxiv{%
He said: yea; and ye shall verily then be of those brought nigh.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxv{%
Musa said unto them: cast whatsoever ye have to cast.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxvi{%
Then they cast their cords and their staves, and said: by the might of Fir'awn, verily we! we shall be the winners.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxvii{%
Then Musa cast down his staff, and lo! it swallowed up that which they had devised.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxviii{%
Then the magicians flung themselves prostrate.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxix{%
They said: we believe in the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxx{%
The Lord of Musa and Harun.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxi{%
Fir'awn said: ye believed in him ere I gave you leave. Verily he is your chief who hath taught you magic, so ye shall surely come to know. Surely I shall cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides and surely I shall crucify you all.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxii{%
They said: no harm! verily unto our Lord we are to return.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxiii{%
Verily we long that our Lord shall forgive us our faults because we have been the first of the believers\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxiv{%
And We revealed unto Musa saying: go by night with My bondmen verily ye shall be pursued.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxv{%
Then Fir'awn sent unto the cities callers:\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxvi{%
Verily these are but a band small.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxvii{%
And verily they have enraged US.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxviii{%
And verily we are host well-provided.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmlxxxix{%
Then We drave them forth from gardens and springs.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxc{%
And treasures and a station noble.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxci{%
Even so. And We caused the Children of Isra'il to inherit them.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcii{%
Then they pursued them at sunrise.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxciii{%
And when the two parties saw each other, the companions of Musa said: verily we are overtaken.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxciv{%
Musa said: by no means; verily with me is my Lord; He shall guide me.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcv{%
Then We revealed unto Musa, saying: smite thou the sea with thy staff. So it became separated, and each part was like unto a cliff mighty.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcvi{%
And We brought near thither the others.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcvii{%
And We delivered Musa and those with him together.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcviii{%
Then We drowned the others.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmcmxcix{%
Verily herein is a sign; but most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmm{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmi{%
And recite unto them the story of Ibrahim.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmii{%
When he said unto his father and his people: what worship ye?\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmiii{%
They said: we worship idols, and we are unto them ever devoted\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmiv{%
He said: hearken they unto you when ye cry?\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmv{%
Or, benefit they you or hurt they you?\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmvi{%
They said: nay; but we found our fathers doing in this wise.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmvii{%
He said: have ye observed that which ye worship\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmviii{%
Ye and your fathers of old?\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmix{%
Verily they are an enemy unto me, save the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmx{%
Who hath created me, and He guideth me.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxi{%
He Who feedeth me and giveth me to drink.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxii{%
And when I sicken, then He healeth me.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxiii{%
And He Who shall cause me to die, and then shall quicken me.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxiv{%
And He Who, long, shall forgive me my faults, on the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxv{%
My Lord! bestow on me wisdom and join me with the righteous.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxvi{%
And appoint for me an honourable mention among the posterity\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxvii{%
And make me one of the inheritors of the Garden of Delight.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxviii{%
And forgive my father; verily he is of the erring.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxix{%
And humiliate me not on the Day whereon people shall be raised.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxx{%
The Day whereon will profit neither substance nor sons.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxi{%
Unless it be he, who shall bring unto Allah a whole heart,\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxii{%
And the Garden shall be brought nigh to the God, fearing.\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxiii{%
And the Fierce Fire shall be made apparent unto the seduced ones.\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxiv{%
And it shall be said unto them where is that which ye were wont to worship?\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxv{%
Beside Allah? Can they succour you or succour themselves?\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxvi{%
Then they shall be hurled therein, they and the seduced ones.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxvii{%
And the hosts of Iblis together.\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxviii{%
And they, While contending therein, shall say:\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxix{%
By Allah, we have indeed been in an error manifest.\qt@no{(97)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxx{%
When we equalled you with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(98)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxi{%
And none led us astray except the Culprits.\qt@no{(99)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxii{%
So none we have as intercessors.\qt@no{(100)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxiii{%
Nor any loving friend.\qt@no{(101)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxiv{%
Were there for us a return, we would be of the believers.\qt@no{(102)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxv{%
Verily herein is a sign, but most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(103)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxvi{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(104)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxvii{%
And Nuh's people belied the sent ones.\qt@no{(105)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxviii{%
When their brother Nuh said Unto them: fear ye not?\qt@no{(106)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxxxix{%
Verily I am unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(107)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxl{%
So fear Allah and obey me.\qt@no{(108)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxli{%
And I ask of you no hire therefor; my hire is but with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(109)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlii{%
So fear Allah and obey me.\qt@no{(110)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxliii{%
They said: shall We believe in thee when the meanest follow thee?\qt@no{(111)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxliv{%
He said: I have no knowledge of that which they have been Working.\qt@no{(112)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlv{%
Their reckoning is upon my Lord, if ye but knew.\qt@no{(113)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlvi{%
And I am not to drive away the believers.\qt@no{(114)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlvii{%
I am naught but a warner manifest.\qt@no{(115)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlviii{%
They said: if thou desistest not, thou shalt surely be of those stoned.\qt@no{(116)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxlix{%
He said: my Lord! verily my people have belied me.\qt@no{(117)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmml{%
So decide Thou between me and them with a decision, and deliver me and those who are with me of the believers.\qt@no{(118)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmli{%
Wherefore We delivered him and those with him in the laden ark.\qt@no{(119)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlii{%
Then We drowned the rest thereafter.\qt@no{(120)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmliii{%
Verily herein is a sign, yet most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(121)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmliv{%
And thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(122)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlv{%
The'Aad belied the sent ones.\qt@no{(123)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlvi{%
When their brother Hud said Unto them: fear ye not?\qt@no{(124)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlvii{%
Verily I am unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(125)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlviii{%
So fear Allah and obey me.\qt@no{(126)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlix{%
And I ask of you no hire therefor: my hire is but with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(127)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlx{%
Build ye on every eminence a landmark in vanity?\qt@no{(128)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxi{%
And take ye for yourselves castles that haply ye may abide.\qt@no{(129)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxii{%
And when ye seize, ye seize like unto tyrants.\qt@no{(130)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxiii{%
So fear Allah, and obey me.\qt@no{(131)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxiv{%
And fear Him Who hath aided you with that which ye know.\qt@no{(132)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxv{%
He hath aided you With Cattle and sons.\qt@no{(133)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxvi{%
And gardens and springs.\qt@no{(134)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxvii{%
Verily I fear for you the torment of a Mighty Day.\qt@no{(135)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxviii{%
They said: it is equal unto us whether thou admonishest or art not of the admonishers.\qt@no{(136)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxix{%
This in but a custom of the ancients.\qt@no{(137)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxx{%
And we are not going to be tormented.\qt@no{(138)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxi{%
And they belied him; so We destroyed them. Verily herein is a sign, yet most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(139)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxii{%
And verily thy Lord? He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(140)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxiii{%
The Thamud belied the sent ones\qt@no{(141)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxiv{%
When their brother Salih said unto them: fear ye not?\qt@no{(142)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxv{%
Verily I am unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(143)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxvi{%
So fear Allah, and obey me.\qt@no{(144)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxvii{%
And I ask of you no hire therefor; MY hire is but with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(145)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxviii{%
Shall ye be left secure in that which is here before us.\qt@no{(146)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxix{%
In gardens and springs.\qt@no{(147)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxx{%
And corn-fields and palm-trees whereof the spathes are fine?\qt@no{(148)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxi{%
And hew ye out houses in the mountains skilfully! g\qt@no{(149)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxii{%
So fear Allah, and obey me.\qt@no{(150)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxiii{%
And obey not the command of the extravagant.\qt@no{(151)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxiv{%
Who work corruption in the land and rectify not.\qt@no{(152)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxv{%
They said: thou art but one of the bewitched;\qt@no{(153)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxvi{%
Thou art but a human being like unto us. So bring thou a sign if thou art of the truth-tellers.\qt@no{(154)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxvii{%
He said: yonder is a she-camel; to her a drink, and to you a drink, each on a day known.\qt@no{(155)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxviii{%
And touch her not with ill, lest there take hold of you the torment of a Mighty Day.\qt@no{(156)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmlxxxix{%
Then they hamstrung her; and then they became regretful.\qt@no{(157)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxc{%
So the torment took hold of them: verily herein is a sign, but most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(158)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxci{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(159)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcii{%
The people of Lut belied the sent ones.\qt@no{(160)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxciii{%
When their brother Lut said unto them: fear ye not?\qt@no{(161)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxciv{%
Verily I am unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(162)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcv{%
So fear Allah, and obey me.\qt@no{(163)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcvi{%
And I ask of you no hire there for; my hire is but with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(164)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcvii{%
Go ye in, of all creatures, unto the males?\qt@no{(165)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcviii{%
And leave ye your spouses your Lord hath created for you? Aye! ye are a people trespassing.\qt@no{(166)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmxcix{%
They said: if thou desistest not, O Lut! thou shalt surely be of those driven forth.\qt@no{(167)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmc{%
He said: verily I am of those who abhor your work.\qt@no{(168)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmci{%
My Lord! deliver me and my household from that which they work.\qt@no{(169)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcii{%
So We delivered him and his household all.\qt@no{(170)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmciii{%
Save an old woman among the lingerers.\qt@no{(171)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmciv{%
Thereafter We annihilated the rest.\qt@no{(172)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcv{%
And We rained on them a rain. So ill was the rain on those warned?\qt@no{(173)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcvi{%
Verily herein is a sign, yet most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(174)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcvii{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(175)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcviii{%
The dwellers of the wood belied the sent ones.\qt@no{(176)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcix{%
What time Shu'aib, said unto them: fear ye not?\qt@no{(177)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcx{%
Verily I am unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(178)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxi{%
So fear Allah, and obey me.\qt@no{(179)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxii{%
And ask of you no hire therefor; and my hire is but with the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(180)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxiii{%
Give full measure, and be not of those who cause others to lose.\qt@no{(181)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxiv{%
And weigh with a balance straight.\qt@no{(182)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxv{%
And defraud not people of their things, and commit not corruption on the earth.\qt@no{(183)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxvi{%
So fear Him Who created you and the former generations.\qt@no{(184)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxvii{%
They said: thou art but of the bewitched;\qt@no{(185)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxviii{%
And thou art but a human being like unto us, and we deem thee to be of the liars.\qt@no{(186)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxix{%
So cause thou a fragment of the heaven to fall upon us, if thou art of the truth-tellers.\qt@no{(187)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxx{%
He. said: My Lord is the Best Knower of that which ye work.\qt@no{(188)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxi{%
Thenn they belied him; wherefore there laid hold of -them the torment of day of shadow. Verily it was the torment of a Mighty Day.\qt@no{(189)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxii{%
Verily herein is a sign; but most of them are not believers.\qt@no{(190)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxiii{%
And verily thy Lord! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(191)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxiv{%
And verily it is a revelation of the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(192)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxv{%
The Trusted spirit hath brought it down.\qt@no{(193)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxvi{%
Upon thy heart, that thou mayest be of the warners,\qt@no{(194)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxvii{%
In plain Arabic speech.\qt@no{(195)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxviii{%
And verily it is in the Scriptures of the ancients.\qt@no{(196)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxix{%
Is it not a sign unto them that the learned among the Children of Isra'il know it?\qt@no{(197)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxx{%
And had We revealed it unto any of the ncn-Arabs,\qt@no{(198)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxi{%
And he had-read it unto them, even then they would not have been believers therein.\qt@no{(199)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxii{%
In this wise have We made way for it into the hearts of the culprits.\qt@no{(200)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxiii{%
They will not believe therein until they behold the torment afflictive.\qt@no{(201)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxiv{%
It shall come unto them on a sudden, and they shall not perceive.\qt@no{(202)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxv{%
Then they will say: are we to be respited?\qt@no{(203)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxvi{%
Seek haste then they with our torment?\qt@no{(204)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxvii{%
Beholdest thou? - if We let them enjoy for years.\qt@no{(205)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxviii{%
And then there cometh unto them that which they had been promised.\qt@no{(206)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxxxix{%
What shall that which they enjoyed avail them?\qt@no{(207)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxl{%
And We destroyed not a city but it had its warners.\qt@no{(208)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxli{%
By way of admonition, and We have never been oppressors.\qt@no{(209)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlii{%
And the satans have not brought it down.\qt@no{(210)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxliii{%
It behoveth them not, nor they can.\qt@no{(211)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxliv{%
Verily far from hearing are they removed.\qt@no{(212)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlv{%
So call not thou unto anot her god along with Allah, lest thou be of the doomed.\qt@no{(213)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlvi{%
And warn thou thy clan, the nearest ones.\qt@no{(214)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlvii{%
And lower thou thy Wlng Unto those who follow thee as believers.\qt@no{(215)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlviii{%
And if they disobey thee, say thou: verily I am quit of that which ye work.\qt@no{(216)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxlix{%
And rely thou upon the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(217)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcl{%
Who seeth thee when thou standest up\qt@no{(218)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcli{%
And thy movements among those who fall prostrate.\qt@no{(219)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclii{%
Verily He! He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(220)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcliii{%
Shall declare unto you upon whom the satans descend!\qt@no{(221)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcliv{%
They descend upon every calumniator, sinner.\qt@no{(222)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclv{%
Who give ear, and most of them are liars.\qt@no{(223)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclvi{%
As for the poets -it is the seduced who follow them.\qt@no{(224)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclvii{%
Observest thou not, that they Wander about every vale.\qt@no{(225)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclviii{%
And that they say that which they do not?\qt@no{(226)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclix{%
Save those who believed and worked righteous works and remembered Allah much, and vindicated themselves after they had been wronged. And anon those who do wrong shall come to know with what a translating they shall be translated.\qt@no{(227)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclx{%
\basmalahen Ta. Sin. These are the verses of the Qur'an and a Book luminous.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxi{%
A guidance and glad tidings unto the believers.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxii{%
Who establish the prayer and give the poor-rate, and of the Hereafter they are convinced.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxiii{%
Verily those who believe not in the Hereafter - fairseeming unto them We have made their works, so that they wander perplexed.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxiv{%
Those are they for whom shall be an evil torment. And in the Hereafter they shall be the greatest losers.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxv{%
And verily thou art receiving the Qur'an) from before the Wise, the Knowing.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxvi{%
Recall what time Musa said unto his household: verily I perceive a fire afar; I shall forthwith bring you tidings thereof, or bring unto you a brand lighted therefrom, haply ye may warm yourselves.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxvii{%
Then when he came unto it, he was cried unto Thus; Blest is whosoever is in the fire and whosoever is around it; and hallowed be Allah, the Lord of the Worlds.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxviii{%
O Musa! verily it is I, Allah, the Mighty the Wise!\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxix{%
And cast thou down thy staff. Then when he saw it wriggling as though it were a serpent, he turned in flight and looked not back. O Musa! fear thou not; verily in My presence the sent ones fear not.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxx{%
Excepting any who may have done wrong and thereafter changeth evil for good then verily I am Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxi{%
And put thy hand into thy bosom, it Shall come forth white, with out hurt: amongst nine signs unto Fir'awn and his people. Verily they have been a people transgressing.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxii{%
Then when Our signs came unto them illuminating, they said: this is a magic manifest.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxiii{%
And they gainsaid them, out of spite and arrogance, although their souls were convinced thereof. So behold! what hath been the end of the corruptors.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxiv{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed unto Daud and Sulaiman a knowledge, and the twain said: praise unto Allah Who hath preferred us above many of His believing bondmen!\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxv{%
And Sulaiman inherited from Daud. And he said: O mankind! verily have been taught the diction of we birds, and we have been vcuchsafed of every thing; and verily this is grace manifest.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxvi{%
And there were gathered unto Sulaiman his hosts of jinns and mankind and birds, and they were set in bands.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxvii{%
Until when they came unto the valley of the ants, an ant said: O ants! enter Your habitations lest Sulaiman and his hosts crush you while they perceive not.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxviii{%
So he smiled, amused at her speech, and said: my Lord! arouse me that I should be thankful for Thy favour wherewith Thou hast favoured me and my parents, and that I should work righteously pleasing Thee, and out of Thy mercy enter me among Thine righteous bondmen.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxix{%
And he sought after the birds and said: what aileth me that I see not the hoopoe; is he among the absentees?\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxx{%
Surely I shall torment him with a severe torment, or I shall slaughter him, unless he bringeth unto me a warranty manifest.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxi{%
Buthe tarried not far, and he said: I have encompassed that which thou hast- not encompassed, and I come unto thee from Saba with a tidings sure.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxii{%
Verily have found a woman ruling over them and she hath been vouchsafed somewhat of everything, and hers is a mighty throne.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxiii{%
I have found her and her people adoring the sun instead of Allah, and the Satan hath made their works fairseeming unto them, and hath barred them from the way, so they are not guided.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxiv{%
So that they adore not Allah who bringeth forth the hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knoweth that which conceal and that which ye make known.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxv{%
Allah! there is no God but he, the Lord of the Magnificent Throne.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxvi{%
Sulaiman said: we shall see now whether thou hast spoken the truth or whether thou art of the liars.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxvii{%
Go thou with this epistle of mine, and cast it down unto them, and turn aside from them, and see how they return.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxviii{%
She said: O chiefs! verily there hath been cast unto me an honourable epistle.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmclxxxix{%
Verily it is from Sulaiman, and verily it is: in the name of Allah, the Compassionate, the Merciful.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxc{%
Saying: exalt not yourselves against me, and come unto me submissive.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxci{%
She said: O chiefs! counsel me in my affair. I am wont not to resolve on any affair until ye are present with me.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcii{%
They said: we are owners of power and owners of great violence, but the command is with thee; see then whatsoever thou shalt command.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxciii{%
She said: verily the kings, when they enter a City, despoil it, and make the most powerful inhabitants thereof the most abased; so will they do.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxciv{%
So verily I am going to send a present unto them, and see with what answer the envoys come back.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcv{%
Then when he came unto Sulaiman, he said: are ye going to add riches to me. Then that which Allah hath vouchsafed unto me is better than that which He hath vouchsafed unto you. Aye! it is ye who exult in your present.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcvi{%
Go back unto them. Then surely we shall come unto them with hosts which they cannot withstand, and we shall drive them forth therefrom abased and they shall be humbled.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcvii{%
He said: O chiefs! which of you will bring unto me her throne, ere they come unto me submitting themselves?\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcviii{%
A giant from the jinns said: I shall bring it unto thee ere thou arisest from thy place; verily I am strong for it and trusty.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcxcix{%
The one who had some knowledge of the Book said: I shall bring it unto thee ere thy eye twinkleth. Then when he saw it placed before him, he said: this is of the grace of my Lord that he may prove me whether I give thanks or am ungrateful. Whosoever giveth thanks he only giveth thanks for his own soul; and whosoever is ungrateful then verily my Lord is Self-sufficient, Munificent.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcc{%
He said: disguise for her her throne, that we may see whether she be guided or be of those who are not guided.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcci{%
Then when she arrived, it was said: is thy throne like unto? She said: it is as though it were it; and we have been vouchsafed the knowledge before this, and we have been Muslims.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccii{%
And that which she was wont to worship instead of Allah hindered her; verily she was of an infidel people.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcciii{%
It was said unto her: enter the palace. Then when she saw it,, he deemed it a pool and bared her shanks. He said: verily it is a palace evenly floored with glass. She said: my Lord! verily I wronged my soul, and now submit myself together with Sulaiman unto Allah, the Lord of the Worlds.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcciv{%
And assuredly We sent unto the Thamud their brother Saleh saying: worship Allah. Then lo! they became two parties contending.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccv{%
He said: O my people! wherefore seek ye to hasten the evil before the good? Wherefore ask ye not forgiveness of Allah, that haply ye may be shewn mercy.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccvi{%
They said: we augur ill of thee and of those who are with thee. He said: your augury is with Allah. Aye! ye are a people being tested.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccvii{%
And there were nine of a group in the City, who spread corruption in the land and rectified not.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccviii{%
They said: swear one to anot her by God that we shall surely fall upon him and his household by night and thereafter we shall surely say unto his heir; We witnessed not the destruction of his household, and verily we are truthtellers.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccix{%
And they plotted a plot, and We plotted a plot, while they perceived it not.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccx{%
So behold thou how was the end of their plotting: verily We annihilated them and their nation all together.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxi{%
So yonder are their houses overturned, for they did wrong. Verily, herein is a sign unto a people who know.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxii{%
And We delivered those who believed and were wont to fear.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxiii{%
And Lut! what time he said unto his people: commit ye indecency while ye see?\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxiv{%
Would ye go in lustfully unto men instead of women? Aye! ye are a people addicted to ignorant ways.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxv{%
Then there was no answer of his people save that they said: drive forth the family of Lut from your City, verily they are a people who would be pure!\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxvi{%
Then We delivered him and his household save his wife: We destined hers to be of the lingerers.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxvii{%
And We rained upon them a rain; ill was the rain upon the warned.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxviii{%
Say thou: All praise unto Allah, and peace upon His bondmen whom He hath Chosen! Is Allah best, or that which they associate?\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxix{%
Is not he best Who hath created the heavens and the earth, and Who sendeth down water for you from the heaven wherewith We cause beauteous orchards to grow up, whereof it was not possible for you to cause the trees to grow up! Is there any god along with Allah! Nay! but they are a people who equalise.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxx{%
Is not he best Who hath made the earth a fixed abode and placed rivers in the midst thereof and placed Firm mountains thereon, and hath set a barrier between the two seas? IS there any god along with Allah? Nay! but most of them know not.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxi{%
Is not he best Who answereth the distressed when he calleth unto Him and removeth the evil, and hath made you the successors in the earth? Is there any god along with Allah? Little ye reflect!\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxii{%
Is not he best Who guideth you in the darknesses of the land and the sea, and Who sendeth the winds as heralds before His mercy Is there any god along with Allah? Exalted be Allah from all that they associate!\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxiii{%
Is not he best Who originateth creation, and shall thereafter restoreth it, and Who provideth for you from the heaven and the earth? IS there any godl along with Allah? Say thou: bring your proof, if ye are truth-tellers.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxiv{%
Say thou: none in the heavens and the earth knoweth the Unseen save Allah; nor can they perceive when they will be raised.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxv{%
Aye! their knowledge attaineth not to the Hereafter, Aye! they are in doubt thereof. Aye! thereunto they are blind.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxvi{%
And those who disbelieve say: when we have become dust, we and our fathers, shall we, for sooth, be brought forth?\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxvii{%
Assuredly we have been promised this aforetime, we and our fathers. Naught is this but fables of the ancients.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxviii{%
Say thou: travel in the land and behold what like hath been the end of the culprits.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxix{%
And grieve thou not over them nor be straitened because of that which they plot.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxx{%
And they say: when will this Promise be fufilled if ye say sooth?\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxi{%
Say thou: belike close behind you may be some of that which ye would hasten on.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxii{%
And verily thine Lord is full of grace for mankind, but most of them give not thanks.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxiii{%
And verily thine Lord knoweth whatsoever their breasts conceal and whatsoever they make known.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxiv{%
And naught there is hidden in the heaven or the earth but it is in a Manifest Book.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxv{%
Verily this Qur'an recounteth with truth unto the Children of Isra'il much of that wherein they differ.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxvi{%
And verily it is a guidance and a mercy unto the believers.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxvii{%
And verily thine Lord shall decide between them with His judgment, and He is the Mighty, the Knowing.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxviii{%
Wherefore put thy trust in Allah; verily thou art on manifest truth.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxxxix{%
Verily thou canst not make the dead hear, nor canst thou make the deaf hear the call when they flee turning their backs.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxl{%
Nor canst thou lead the blind out of their error. Thou canst make none hear save these who believe in Our signs and who have submitted themselves.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxli{%
And when the word shall come to be fulfilled concerning them, We shall bring forth a beast of the earth speaking unto them, that the people have not of Our signs been convinced.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlii{%
And remind them of the Day whereon We shall Rather from every community a troop of those who belied Our signs, and they shall be held in order.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxliii{%
Until when they shall have come, He Shall say: belied ye My signs when ye encompassed them not in Your knowledge; nay, what else was it that ye have been working?\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxliv{%
And the Word shall be fulfilled concerning them, because they did wrong, and they shall not be able to speak.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlv{%
Observe they not that We have appointed the night that they may repose therein, and the day sight-giving? Verily herein are signs unto a people who believe.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlvi{%
And remind them of the Day whereon the trumpet shall be blown, and affrighted will be those who are in the heavens and the earth, save him whom Allah willeth. And all shall come unto Him, lowly.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlvii{%
And thou shalt see the mountains thou deemest solid passing away as the passing away of the clouds: the handiwork of Allah Who hath perfected everything. Verily He is Aware of all that ye do.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlviii{%
Whosoever will bring good shall have better than the worth thereof; and they from the terror of that Day will be secure.\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxlix{%
And whosoever will bring evil --their faces shall be cast down into the Fire. Are ye being requited aught save that which ye have been working?\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccl{%
I am commanded only to worship the Lord of this city which He hath sanctified, -and His is every thing - and I am commanded to be of the Muslims;\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccli{%
And that I should recite the Qur'an. And whosoever receiveth guidance, receiveth guidance for his own soul, and as for him who strayeth say thou: I am only of the warners.\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclii{%
And say thou: All praise unto Allah! Anon He shall shew you His signs, so that ye will recognize them. And thy Lord is not negligent of that which ye Work.\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccliii{%
\basmalahen Ta. Sin. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccliv{%
These are verses of the Manifest Book.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclv{%
WE recite unto thee of the story of Musa and Fir'awn with truth fora people who believe.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclvi{%
Verily Fir'awn exalted himself in the earth and made the people thereof into sects, weakening a party among them, slaying their sons and letting their women live. Verify he was of the corrupters.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclvii{%
And We desired that We should be gracious unto those who were weakened in the land, and We should make them leaders and We should make them the inheritors.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclviii{%
And We should establish them in the earth, and We should let Fir'awn and Haman and their hostee from them that which they dreaded.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclix{%
And We inspired the mother of Musa, saying: suckle him, then when thou fearest for him, cast him into the river and fear not, nor grieve. Verily We are going to restore him unto thee, and shall make him one of the sent ones.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclx{%
And the household of Fir'awn took him Up, that he should become unto them an enemy and a grief. Verily Fir'awn and Haman and their hosts were sinners.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxi{%
And the wife of Fir'awn said: a comfort unto me and thee slay him not; belike he shall be of benefit to us or we might like him for a son; and they perceived not.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxii{%
And the heart of the mother of Musa became void, and she had wellnigh disclosed him, had We not fortified her heart, that she might remain one of the believers.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxiii{%
And she said unto his sister: follow him. So she watched him from afar; and they perceived not.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxiv{%
And We had aforetime forbidden foster-mothers for him; so she said: shall direct you unto a household who will rear him for you and who will be unto him good counsellors.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxv{%
So We restored him unto his mother that she might be comforted and not grieve, and that she might know that the promise of Allah is true. Yet most of them know not.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxvi{%
And when he attained his full strength and became firm, We vouchsafed unto him wisdom and knowledge; and Thus We reward the well- doers.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxvii{%
And he entered the City at a time of unawareness of the inhabitants thereof, and he found therein two men fighting, one being of his own party, and the other of his enemies. And he who was of his party, called him for help against him who was of his enemies. So Musa truck him with his fist, and put an end of him. He said: this is of the work of the satan, verily he is an enemy, a misleader manifest.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxviii{%
He said: my Lord! verily I have wronged my soul, so wherefore forgive me. So He forgave him. Verily He! He is the Forgiving, the Owner of Mercy.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxix{%
He said: my Lord! whereas Thou hast favoured me, I shall nevermore be a supporter of the culprits.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxx{%
And in the morning he was in the city fearing and looking about, when lo! he who had asked his succour yesterday was crying out unto him. Musa said: verily thou art a seducer manifest.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxi{%
And when he sought to seize him who was an enemy unto them both, he said: O Musa wouldst thou slay me as thou didst slay a person yesterday? Thou seekest only to be a tyrant in the land, and thou seekest not to be of the reconcilers.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxii{%
And there came a man from the farthest part of the city, running; he said: O Musa! the chiefs are taking counsel together concerning thee, that they might slay thee; wherefore go forth thou, verily I am unto thee of the admonishers.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxiii{%
So he went forth from thence fearing, looking abcut. He said: my Lord! deliver me from the wrong-doing people.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxiv{%
And when he betook himself toward Madyan, he said: belike my Lord will guide me even way.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxv{%
And when he arrived at the water of Madyan, he found there a community of the people watering. And he found, apart from them, two women keeping back their flocks. He said: what aileth you twain! The twain said: we water not until the shepherds have driven away their flocks; and our father is a very old man.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxvi{%
Then he watered their flocks for the twain. Then he turned aside into the shade, and said: my Lord! I verily of the good which Thou mayest send down for me I am needy.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxvii{%
Then there came unto him one of the twain walking bashfully, and said: verily my father calleth for thee, that he may recompense thee with a hire for that thou didst water the flock for us. Then, when he was come unto him and had recounted unto him the whole story, he said: fear not; thou hast escaped from the wrong-doing people.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxviii{%
And said one of the twain: O my father! hire him, for the best that thou canst hire is the strong and trustworthy one.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxix{%
He said: verily I wish I would marry thee to one of these two daughters of mine provided that thou hirest thyself to me for eight years. then if thou completest ten it will de of thine own accord, and I would not make it hard for thee; thou Shalt find me, Allah willing, of the righteous.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxx{%
Musa said: be that between me and thee: whichsoever of the two terms I shall fulfil, it shall be no harshness to me; and of that which we say Allah is Trustee.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxi{%
Then when Musa had fulfilled the term, and was journeying with his household, he saw a fire on the side of Tur, and said unto his household: bide ye; verily I see a fire afar, haply I may bring unto you tidings thereon, or a brand out: of the fire, haply ye may warm yourselves.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxii{%
Then when he was come thereto, he was called from the right side of the valley in the ground blest from the tree: Musa! verily I! I am Allah, the Lord of the worlds;\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxiii{%
And cast thou down thy staff. And when he saw it stirring, as though it were a serpent, he turned in flight and looked not back. O Musa! draw nigh, and fear not; thou art of the secure ones.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxiv{%
Slip thy hand in thy bosom, it shall come forth white without hurt; and draw back thy arm unto thee for fear. These shall be two proofs from thy Lord unto Fir'awn and his chiefs; verily they have been a people given to transgression.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxv{%
He said: My Lord! verily I have slain a man among them and I fear they shall slay me.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxvi{%
And My brother Harun! He is more eloquent than I in speech; wherefore send him with me as a support, to corroborate me; verily I fear that they shall belie me.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxvii{%
He said: We shall indeed strengthen thine arm with thy brother, and We shall vouchsafe unto you authority, so that they shall not be able to come up to you. Go forth with Our signs! Ye twain and those who follow you, shall be the victors.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxviii{%
Then when Musa came unto them with Our manifest signs, they said: this is naught but magic fabricated; and we heard not of this among our fathers of old.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcclxxxix{%
And Musa said: My Lord best knoweth him who bringeth guidance from before Him and him whose will be the happy end of the Abode. Verily the wrong-doers shall not thrive.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxc{%
And Fir'awn said: O chiefs! know not of a god for you except me. Wherefore light thou for me, O Haman! clay, and make me a lofty tower that I may ascend unto the God of Musa; and verily I imagine him to be of the liars.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxci{%
And he and his hosts were stiff-necked in the land without right, and imagined that before Us they would not be brought back.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcii{%
Wherefore We laid hold of him and his hosts and cast them into the sea. So behold thou what like hath been the end of the wrong- doers!\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxciii{%
And We made them leaders calling to the Fire, and on the Day of Resurrection they shall not be succoured.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxciv{%
And We caused a curse to follow them in this world, and on the Day of Resurrection they shall be of the castaway.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcv{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed the the Scripture unto Musa after We had destroyed the generations of old: enlightenment unto mankind and a guidance and a mercy, that haply they might be admonished.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcvi{%
And thou wast not on the western side when We decreed the affair unto Musa, and thou wast not of the witnesses.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcvii{%
But We brought forth generations, and prolonged unto them was life; nor wast thou a dweller among the people of Madyan, reciting unto them Our revelations; but it is We who were to send.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcviii{%
Nor wast thou beside the Tur when We called; but thou art sent as a mercy from thy Lord, that thou mayest warn a people unto whom no warner came before thee, that haply they might be admonished.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccxcix{%
And lest, if an affliction had afflicted them for that which their hands had sent before, they should have said: our Lord! wherefore sent not Thou an apostle unto us that we might have followed Thy revelations and been of the believers!\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccc{%
Yet when the truth is come unto them from before Us, they say: wherefore hast he not been vouchsafed the like of that which was given unto Musa? Disbelieved they not in that which was given unto Musa aforetime? They say; two magics supporting each other. And they say: verily in all such things we are disbelievers.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccci{%
Say thou: then bring a Book from before Allah, that is better in guidance than these two shall follow it--if ye are truth- tellers.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccii{%
Then if they answer thee not, know thou that they only follow their own desires; and who is farther astray than he who followeth his desire without guidance from Allah? Verily Allah guideth not a wrong- doing people.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccciii{%
And assuredly We have caused the Word to reach them in succession, that haply they may be admonished.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccciv{%
Those unto whom We vouchsafed the Book before it, --they believe therein.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccv{%
And when it is rehearsed unto them they say: we believe therein: verily it is truth from our Lord: verily we have been even before it of those who submit themselves.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccvi{%
These shall be vouchsafed their hire twice over, because they have persevered, and they repel evil with good, and expend of that wherewith We have provided them.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccvii{%
And when they hear vain discourse they withdraw therefrom and say: unto US our works, and unto you your works; peace be unto you; we seek not the ignorant.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccviii{%
Verily thou shalt not guide whomsoever thou lovest, but Allah shall guide whomsoever He will. And He knoweth best who are the guided.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccix{%
And they say: were we to follow the guidance with thee, We Shall be snatched away from our land. Have We not established for them an inviolable sanctuary whereunto fruits of every sort are brought: a provision from Our presence? But most of them know not.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccx{%
And how many a city have We destroyed that exulted in their living! And yonder are their dwellings which have not been inhabited after them unless for a little while; and verily We! We have been the inheritors.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxi{%
Nor was thy Lord to destroy the Cities, until He had raised up in their mother-city an apostle reciting unto them our revealations. Nor were We to destroy the cities unless the inhabitants thereof were wrong-doers.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxii{%
And whatsoever ye are vouchsafed is an enjoyment of the life of the world and an adornment thereof; and that which is with Allah is better and more lasting. Will ye not therefore reflect?\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxiii{%
Is he, then, whom We have promised an excellent promise which he is going to meet, like unto him whom We have suffered to enjoy awhile the enjoyment of the life of the world, then on the Day of Resurrection he shall be of those brought up!\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxiv{%
And on the Day whereon He shall call unto them and say: where are My associates whom ye were wont to assert?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxv{%
Those upon whom the sentence will be pronounced will say: our Lord these are they whom we seduced, we seduced them even as we our selves were seduced. We declare ourselves quit of them before Thee; not our selves they were wont to worship.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxvi{%
And it shall be said: Call upon your associate-gods. And they shall call upon them, and they shall not answer them, and they shall behold the torment. Would that they had received the guidance!\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxvii{%
And on the Day whereon He shall call unto them and say: what answer gave ye to the sent ones?\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxviii{%
Bedimmed unto them shall be all excuses on that Day, wherefore they shall not be able to ask one of another.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxix{%
Howbeit, whosoever shall repent and believe, and work righteous works - belike he shall be of the thrivers.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxx{%
And thy lord createth whatsoever He listeth and chooseth; no Choice is to be far them. Hallowed be Allah and exalted above that which they associate!\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxi{%
And thy Lord knoweth that which their breasts conceal and that which they make known.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxii{%
And He is Allah there is no god but he! His is all praise in the first and in the last, and His is the command, and unto Him ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxiii{%
Say thou: bethink ye, if Allah made night continuous for you till the Day of Resurrection, what god is there beside Allah, who would bring you light? Hearken ye not?\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxiv{%
Say thou: bethink ye, if Allah made day continuous for you till the Day of Resurrection, what god is there beside Allah, who would bring you night wherein ye have repose? Behold ye not?\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxv{%
It is of His mercy He hath appointed for you night and day, that therein ye may have repose, and that ye may seek of His grace, and that haply ye may give thanks.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxvi{%
And on the Day whereon He shall call unto them and say: where are My associates whom ye were wont to assert?\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxvii{%
We shall take out from every community a witness and We shall say: come forth with your proof; then they shall know that the truth was Allah's, and astray will go from them that which they were wont to fabricate.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxviii{%
Verily Qarun was of the people of Musa; then he behaved arrogantly toward them. And We had vouchsafed him of the treasures whereof the keys would have weighed down a band of strong men. Recall what time his people said unto him: exult not; verily God loveth not the exultant.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxix{%
And seek the abode of the Hereafter with that which God hath vouchsafed thee, and forget not thy portion in the World, and be thou bounteous even as God hath been bounteous unto thee, and seek not corruption in the earth; verily Allah loveth not corrupters.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxx{%
He said: I have been vouchsafed this only because of the knowledge that is with me. Knew he not that Allah had destroyed before him, of the generations, those who were stronger than he in might and larger in respect of following? And the culprits shall not be questioned of their sins.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxi{%
Then he went forth unto his people in his pomp. Those who sought the life of the world said: would that we had the like of that which hath been vouchsafed unto Qarun! Verily he is the owner of a very great fortune.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxii{%
And those who had been vouchsafed the knowledge said: woe unto you! the reward of Allah is best for him who believeth and worketh righteously and none shall attain it except the patient.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxiii{%
Then We sank the earth with him and his dwelling-place. And he had no host to defend him against Allah, nor was he of those who could defend themselves.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxiv{%
And those who had wished for his place but yesterday began to say: Ah! Allah expandeth the provision for whomsoever He will of His bondmen and stinteth, had not Allah been gracious unto us, He would have sunk the earth with us also. Ah! the infidels thrive not.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxv{%
This is the abode of the Hereafter! We appoint it unto those who Seek not exaltation in the earth nor corruption; and the happy end is for the God-fearing.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxvi{%
Whosoever bringeth good shall have better than it, and whosoever bringeth evil, then those who do ill works shall be rewarded only for that which they have been working.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxvii{%
Verily He who hath imposed the Qur'an on thee Is surely about to bring thee back home. Say thou: my Lord knoweth best who bringeth guidance and who is in an error manifest.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxviii{%
And thou wast not hoping that the Book would be Inspired in thee; but it is a mercy from thy Lord, so be thou not a supporter of the infidels.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxxxix{%
And let them not turn thee aside from the signs of Allah after they have been sent down unto thee. And call thou men unto thy Lord, and be thou not of the associaters.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxl{%
And invoke thou not any other god along with Allah. There is no god but he. Everything is perishable save His countenance His is the judgment, and unto Him ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxli{%
\basmalahen Alif. Lam. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlii{%
Bethink men that they shall be left alone because they say: we believe; and that they shall not be tempted?\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxliii{%
And assuredly We have tempted those who were before them. So Allah will surely know those who are true and He will surely know the liars.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxliv{%
Or bethink those who work ill deeds that they shall outstrip Us? lll do they judge!\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlv{%
Whosoever hopeth for the meeting with Allah, then Allah's term is surely coming, and He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlvi{%
And whosoever strive, striveth only for himself: verily Allah is Independent of the worlds.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlvii{%
And whosoever believe and work righteous works, We shall purge away from them their ill-deeds and shall recompense them the best of that which they have been working.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlviii{%
And We have enjoined on man kindness unto parents. But if the twain strive to make thee associate with Me that of which thou hast no knowledge, obey them not. Unto Me is your return, and I shall declare unto you that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxlix{%
And those who believe and work righteous works--We shall surely cause them enter among the righteous.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccl{%
Of mankind are some who say: we believe in Allah; then if they are afflicted in the way of Allah, they take the persecution of men even as the torment of Allah; and then, if succour cometh from thy Lord they say: verily we have been with you. Is not Allah the Best Knower of that which is in the breasts of the creatures?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccli{%
And surely Allah shall come to know those who believe, and surely He shall come to know the hypocrites.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclii{%
And those who disbelieve say unto those who believe: follow our way, and we shall surely bear your sins; whereas they shall not bear aught of their sins; verily they are the liars.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccliii{%
And surely they shall bear their loads and other loads beside their own loads, and surely they shall be questioned on the Day of Resurrection concerning that which they were wont to fabricate.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccliv{%
And assuredly We sent Nuh unto his people. Then he tarried among them for a thousand years, save tifty years; and then deluge overtook them, while they were wrong-doers.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclv{%
Then We delivered him and those in the ark, and made it a sign unto the worlds.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclvi{%
And We sent Ibrahim. Recall what time he said unto his people: worship Allah, and fear Him; that is best for you if ye but knew.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclvii{%
Ye only worship images instead of Allah, and ye create a falsehood. Verily those whom ye worship instead of Allah own no provision for you. Wherefore seek with Allah provision, and worship Him, and give thanks unto Him: unto Him ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclviii{%
And if ye belie me, then communities before you have belied: and upon the apostle is naught but a preaching manifest.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclix{%
Observe they not what wise Allah originateth creation? And then He shall restore it. Verily for Allah that is easy.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclx{%
Say thou: go about in the land and behold what wise He hath originated creation; and then Allah shall produce another production; verily Allah is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxi{%
He shall torment whomsoever He Will, and shall show mercy unto whomsoever He Will, and unto Him ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxii{%
And ye cannot escape in the earth nor in the heaven, and beside Allah there is for you no friend nor helper.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxiii{%
Those who disbelieve in the signs of Allah and in their meeting with Him, they shall despair of My mercy, and they! theirs shall be a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxiv{%
Then the answer of his people was naught but that they said: slay him, or burn him. Then Allah delivered him from the fire; verily herein are signs for a people who believe.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxv{%
And he said: ye have taken images instead of Allah out of affection between you in the life of the world; but on the Day of Resurrection ye shall deny each other and ye shall curse each other, and your resort shall be the Fire, and ye shall have no helpers.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxvi{%
And Lut believed in him. And he said: verily I am going to migrate to my Lord; verily He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxvii{%
And We bestowed on him Is-haq and Y'aqub, and We placed among his posterity prophethood and the Book, and We vouchsafed unto him his hire in the World, and verily in the Hereafter he shall be of the righteous.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxviii{%
And Lut: Recall what time he said unto his people: verily ye commit an indecency wherein none hath preceded you in the Worlds.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxix{%
Ye go in indeed unto males, and ye rob on the highway, and ye commit that which is disreputable in your assembly? Then the answer of his people was naught but that they said: bring thou God's torment on us if thou art of the truth-tellers.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxx{%
He said: my Lord! give me victory over the corrupt people.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxi{%
And when Our messengers came unto Ibrahim with the glad tidings, they said: verily we are about to destroy the inhabitants of that city: verily the inhabitants thereof have been wrong-doers.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxii{%
He said: verily Lut is therein. They said: we know better who is therein: we are to deliver him and his household, save his wife; she is to be of the lingerers.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxiii{%
And when Our messengers came unto Lut, he was distressed on their account and felt straitened on their account. And they said: fear not, nor grieve: verily we are to deliver thee and thy household, save thy wife: she is to be of the lingerers.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxiv{%
Verily we are about to bring down upon the inhabitants of this city a scourge from the heaven, for they have been transgressing.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxv{%
And assuredly We have left thereof manifest sign for a people who reflect.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxvi{%
And unto Madyan We sent their brother, Shu'aib. He said: my people! worship Allah, and fear the Last Day, and commit not evil on the earth as corrupters.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxvii{%
Then they belied him; wherefore an earthquake laid hold of them, and they lay in their dwellings, crouching.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxviii{%
And the 'Aad and Thamud and of a surety their destruction is apparent unto you from their dwellings. The Satan made fairseeming their works unto them, and so kept them off from the path, while they were endued with sight.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxix{%
And Qarun and Fir'awn and Haman! And assuredly Musa came unto them with the evidences, yet they were stiff-necked in the land. And they could not outstrip Us.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxx{%
Wherefore each We laid hold of for his sin. Of them were some on whom We sent a violent wind; and of them were some - who were overtaken by a shout; and of them were some - with whom We sank the earth; and of them were some - whom We drowned. Allah was not such as to wrong them, but themselves they were wont to wrong.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxi{%
The likeness of those who take other patrons than Allah is as the likeness of the spider who taketh unto herself a house. And verily the frailest of all houses is the spider's house - if they but knew!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxii{%
Verily Allah knoweth whatsoever thing they invoke beside Him. And He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxiii{%
And these similtudes! We propound them for mankind; and none understand them save men of knowledge.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxiv{%
Allah hath created the heavens and the earth in truth; verily there in is a sign for the believers.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxv{%
Recite thou that which hath been revealed unto thee of the Book and establish thou the prayer; verily prayer preventeth man from indecency and that which is disreputable: and surely the remembrance of Allah is the greatest. And Allah knoweth that which ye perform.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxvi{%
And dispute not with the people of the Book unless in the best manner, save with those of them who do wrong; and say: we believe in that which hath been sent down unto us and that which hath been sent down unto you: our God and your God is One; and unto Him we are submissive.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxvii{%
And likewise have We sent down unto thee the Book; so those to whom We have vouchsafed the Book believe therein, and of those also some believe therein. And none gainsay Our signs save the infidels.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxviii{%
And thou hast not been reciting any book before it, nor hast thou been writing it With thine right hand, for then might the followers of falsehood have doubted.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmccclxxxix{%
Aye! it in itself manifest signs in the breasts of those who have been vouchsafed knowledge, and none gainsay Our signs save the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxc{%
And they say: wherefore are not signs sent down upon him from his Lord! Say thou: signs are with Allah only, and I am but a manifest warner.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxci{%
Sufficeth it not for them that We have sent down unto thee the Book to be recited unto them? Verily herein is a mercy and an admonition for a people who believe.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcii{%
Say thou: Allah sufficeth for witness between me and you: He knoweth whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth. And they who believe in falsehood and disbelieve in Allah, those: they shall be the losers.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxciii{%
And they ask thee to hasten on the torment. And had not there been a term appointed, the torment would surely have come unto them. And surely it shall come upon them of a sudden while they perceive not.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxciv{%
They ask thee to hasten on the torment; and verily the Hell is about to encompass the infidels.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcv{%
On the Day whereon the torment shall cover them from above them and from underneath their feet, and He shall say: taste that which ye have been working!\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcvi{%
My bondmen, who believe! verily My earth is wide, so Me alone worship.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcvii{%
Every soul shall taste of death; then unto Us ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcviii{%
And those who believe and work righteous works--them We shall surely settle in lofty dwellins of the; they shall be of the Garden whereunder the rivers flow; they shall be abiders therein. Excellent is the hire of the Workers.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcccxcix{%
Who persevere and in their Lord trust!\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcd{%
And how many a moving creature there is that beareth not its provision! Allah provideth for it and for you. And He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdi{%
And wert thou to ask them.: who hath created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon they would surely say: Allah. How then are they deviating?\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdii{%
Allah expandeth provision for whomsoever He Will of His bondmen and stinteth it for him. Verily Allah is of everything the Knower.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdiii{%
And wert thou to ask them: who sendeth down water from the heaven, and therewith quickeneth the earth after the death thereof? they would surely say: Allah. Say thou: all praise unto Allah! Aye! most of them reflect not.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdiv{%
And this life of the world is but: sport and play. Verily the home of the Hereafter--that is life indeed, if they but knew!\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdv{%
So When they mount upon the ships they call on Allah making pure for Him the religion, then when He delivereth them safely on the land, lo! they associate\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdvi{%
So that they become ingrate for that which We have vouchsafed unto them, and that they enjoy themselves; but presently they shall know.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdvii{%
Behold they not that We have appointed an inviolable sanctuary, while men are being snatched away round about them? in falsehood then believe they, and unto the favour of Allah will they be ingrate?\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdviii{%
And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who fabricateth a lie against Allah or belieth the truth when it cometh unto him Will there not be in the Hell an abiding-place for the infidels?\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdix{%
And those who strive hard in us, We shall surely guide them in Our paths; verily Allah is with the welldoers.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdx{%
\basmalahen Alif. Lam Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxi{%
The Byzantians have been overcome.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxii{%
In a nearer land; and they, after the overcoming of them, shall soon overcome.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxiii{%
In some few years. Allah's is the command, before and after. And on that day the believers wiil rejoice.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxiv{%
In Allah succour. He succoureth whomsoever He will, and He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxv{%
This is Allah's promise; and Allah faileth not His promise. Yet most men know not.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxvi{%
They know only the outward appearance of the life of the world, and they! of the Hereafter, they are neglecetful.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxvii{%
Ponder they not in their minds: Allah hath not created the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in-between the twain save with a purpose and for a term appointed? And verily many men in the meecing of their Lord are unbelievers.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxviii{%
Have they not journeyed in the land and observed what wise hath been the end of those before them? They were stronger than they in power and they brake up the earth and they inhabited it with greater affluence than these have inhabited it, and their apostles came unto them with evidences. And Allah was not one to wrong them, but themselves they were wont to wrong.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxix{%
Then the end of those who committed evil was evil, for they belied the signs of Allah and they were wont to mock at them.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxx{%
Allah originateth the creation, then He shall restore it, then unto Him ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxi{%
And on the day whereon the Hour arriveth, dumb-struck will be the culprits.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxii{%
And not from their associate-gods, there will be intercessors for them, and unto their associate-gods they will be unbelievers.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxiii{%
On the Day whereon the Hour arriveth, that Day they shall be separated.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxiv{%
Then as for those who believed and worked righteous works, they shall be in a meadow made happy.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxv{%
And as for those who disbelieved and belied Our signs and the meeting of the Hereafter--these to the torment shall be brought.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxvi{%
So hallow Allah when ye enter the night and when ye enter the morning, --\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxvii{%
And His is all praise in the heavens and the earth! --and at the sun's decline and when ye enter the noon.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxviii{%
He bringeth forth the living from the lifeless, and He bringeth forth the lifeless from the living, and He quickeneth the earth after the death thereof; and even so shall ye be brought forth.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxix{%
And of His signs is, that he created you of dust, then lo! ye are humankind spreading yourselves.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxx{%
And of His signs is, thathe created for you from yourselves pouses that ye may find repose in them, and He set between you affection and mercy. verily herein are signs for a people who ponder.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxi{%
And of His signs are the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the variation of your languages and complexions; verily herein are signs for men of knowledge.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxii{%
And of His signs are your sleeping by night and by day, and your seeking of His grace verily herein are signs for a people who hearken.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxiii{%
And of His signs is that he sheweth you the lightning for a fear's and for a hope, and sendeth down from the heaven water, and therewith quickeneth the earth after the death thereof; verily herein are signs for a people who reflect.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxiv{%
And of His signs is that the heaven and the earth stand fast by His command, and thereafter, when He calleth you, a call from the earth, lo! ye shall come forth.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxv{%
His is whosoever is in the heavens and the earth; all are unto Him obedient.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxvi{%
And He it is who originateth the creation, then shall restore it, and it is easier for Him. His is the most exalted similitude in the heavens and in the earth; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxvii{%
He propoundeth unto you a similitude taken from yourselves. Have you, from among those whom your right hands own, partners in that wherewith We have provided you, so that ye are equal in respect thereof, and ye fear them as ye fear each other? In this wise We detail the signs for a people who reflect.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxviii{%
Aye! those who do wrong follow their own lusts without knowledge. Who, then, will guide him whom Allah hath sent astray? And for them there will be no helpers.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxxxix{%
Wherefore set thou thy face towards the true religion uprightly. And follow thou the constitution of Allah according to which He hath constituted mankind. No altering let there be in Allah's creation. That is the right religion, but most men know not.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxl{%
And remain turning penitently unto Him, and fear Him, and establish prayer, and be not of the associaters:\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxli{%
Of those who split up their religion and became sects, each band in that which is with them exulting.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlii{%
And when hurt toucheth mankind they cry unto their Lord, turning penitently unto Him; then when He causeth them to taste of His mercy, lo! a part of them with their Lord associate others.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxliii{%
So that they may be ungrateful for that which We have vouchsafed to them. So enjoy awhile; presently ye shall come to know.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxliv{%
Or have We sent unto them any authority, so that it speaketh of that which they have been with Him associating?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlv{%
And when We cause mankind to taste of mercy they exult thereat; then if an evil befalleth them because of that which their hands have sent forth, lo! they despair.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlvi{%
Behold they not that expandeth the provision for whomsoever He and stinteth? Verily herein are signs for a people who believe.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlvii{%
So give thou unto the kinsman his due and unto the needy and unto the wayfarer. That is best for those who seek Allah's countenance; and those: they are the blissful ones.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlviii{%
And whatsoever ye give in gift in order that it may increase among the substance of men increaseth not with Allah; and whatsoever ye give in poor-rate seeking the countenance of Allah-then those: they shall, have increase manifold.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxlix{%
Allah is He Who created you and provided food for you, then He causeth you to die, and then He shall quicken you. Is there any of your associate-gods that doth aught of that? Hallowed and exalted be He above that which they associate!\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdl{%
Corruptness hath appeared on land and sea because of that which men's hands have earned, so that he may make them taste a part of that which they have worked, in order that haply they may turn.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdli{%
Say thou: go forth in the land and behold what wise hath been the end of those of aforetime? And most of them were associaters.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlii{%
So set thy face toward the right religion before the Day cometh from which there is no averting, from Allah, on that Day they shall be sundered.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdliii{%
Whosoever disbelieveth, on him is his infidelity, and those who work righteously are preparing for themselves.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdliv{%
So that he shall recompense those who believe and work righteous works out of His grace; verily He loveth not the infidels.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlv{%
And of His signs is that he sendeth winds heralding rain and that he may make you taste of His mercy, and that the ships may sail at His command and that ye may seek His grace, and that haply ye may return thanks.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlvi{%
And assuredly We sent apostles before thee unto their people. They brought them manifest signs. Then We took vengeance upon those who transgressed. And incumbent upon us was avengement of the believers.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlvii{%
Allah is He Who sendeth the winds so that they raise a cloud and then spreadeth it along the heaven as He will and breaketh it into fragments, and thou beholdest the rain come forth from the intestines thereof. Then when He maketh it fall upon such of His bondmen as He will, lo! they rejoice.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlviii{%
Even though before it was sent down upon them, before that, they were surely despairing.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlix{%
Look then at the effects of Allah's mercy: what wise He quickeneth the earth after the death thereof. Verily. He is the Quickener of the dead, and He is over every-thing potent.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlx{%
And if We send a wind, and they should see their tilth yellow, then they would thereafter remain disbelieving.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxi{%
So verily thou canst not make the dead hear, nor canst thou make the deaf hear the call when they turn away in flight.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxii{%
Nor canst thou be a guide to the blind out of their error; thou canst make none to hear save those who believe in Our signs, and who have surrendered themselves.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxiii{%
Allah it is Who created you in weakness, then He appointed strength after weakness, then after strength appointed weakness and grey hair. He createth whatsoever He listeth: and He is Knower, the Potent.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxiv{%
And on the Day whereon the Hour arriveth, the Culprits Will swear that they tarried not but an hour: Thus Were they ever deluded.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxv{%
And those who have been vouchsafed knowledge and belief will say: assuredly ye have tarried according to the decree of Allah until the Day of Upraising; so this is the Day of Upraising, but ye were wont not to know.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxvi{%
On that Day the excusing of themselves will not profit those who did wrong, nor shall they be suffered to please Allah.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxvii{%
And assuredly We have propounded for mankind, in this Qur'an, every kind of similitude; and if thou bringest unto them a sign, those who disbelieve are sure to say: ye are but followers of falsehood.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxviii{%
In this wise Allah sealeth the hearts of those who believe not.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxix{%
So have thou patience; verily the promise of Allah is true. And let not make thee impatient those who have no conviction.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxx{%
\basmalahen Alif; Lam. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxi{%
These are verses of the Wise Book.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxii{%
A guidance and a mercy for the well-doers:\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxiii{%
Those who establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and of the Hereafter are convinced.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxiv{%
These are on guidance from their Lord, and these! they are the blissful ones.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxv{%
And of mankind is one who purchaseth an idle discourse, that he may mislead from Allah's way without knowledge, and taketh it by way of mockery. These! for them shall be a torment ignominious.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxvi{%
And when Our revelations are recited unto him he turneth away in his stiff-neckedness as though he heard them not: as though there was a deafness in his ears. So announce thou unto him a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxvii{%
Verily those who believe and work righteous works, theirs shall be Gardens of Delight.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxviii{%
Therein they will be abiders: a true promise of Allah. And He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxix{%
He hath created the heavens that ye behold without pillars and hath cast Into the earth firm mountains lest it move away with you; and He hath scattered thereon every kind of animal. And We send down water from the heaven and We make grow every kind of goodly growth therein.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxx{%
This is the creation of Allah; shew that which those beside Him me have created. Aye! the wrong-doers are in error manifest.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxi{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed unto Luqman Wisdom, saying: give thanks unto Allah; and whosoever giveth thanks giveth thanks for his soul; and whosoever is unthankful--then verily Allah is self-sufficient, praiseworthy\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxii{%
And recall what time Luqman said unto his son, while he was exhorting him: O my son! associate not aught with Allah; verily this associating is surely a tremendous wrong.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxiii{%
And We have enjoined upon man concerning his parents--his mother beareth him in hardship upon hardship and his weaning is in two years: give thanks unto Me and unto thy parents; Unto Me is the goal.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxiv{%
And if the twain strive with thee to make thee associate with Me that for which thou hast no knowledge, then obey them not. And bear them thou company in the world reputably, and follow thou the path of him who turneth penitently unto Me. Then unto Me is your return, and I shall declare unto you that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxv{%
O my son! though it be but the weight of a grain of mustard-seed, and though it be in a rock or in the heavens, or in the earth, Allah shall bring it forth. Verily Allah is subtile, Aware.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxvi{%
O My son! establish prayer and command that which is reputable and forbid iniquity, and bear patiently whatsoever may befall thee; verily that is of the firmness of affairs.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxvii{%
And turn not away thy cheek from men nor walk on the earth stultingly, verily Allah loveth not any vainglorious boaster.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxviii{%
And be modest in thy gait and lower thy voice; verily the most abominable of voices is the voice of the ass.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdlxxxix{%
Observe ye not that Allah hath subjected for you whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, and hath completed His favours on you outwardly and inwardly? And yet of mankind is one who disputeth concerning Allah without knowledge and with neither guidance nor a Book luminous.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxc{%
And when it is said unto them: follow that which Allah hath sent down, they say: nay! we shall follow that which we found our fathers upon. What! even though the Satan had been calling on them unto the torment of the Blaze.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxci{%
And whosoever submitteth his countenance unto Allah and he is a well doer, he hath of a surety lain hold of the firm cable. Unto Allah is the end of all affairs.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcii{%
And whosoever disbelieveth, let not his unbelief grieve thee. Unto Us is their return, and We shall declare unto them that which they have worked. Verily Allah is the Knower of that which is in the breasts.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxciii{%
We let them enjoy for a while, and then We shall drive them to a torment rough.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxciv{%
And wert thou to ask them: who hath created the heavens and the earth they will surely say: Allah. Say thou: All praise unto Allah! But most of them know not,\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcv{%
Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth. Verily Allah! He is the Self-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcvi{%
And if whatever trees there are on the earth were pens, and the sea were ink with seven more seas to help it, the words of Allah could not be exhausted; verily Allah is Mighty, Wise.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcvii{%
And your creation and your upraising are only as though of one soul; verily Allah is Hearing, Beholding.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcviii{%
Observest thou not that Allah plungeth the night into the day and plungeth the day into the night and hath subjected the sun and the moon, each running unto an appointed term, and that Allah is of that which ye work Aware.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcdxcix{%
That is because Allah! He is the Truth, because whatsoever they call upon beside Him is falsehood, and because He is the Exalted, the Grand.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmd{%
Observest thou not that the ship saileth in the sea by the favour of Allah that he may shew you of His signs? Verily therein are signs for every persevering, grateful heart.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdi{%
And when a wave covereth them like awnings, they call upon Allah, making their religion pure for Him. Then when He delivereth them on the land, only some of them keep to the middle course. And none gainsaith Our signssave each perfidious, ingrate one.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdii{%
Mankind! fear your Lord and dread a Day whereon no father shall atone for his son, and no son shall atone for his father at all. Verily the promise of Allahs is true. Let not the life of the world beguile you, and let not the great beguiler beguile you in regard to Allah.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdiii{%
Verily Allah! with Him alone is the knowledge of the Hour, and He it is who sendeth down the rain and knoweth that which is in the wombs: and no person knoweth whatsoever it shall earn on the morrow, and a person knoweth not in whatsoever land he shall die. Verily Allah is Knowing, Aware.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdiv{%
\basmalahen Alif. Lam Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdv{%
Revelation of this Book, whereof there is no doubt, is from the Lord of the Worlds.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdvi{%
Will they say: he hath fabricated it? Aye! it is the truth from thy Lord, that thou mayest warn therewith a people unto whom no warner came before thee, that haply they may be guided.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdvii{%
Allah it is Who created the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is betwixt the twain in six days, and then He established Himself on the throne. No patron have ye nor an intercessor, besides Him. Will ye not then be admonished?\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdviii{%
He disposeth every affair from the heaven unto the earth; thereafter it shall ascend unto Him in a Day the measure whereof is one thousand years of that which ye compute.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdix{%
Such is the Knower of the unseen and the seen, the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdx{%
Who hath made everything exceeding good which He hath created. And He originated the creation of man from clay;\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxi{%
Then He made his progeny from an extract of water base.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxii{%
Then He fashioned him and breathed into him something of a spirit from Him; and He ordained for you hearing and sight and hearts. Little is the thanks ye return.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxiii{%
And they say: when we are vanished in the earth, shall we then be raised in a new creation? Aye! in the meeting with their Lord they are disbelieving.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxiv{%
Say thou: the angel of death who is set over you shall cause you to die, thereafter unto your Lord ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxv{%
Couldst thou but see when the culprits shall hang their heads before their Lord, saying: our Lord! we have now seen and heard; so send us back; we shall work righteously, verily we are convinced.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxvi{%
And had We listed surely We could have given every soul its guidance; but true must be the word from Me; I shall surely fill Hell with the Jinn and mankind together.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxvii{%
So taste ye the sequel, for as much as ye forgat the meeting of this your day, verily We have forgotten you. Taste the torment abiding for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxviii{%
They alone believe in Our revelations who, when they are reminded thereof, fall down prostrate and hallow the praise of their Lord, and they are not stiff-necked.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxix{%
Their sides leave off the couches calling upon their Lord in fear and in desire, and of that wherewith We have provided them they expend.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxx{%
No soul knoweth that which is kept hidden for them of perfect comfort as a recompense for that which they have been working.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxi{%
Shall he, therefore, who is a believer, be like unto him who is a transgressor? They are not equal.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxii{%
And as for those who believe and work rigteous works--for them are Gardens of Abode: an entertainment for that which they have been working.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxiii{%
And as for those who transgress their abode is the Fire. So oft as they desire to get thereout, they shall be sent back thereto; and it will be said unto them: taste the torment of the Fire which ye were wont to belie.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxiv{%
And surely We shall make them taste of the smaller torment prior to the greater torment, that haply they may yet return.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxv{%
And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who is reminded of His signs, then he turneth aside therefrom? Verily unto the culprits We are going to be Avenger.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxvi{%
Assuredly We vouchsafed the Book Unto Musa; so be thou not in doubt in thy receiving it. And We appointed it to be a guidance unto the Children of Is'rail.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxvii{%
And We appointed, from amongst them, leaders guiding others by Our command, when they had persevered, and of Our signs they were convinced.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxviii{%
Verily thy Lord! He shall decide between them on the Day of Judgment concerning that wherein they have been differing.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxix{%
Hath this not guided them: how many generations We have destroyed before them amidst whose dwellings they walk? Verily therein are signs; will they not therefore hearken?\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxx{%
Observe they not that We drive water unto a land bare, and bring forth therewith crops whereof their cattle and they themselves eat? Will they not therefore be enlightened?\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxi{%
And they say: When will this Decision arrive if ye are truthtellers?\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxii{%
Say thou: on the day of the Decision their belief will not profit those who have disbelieved; nor will they be respited.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxiii{%
Wherefore turn aside thou from them, and await; verily they are awaiting.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxiv{%
\basmalahen O Prophet! fear Allah and obey not the infidels and the hypocrites; verily Allah is ever Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxv{%
And follow that which is revealed to thee from thy Lord; verily Allah is of that which ye Work ever Aware.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxvi{%
And put thy trust in Allah and Allah sufficeth as a Trustee.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxvii{%
Allah hath not placed unto any man two hearts in his inside, nor hath He made your spouses whom ye declare to be as your mother's backs, your real mothers, nor hath He made your adopted sons your real sons. This is only your saying by your mouths, whereas Allah saith the truth and He guideth the way.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxviii{%
Call them by their fathers: that will be most equitable in the sight of Allah. And if ye know not their fathers then they are your brethren in religion and your friends. And there is no fault upon you in regard to the mistake ye have made therein, but in regard to that which your hearts intend purposely. And Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxxxix{%
The Prophet is nigher unto the believers than themselves, and his wives are their mothers. And kinsmen are nigher one to another in the ordinance of Allah than other believers and the emigrants except that ye may act reputably unto your friends. This hath been written in the Book.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxl{%
And recall what time We took a bond from the prophets and from thee and from Nuh and Ibrahim and Musa and 'Isa son of Maryam. And We took from them a solemn bond;\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxli{%
That he may question the truthful of their truth. And for the Infidels He hath gotten ready a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlii{%
O Ye who believe! remember Allah's favour unto you when there came unto you hosts, and We sent against them a wind and hosts which ye saw not, and Allah was of that which ye were working a Beholder.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxliii{%
When they came upon you from above you and from below you, and when eyes turned aside and hearts reached to the gullets, and of Allah ye were imagining various things.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxliv{%
There were the believers proven and shaken with a mighty shaking\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlv{%
And when the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is disease were saying: Allah and His apostle have promised us nought but delusion.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlvi{%
And when a party of them said: O inhabitants of Yathrib! there is no place for you, so return. And a part of them asked leave of the Prophet, saying: verily our houses lie open; whereas they lay not open; they only wished to flee.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlvii{%
And if they were to be entered upon from the sides thereof and they were asked to sedition, they would surely have committed it, and they would have tarried therein but slightly.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlviii{%
And arruredly they had already covenanted with Allah that they would not turn their backs; verily the covenant with Allah must be questioned about.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxlix{%
Say thou: flight shall not profit you if ye flee from death or slaughter, and lo! ye will not enjoy life except for a little.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdl{%
Say thou: who is there that will protect you from Allah if He intendeth to bring evil on you or intendeth mercy for you? And they shall not find for themselves, besides Allah, a patron or helper.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdli{%
Surely Allah knoweth those among you who hinder and those who say unto their brethren: come hither unto us; and they themselves come not to the battle save a ittle,\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlii{%
Being niggardly toward you. Then when the fightin cometh, thou beholdest them look unto thee, their eyes rolling about, like the eyes of him who fainteth unto death. Then when the fighting is over they inveigh against you with sharp tongues, being niggardly of the good things. These have not believed; wherefore Allah hath made their works of none effect, and that is with Allah ever easy.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdliii{%
They deem that the confederates have not yet departed; and if the confederates should come, they would fain to be in the desert with the wandering Arabs inquiring for tidings of you. And if they happen to be amongst you, they would fight but little.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdliv{%
Assuredly there hath been for you: in the apostle of Allah an excellent pattern for him who hopeth in Allah and the Last Day and remembereth Allah much.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlv{%
And when the believers saw the confederates, they said: this is that which Allah and His apostle had promised us; and Allah and His apostle had spoken the truth. And it only increased them in belief and in self-surrender.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlvi{%
Of the believers are men who have fulfilled that which they covenaned with Allah. Some of them have performed their vow, and some of them are waiting, so and they have not changed in the least.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlvii{%
All this happened in order that Allah may recompense the truthful for their truth, and may punish the hypocrites if He would, or relent toward them. Verily Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlviii{%
And Allah drave baCk those who disbelieved in their rage; they obtained no advantage, and Allah sufficed for the believers in the fighting; and Allah is ever Strong, Mighty.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlix{%
And He brought those of the people of the Book who backed them down from their fortresses and cast into their hearts terror; a part of them ye slew, and ye made captives a part.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlx{%
And He caused you to inherit their land and their houses and their riches, and land which ye have not yet trodden. And Allah is over everything ever potent.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxi{%
Prophet! say unto thy wives: if it be that ye seek the world's life and the adornment thereof, then come I shall make a provision for you and I shall release you with a handsome release.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxii{%
And if ye seek Allah and His apostle and the abode of the Hereafter, then verily Allah hath gotten ready for the well-doers among you a mighty hire.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxiii{%
O Ye wives of the Prophet! whosoever of you shall commit a manifest Indecency, doubled for her would be the punishment twice over; and with Allah that is easy.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxiv{%
And whosoever of you shall be obedient unto Allah and His apostle and shall work righteously, her hire We shall give her twice over, and We have gotten ready for her a generous provision.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxv{%
wives of the prophet! ye are not like any others of women, if ye are God-fearing. So be not soft in speech, lest one in whose heart is disease should be moved with desire, bun speak a reputable speech.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxvi{%
And stay in Your houses. and display not yourselves! with the display of the times of former Paganism; and establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and obey Allah and His apostle. Allah only desireth to take away uncleanness from you, people of the house-hold, and to purify you with a thorough purification.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxvii{%
And bear in mind that which is rehearsed in your homes of the revelations of Allah and the wisdom. Verily Allah is ever Subtile, Aware.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxviii{%
Verily the Muslim men and Muslim women, and the believing men and the believing women, and the devout men and the devout women, and the men of veracity and the women of veracity, and the persevering men and the persevering women, and the men of humility and the women of humility and the almsgiving men and the almsgiving women, and the fasting men and the fasting women, and the men who guard their modesty and the women who guard their modesty, and the Allah-remembering men and the Allah remembering women: Allah hath gotten ready for them forgiveness and mighty hire.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxix{%
And it is not for a believing man or a believing woman, when Allah and His apostle have decreed an affair, that they should have any choice in their affair. And whosoever disobeyeth Allah and His apostle hath strayed with a manifest straying.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxx{%
And recall what time thou wast saying unto him on whom Allah had conferred favour and thou hadst conferred favour: keep thy wife to thyself and fear Allah; so and thou wast concealing in thy mind that which Allah was going to disclose, and thou wast fearing mankind, whereas Allah had a better right that Him thou shouldst fear. Then when Zaid had performed his purpose concerning her, We wedded her to thee, that there should be no blame for believers in respect of wives of their adopted sons, when they have performed their purpose concerning them. And the ordinance of Allah was to be fulfilled.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxi{%
No blame there is upon the Prophet in that which Allah hath decreed for him. That hath been Allah's dispensation with those who have passed away afore - and the ordinance of Allah hath been a destiny destined\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxii{%
Those who preached the messages of Allah and feared Him, and feared none save Allah; and Allah sufficeth as a Reckoner.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxiii{%
Muhammad is not the father of any of your males, but the apostle of Allah and the seal of the prophets; and Allah of everything is ever the Knower.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxiv{%
O Ye who believe! remember Allah with much remembrance.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxv{%
And hallow Him morning and evening.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxvi{%
He it is Who sendeth His benedictions to you and His angels also that he may bring you forth from darknessess into light; and unto the believers He is ever Merciful.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxvii{%
Their greeting on the Day whereon they meet Him will be: peace. And He hath gotten ready for them a generous hire.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxviii{%
Prophet! verily We have sent thee a witness and a bearer of glad tidings and a warner.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxix{%
And a summoner unto Allah by His command and an illuminating lamp.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxx{%
And bear thou unto the believers the glad tidings that theirs is from Allah a great grace.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxi{%
And obey thou not the infidels and the hypocrites, and heed not their annoyances, and trust in Allah; and Allah sufficeth as a Trustee.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxii{%
O Ye who believe! when ye marry believing women and then divorce them before ye have touched them, then there is no waiting-period from you incumbent on them that ye should count. So make provision for them and release them with a seemly release.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxiii{%
O Prophet! verily We have allowed unto thee thy wives unto whom thou hast given their hires, and also those whomsoever thy right hand ownEth of those whomsoever Allah hath given thee as spoils of war, and the daughters of thy paternal uncle, and the daughters of thy paternal aunts, and the daughters of thy maternal uncle, and the daughters of thy maternal aunts, who migrated with thee, and any believing woman, when she offereth herself unto the Prophet if the Prophet desire to wed her --purely for thee, above the rest of the believers. Surely We know that which We have ordained unto them concerning their wives and those whom their right hands won: in order that there may be no blame upon thee: And Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxiv{%
Thou myest put off such of them as thou wilt, and thou mayest take unto thee such of them as thou wilt; and whomsoever thou desirest if such as thou hadst set aside there is no blame upon thee. This is likelier to cool their eyes and not let them grieve and to keep them pleased with whatsoever thou shalt give every one of them. Allah knoweth that which is in your hearts. and Allah is ever Knowing, Forbearing.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxv{%
Women are not allowed unto thee henceforth, nor mayest thou change them for other wives although their beauty please thee, save those whom thy right hand shall own; and Allah is ever over everything a Watcher.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxvi{%
O Ye who believe! enter not the houses of the Prophet, except when leave is given you, for a meal and at a time that ye will have to wait for its preparation; but when ye are invited, then enter, and when ye have eaten, then disperse, without lingering to enter into familiar discourse. Verily that incommodeth the Prophet, and he is shy of asking you to depart, bur Allah is not shy of the truth. And when ye ask of them aught, ask it of them from behind a curtain. That shall be purer for your hearts and for their hearts. And it is not lawful for you that ye should cause annoyance to the apostle of Allah, nor that ye should ever marry his wives after him; verily that in the sight of Allah shall be an enormity.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxvii{%
Whether ye disclose a thing or conceal it, verily Allah is of everything ever Knower.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxviii{%
It is no sin for them in respect to their fathers or their brothers, or their brothers sons, or their sisters sons, or their own women, or those whom their right hands own; and fear Allah; verily Allah is of everything ever a Witness.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdlxxxix{%
Verily Allah and His angels send their benedictions upon the prophet. O ye who believe! send your benedictions upon him and salute him with a goodly Salutation.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxc{%
Verily those who annoy Allah and His apostle, --Allah hath cursed them in the world and the Hereafter, and hath gotten ready for them a torment Ignominious.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxci{%
And those who annoy the believing men and the believing women, without their earning it, shall surely bear the guilt of calumny and manifest sin.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcii{%
O Prophet! say unto thy wives and thy daughters and women of the believers that they should let down upon them their wrapping- garments. That would be more likely to distinguish them so that they will not be affronted. And Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxciii{%
If the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a disease and the raisers of commotion in Madina desist not, We shall surely set thee up against them; thenceforth they shall not be suffered to neighbour thee therein except for a little while.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxciv{%
Accursed; wherever found they shall be laid hold of and slain with a relentless slaughter.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcv{%
That hath been the dispensation of Allah with those who have passed away afore; and thou shalt not find in the dispensation of Allah any change.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcvi{%
People ask thee ccncerning the Hour. Say thou: the knowledge there of is only with Allah: and what knowest thou! --belike the Hour is nigh.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcvii{%
Verily Allah hath cursed the infidels, and hath gotten ready for them a Blaze.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcviii{%
Abiders therein they shall be for ever, and they shall find neither a protecting friend nor a helper.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdxcix{%
On the Day whereon their faces shall be rolled in the Fire, they will say: Oh that we had obeyed Allah and had obeyed the apostle!\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdc{%
And they will say: our Lord! verily we obeyed our chiefs and our great ones, and they led us astray from the way.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdci{%
Our Lord! give them double torment and curse them with a great curse.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcii{%
O Ye who believe! be not like unto those who annoyed Musa; but Allah cleared him of that which they said, and he was in the sight of Allah illustrious.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdciii{%
O Ye who believe! fear Allah, and speak a straight speech.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdciv{%
He WiLL rectify for you your works, and forgive you your sins. And Whosoever obeyeth Allah and His apostle, he hath indeed achieved a mighty achievement.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcv{%
Verily We! We offered the trust unto the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they refused to bear it and shrank therefor. And man bore it; verily he was very iniquitous and very ignorant-\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcvi{%
So that Allah will torment the hypocritical men and the hypocritical women and the associators and the associatoresses and Allah will relent toward believing men and the believing women; and Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcvii{%
\basmalahen All praise Unto Allah whose is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth; and His is the praise in the Hereafter And He is the Wise, the Aware.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcviii{%
He knoweth whatsoever penetrateth into the earth and whatsoever cometh forth therefrom and whatsoever descendeth from the heaven and whatsoever ascendeth thereto. And He is the Merciful, the Forgiving.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcix{%
Those who disbelieve say: the Hour will not come Unto us. Say thou: yea, by my Lord the Knower of the unseen, it will surely come Unto you. Not the weight of an atom escapeth Him in the heavens or in the earth; nor is there anything less than it nor greater but it is inscribed in a Luminous Book\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcx{%
That He may recompense these who believed and worked righteous works. Those! theirs shall be forgiveness and a generous provision.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxi{%
And those who endeavoured to frustrate Our signs - those! theirs shall be a torment of afflictive calamity.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxii{%
And who have been vouchsafed knowledge beholding that the Book which hath been sent down Unto thee from thy Lord, - it is the truth and it guideth Unto the path of the Mighty, the Praiseworthy,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxiii{%
And those who disbelieve say: shall we direct you toward a man declaring Unto you that when ye have become dispersed" with full dispersion, then ye will be raised Unto a new creation?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxiv{%
Hath he fabricated a lie against Allah, or is therein him a madness? Nay, but those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are themselves in a torment and error far-reaching:\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxv{%
Behold they not that which is before them and that which is behind them of the heaven and the earth If We will, We shall sink the earth with them or cause a fragment of the heaven to fall on them. Verily therein is a sign Unto every repentant bondman.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxvi{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed Unto Da'ud grace from us,' and said: mountains! repeat Our praise with him; and also ye birds! And We softened for him the iron.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxvii{%
Saying: make thou complete coats of mail, and rightly dispose the links, and work ye, righteously; verily I am of that which Ye work a Beholder.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxviii{%
And Unto Sulaiman We subjected the wind, whereof the morning journeying was a month and the evening journeying a month. And We made a fount of brass to flow for him. And of the Jinn were some who worked before him by the Will Of his Lord. And whosoever of them swerved from Our command, him We shall cause to taste the torment of the Blaze.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxix{%
They worked for him whatsoever he pleased, of lofty halls and statues and basins like cisterns and cauldrons Standing firm. Work ye, house of Da'ud! with thanksgiving; few of My bondmen are thankful.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxx{%
Then when We decreed death for him, naught discovered his death to them' save a moving creature of the earth which gnawed away his staff. Then when he fell, the Jinn clearly perceived that, if they had known the unseen they would not have tarried in the ignominious torment.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxi{%
Assuredly there was for Saba a sign in their own dwelling- place: two gardens on the right hand and on the left. And it was said Unto them: eat ye of the provision of your Lord and give thanks Unto Him: a fair land' and a forgiving Lord.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxii{%
But they turned away. Wherefore We sent upon them the inundation of the dam and We exchanged their two gardens for two gardens bearing bitter fruit, and tamarisk. And some few lote-trees.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxiii{%
In this wise We requited them for they were ungrateful. And We requite not thus any save the ungrateful infidels.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxiv{%
And We had placed between them and the cities" which We had blest cities easy to be seen, and We had made the stages of journey between them easy:" travel in them nights and days secure.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxv{%
Then they said: Our Lord make the distance between our journeys longer. And they wronged themselves. Wherefore We made them by words and dispersed them with a total dispersion. Verily herein are signs for every persevering, grateful persons.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxvi{%
And assuredly Iblis found his conjecture true concerning them; and they followed him all save a party of the believers.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxvii{%
And he hath no authority over them except that We would know him who believeth in the Hereafter from him who is in doubt thereof. And thy Lord is over everything a Warden.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxviii{%
Say thou: call upon those whom ye assert beside Allah. They own not an atom's weight either in the heavens or in the earth, nor have they any partnership in either, nor is there for Him from among them any supporter.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxix{%
lntercession with Him profiteth not save the intercession of him whom He giveth leave. They hold their peace until when fright is taken off from their hearts, they say: What is it that your Lord hath said? They say: the very truth. And He is the Exalted, the Great.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxx{%
Say thou: who provideth food for you from the heavens and the earth? Say thou: Allah; verily either we or ye are on the guidance or in error manifest.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxi{%
Say thou: ye will not be questioned about that which we have committed, nor shall we be questioned about that which ye work.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxii{%
Say thou: our Lord shall assemble us together, then He shall judge between us with truth; and He is the Great Judge, the Knower.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxiii{%
Say thou: show me those whom ye have joined with Him as associates. By no means! Aye! He is Allah, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxiv{%
And We have not sent thee save as a bearer of glad tidings and a warner Unto all mankind; but most of man kind know not.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxv{%
And they say: when is this promise to be fulfilled if ye say sooth?\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxvi{%
Say thou: the appointment to you is for a Day which ye cannot put back for one hour nor can ye anticipate.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxvii{%
And those who disbelieve say: we shall by no means believe in this Qur'an nor in that which hath been before it. Would that thou couldst see when the wrong-doers shall be made to stand before their Lord! They shall cast back the word one to another; those who were deemed weak will say Unto those who were stiff-necked: had it not been for you, surely we should have been believers.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxviii{%
Those who were stiff-necked will say Unto those who were deemed weak: was it we who prevented you from the guidance after it had come Unto you? Aye! ye have been guilty yourselves.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxxxix{%
And those who were deemed weak will say Unto those who were stiff necked: aye, it was your plotting by night and by day, When ye were commanding us that we should disbelieve in Allah and set up peers Unto Him. And they Will keep secret their shame when they behold the torment. And We shall place shackles on the necks of those who disbelieved. They shall be requited not save according to that which they had been working.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxl{%
And We sent not a warner Unto a town but the affluent thereof said:' verily in that wherewith ye have been sent we are disbelievers.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxli{%
And they said: we are more numerous in riches and children, and we are not going to be tormented.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlii{%
Say thou: verily my Lord expandeth the provision for whomsoever He will and stinteth it; but most of mankind know not.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxliii{%
And it is not your riches nor your children that shall draw you nigh Unto us with a near approach, but whoso ever believeth and worketh righteously- then those! theirs shall be a twofold meed for that which they will have worked, and they will be in upper apartments secure.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxliv{%
And those who endeavour to frustrate Our signs, Unto the torment they will be brought.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlv{%
Say thou: verily my Lord expandeth the provision for whomsoever He listeth of His bondmen, and stinteth it for him. And whatsoever ye expend of aught He shall replace it. And He is the Best of Providers.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlvi{%
And on the Day whereon He gathereth them together, then He will say Unto the angels: was it ye that these were wont to worship?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlvii{%
They will say: hallowed be Thou! Thou art our protecting friend, not they; Aye! they have been worshipping the jinn; In them most of them were believers.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlviii{%
To-day ye own not for one another either benefit or hurt. And We shall say Unto those who did wrong: taste the torment of the Fire which ye were wont to belie.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxlix{%
And when there are rehearsed Unto them Our plain revelations, they this messenger is naught but as a man who seeketh to prevent you from that which your fathers have been worshipping. And they say: this message is naught but a fraud fabricated. And those who disbelieve say of the truth When it is come Unto them: this is naught but manifest magic.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcl{%
And We had not vouchsafed Unto them Books they should have been studying, nor had We sent Unto them, before thee, any warner.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcli{%
And those before them belied; and these have not arrived Unto a tithe of that which We vouchsafed Unto them. But they belied My apostles. So how terrible was My disapproval\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclii{%
Say thou: I but exhort you Unto one thing: that ye stand, for Allah's sake, by twos and singly, and then ponder; in your companion there is no madness; he is naught but a warner Unto you preceding a torment severe.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcliii{%
Say thou: whatsoever hire might have asked of you is yours; my hire is with Allah only. And He is of everything a Witness.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcliv{%
Say thou: verily my Lord hurleth the truth: the Knower of things hidden.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclv{%
Say thou: the truth is come, and falsehood shall neither originate nor be restored."\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclvi{%
Say thou: if ever I go astray, I shall stray only against myself, and if I remain guided it is because of that which my Lord hath revealed Unto me. Verily He is Hearing, Nigh.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclvii{%
And couldst thou see the time when they shall be terrified! Then there shall be no escaping, and they shall be laid hold of from a place quite nigh.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclviii{%
And then they will say: we believe therein. But whence can there be the attainment of faith from a place so afar.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclix{%
Whereas they disbelieved therein afore, and conjectured about the unseen from a place so afar.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclx{%
And they will be shut off from that which they will eagerly desire, as shall be done with the likes of them of yore. Verily they have been in doubt perplexing.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxi{%
\basmalahen All praise Unto Allah, the Creator Of the heavens and the earth, the Appointer of the angels as His messengers, with wings of twos and threes and fours. He addeth in creation what soever He listeth Verily Allah is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxii{%
Whatsoever of mercy Allah may grant Unto mankind none there is to withhold it; and whatsoever He may with hold none there is to release it thereafter. And He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxiii{%
O mankind! remember the favour of Allah toward you. Is there any Creator other than Allah who provideth for you from the heaven and the earth? There is no god but He. Wither then are ye deviating?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxiv{%
And if they belie thee, then surely apostles have been belied before thee. And Unto Allah shall be brought back all affairs.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxv{%
O mankind! verily the promise of Allah is true. So let not the life of the world beguile you, and with respect to Allah let not beguile you the great be guiler.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxvi{%
Verily the Satan is an enemy Unto you, wherefore hold him for an enemy; he only calleth his confederates that they become of the fellows of the Blaze.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxvii{%
Those who disbelieve - theirs shall be a torment severe; and those who believe and work righteous works, - theirs shall be forgiveness and a great hire.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxviii{%
Is he, then, whose evil work hath been made fair-seeming unto him, so that he deemeth it good, be as he who rightly perceiveth the truth? Verily Allah sendeth astray whomsoever He listeth, and guideth whomsoever He listeth; so let not thine soul expire after them in sighings; verily Allah is the Knower of that which they perform.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxix{%
And it is Allah Who sendeth the winds, and they raise a cloud; then We drive it unto a dead land and We quicken thereby the earth after the death thereof. Even so shall be the Resurrection.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxx{%
Whosoever desireth glory, then all glory is Allah's; unto Him mount up the goodly words; and the righteous works exalteth it. And those who plot evils,--theirs shall be a torment severe; and the plotting of those!--it shall perish.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxi{%
And Allah created you of dust, then of a seed; then He made you pairs. No female beareth or bringeth forth but with His knowledge. And no aged man growth old, nor is aught diminished of his life, but it is in a Book; verily for Allah that is easy.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxii{%
And the two seas are not alike: this, sweet, thirst- quenching, pleasant to drink; and that, saltish and bitter. And yet from each ye eat flesh fresh and bring forth the ornaments that ye wear. And thou seest therein ships cleaving the water, that ye may seek of His graCe, and that haply ye may give thanks.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxiii{%
He plungeth the night into the day and He plungeth the day into the night, and He hath subjected the sun and moon, each running till an appointed term. Such is Allah, your Lord; His is the dominion; and those whom ye call on besides Him own not even the husk of a date-stone.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxiv{%
If ye call Unto them, they hear not your calling, and even if they heard, they could not answer you. On the Day of Judgment they will deny your associating. And none can declare Unto thee the truth like Him who is Aware.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxv{%
O mankind! ye are needers Unto Allah, and Allah! He is the Selfsufficient, the Praiseworthy\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxvi{%
If He will, He can take you away and bring about a new creation."\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxvii{%
And with Allah that shall not be hard.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxviii{%
And a bearer of burthen will not bear another's burthen, and if one heavy-laden calleth for his load, naught thereof will be borne although he be of kin. Thou canst warn only those who fear their Lord, unseen, and establish prayer. And whosoever becometh clean becometh clean only for himself; and Unto Allah is the return.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxix{%
Not alike are the blind and the seeing.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxx{%
Neither darknesses and light,\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxi{%
- Nor the shade and the sun's heat.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxii{%
Nor alike are the living and the dead. Verily Allah maketh whomsoever He listeth to hear and thou canst not make them hear who are in the graves.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxiii{%
Thou art naught but a warner.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxiv{%
Verily We! We have sent thee with the truth, as a bearer of glad tidings and as a warner; and there is not a community but there hath passed among them a warner.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxv{%
And if they belie thee, then surely those before them have also belied. Their apostles came Unto them with evidences and scriptures and a Book luminous.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxvi{%
Then I took hold of those who disbelieved. So how terrible was My disapproval!\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxvii{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah sendeth down water from the heaven, and then We thereby bring fruit of diverse colours? And in the mountains are steaks white and red, of diverse colours, and also intensely black.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxviii{%
And of men and beasts and cattle, likewise of diverse colours. Those only of His bondmen who have knowledge fear Allah Verily Allahis the Mighty, the Forgiving.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdclxxxix{%
Verily those Who read the book of Allah and establish prayer and expend of that wherewith We have provided them, secretly and in open, hope for a merchandise that shall not perish.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxc{%
That He may pay them their hires in full and increase Unto them of His grace; verily, He is Forgiving, Appreciative.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxci{%
And that which We have revealed Unto thee of the Book - it is the very truth confirming that which hath been before it; verily, Allah is Unto His servants Aware, Beholding.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcii{%
Thereafter We made inheritors of the book those whom We chose of Our bondmen. Then of them are some who wrong themselves, and of them are some who keep the middle way, and of them are some who, by Allah's leave, go ahead in virtues. That! that is a great grace.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxciii{%
Gardens Everlasting! these they Shall enter, wearing therein bracelets of gold and pearls, and their raiment therein shall be of silk.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxciv{%
And they will Say: all praise Unto Allah who hath taken away grief from us. verily, our Lord is Forgiving, Appreciative.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcv{%
Who hath, through His grace, lodged us in the abode of permanence, wherein there will not touch us tall, and wherein there will not touch us weariness.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcvi{%
And those who disbelieve-for them shall be Hell-Fire. It shall not be decreed to them that they should die, nor shall the torment thereof be lightened for them. Thus We requite Every ingrate.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcvii{%
And they will be shouting therein: our Lord! take us out; we shall work righteously, not that which we have been working. Gave We not you lives long enough so that whosoever would receive admonition could receive admonition therein? and there came Unto you a warner; taste therefore and for the wrong-doers there will be no helper.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcviii{%
Verily Allah is the Knower of the unseen of the heavens and the earth. Verily, He is the Knower of that which is in the breasts.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcxcix{%
He it is who hath made you successors in the earth. So whosoever disbelieveth, on him will befall his infidelity. And for the infidels their infidelity increaseth with their Lord naught save abhorence. And for the infidels their infidelity increastth naught save loss.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcc{%
Say thou: what bethink ye of your associate-gods upon which ye call besides Allah? Show me whatsoever they have created of the earth. Or, have they7 any partnership in the heavens? Or have We vouchsafed to them a Book so that they stand on an evidence therefrom? Nay! the wrong-doers promise each other only delusions.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcci{%
Verily Allah withholdeth the heavens and the earth lest they cease; and should they cease, not any one could withhold them after Him. Verily He is ever Forbearing, Forgiving.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccii{%
And`they swear by God with a most solemn oath, that if there came a warnet Unto them, they would surely be better guided than any of the other communities. Then when there did come Unto them a warner, it increased in them naught save aversion,-\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcciii{%
Through their stiff-neckedness in the land, And the plotting of evil only infoldeth the authors thereof. Wait they, then, but the dispensation of the ancients? And thou wilt not find in dispensation of Allah a change, nor wilt thou find in dispensation of Allah a turning off\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcciv{%
Have they not travelled on the earth, so that they might see what wise hath been the end of those before them. although they were stronger than these in Power? And Allah is not such that aught in the heavens and the earth can frustrate him. Verily, He is ever the Knowing, the potent.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccv{%
Were Allah to take mankind to task for that which they earn, He would not leave a moving creature on the back thereof; but He putteth them off until a term appointed; then when their term cometh, - then, verily Allah is ever of His bondmen a Beholder.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccvi{%
\basmalahen Ya-Sin.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccvii{%
By the Qur'an full of wisdom.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccviii{%
Verily thou art of the sent ones,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccix{%
upon the straight path.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccx{%
This is a revelation of the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxi{%
That thou mayest warn a people whose fathers were not warned; so they are negligent.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxii{%
Assuredly the word hath been justified against most of them, wherefore they shall not believe.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxiii{%
Verily We have placed on their necks shackles which are up to the chins; so that their heads are forced up.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxiv{%
And We have placed before them a barrier and behind them a barrier, so We have covered them, so that they see not.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxv{%
And it is alike Unto them, whather thou warnest them or warnest them not; they shall not believe.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxvi{%
Thou canst warn only him who followeth the admonition and feareth the Compassionate, unseen. So bear thou Unto him the glad tidings of forgiveness and a generous hire.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxvii{%
Verily We! We shall guicken the dead. And We write down that which they send before and their footsteps. And everything We have counted up in a Book luminous.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxviii{%
And propound thou Unto them the similitude of the inhabitants of a town, When there came thereto the sent ones;\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxix{%
What time We sent Unto them two, then they belied the twain, wherefore We strengthened them with a third, and they said: verily we are Unto you the sent ones.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxx{%
They said: ye are but human beings like ourselves; the Compassionate hath not sent down aught; ye are only lying.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxi{%
They said: our Lord knoweth that we are surely Unto you the sent ones.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxii{%
And on us is naught but manifest preaching.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxiii{%
They said: verily we augur ill of you; if ye desist not, we shall surely stone you, and there will befall you from us a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxiv{%
They said: your evil augury be with you. Call ye it an ill- luck because ye are admonished! Aye! ye are a people extravagant.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxv{%
And there came from the farthest part of the town a man running. He said; O my people! follow the sent ones.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxvi{%
Follow those who ask not of you any hire, and who are rightly guided.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxvii{%
And what aileth me that I should not worship Him who hath created me, and Unto whom ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxviii{%
Shall I take beside Him gods when, if the Compassionate should intend me any harm, their intercession will avail me not at all, nor would they save me?\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxix{%
Verily then I should be in error manifest.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxx{%
Verily I believe now in your Lord; so hearken Unto me."\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxi{%
It was said: enter thou the Garden. He said: would that my people knew.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxii{%
That my Lord hath forgiven me, and hath made me of the honoured ones.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxiii{%
And We sent not against his people after him a host from heaven, nor have We been sending down any such.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxiv{%
It was but one shout, and lo! they were extinct.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxv{%
Ah the misery of the bondmen! there cometh not: Unto them an apostle but him they have been mocking.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxvi{%
Behold they not how many We have destroyed before them of the generations! verily Unto them they shall not return.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxvii{%
And surely all, every one of them, shall be brought before us.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxviii{%
And a sign Unto them is the dead land. We quicken it and therecut We bring forth grain, so that thereof they eat.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxxxix{%
And We place therein gardens of the date-palms and vines; and We therein cause to gush forth springs.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxl{%
That they may eat of the fruit thereof; and their hands worked it not. Will they not, therefore, give thanks?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxli{%
Hallowed be He who hath created all the pairs of that which the earth groweth, and of themselves and of that which they know not!\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlii{%
And a sign Unto them is the night. We draw off the day therefrom, and lo! they are darkened.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxliii{%
And the sun runneth to its appointed term: that is the disposition of the Mighty, the Knowing."\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxliv{%
And the moon! For it We have decreed mansions till it reverteth like the old branch of a palm-tree.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlv{%
It is not permitted to the sun that it should overtake the moon, nor can the night outstrip the day: each in an orbit, they float.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlvi{%
And a sign Unto them is that We bear their offspring in a laden ship.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlvii{%
And We have created for them of the like thereUnto whereon they ride.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlviii{%
And if We list, We shall drown them, and there will be no shout for them, nor will they be saved.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxlix{%
unless it be a mercy from us, and as an enjoyment for a season.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccl{%
And when it is said Unto them: fear that which is before you and that which is behind you, that haply ye may find mercy, they withdraw.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccli{%
And not a sign cometh Unto them of the signs of their Lord, but they are ever backsliders therefrom.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclii{%
And when it is said Unto them: expend of that wherewith Allah hath provided you, those who disbelieve say Unto those who believe: shall we feed those whom God Himself would have fed, if He listed? Ye are in naught else than error manifest.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccliii{%
And they say: when will this promise be fulfilled if ye say sooth?\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccliv{%
They await not but one shout, which shall lay hold of them while they are yet wrangling.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclv{%
And they will not be able to make a disposition, nor to their family they return.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclvi{%
And the trumpet shall be blown, and lo! from the tombs Unto their Lord they shall be hastening.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclvii{%
They will say: Ah woe Unto us! who hath roused us from our sleeping-place? This is that which the Compassionate had promised, and truly spake the sent ones.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclviii{%
It shall be but one shout; and lo! they shall all be brought together before us.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclix{%
To-day no soul will be wronged at all; nor shall ye be requited but for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclx{%
Verily the fellows of the Garden to-day shall be happily employed.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxi{%
They and their spouses, in shade on couches shall be reclining.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxii{%
Theirs shall be fruit therein and theirs shall be whatsoever they ask for.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxiii{%
Peace shall be the word from the Lord Merciful.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxiv{%
And separate yourselves this Day, O ye culprits!\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxv{%
Enjoined I not on you, ye children of Adam, that ye shall not worship the Satan - verily he is Unto you manifest foe.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxvi{%
And that: ye shall worship Me; this is the straight path?\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxvii{%
And yet assuredly he hath led astray of you a great multitude. Wherefore reflect ye not?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxviii{%
Yonder is Hell, which ye were promised.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxix{%
Roast therein To-day for that ye have been disbelieving.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxx{%
To-day We shall seal upon their mouths, and their hands will speak Unto us, and their feet will bear witness of that which they have been earning.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxi{%
And if We listed, surely We should wipe out their eyes so that they would struggle for the way how then would they see?\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxii{%
And if We listed, surely We should transform them in their places, so that they would be able neither to go forward nor to return\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxiii{%
And whomsoever We grant long life, We reverse him in creation. Reflect then they not?\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxiv{%
And We have not taught him poetry, nor it befitteth him. This is but an admonition and a Recital luminous:\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxv{%
In order that it may warn him who is alive, and that the sentence may be justified on the infidels.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxvi{%
Observe they not that We have created for them, of that which Our hands have worked, cattle: so that they are their owners.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxvii{%
And We have subdued them Unto them, so that some of them they have for riding and on some of them they feed?\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxviii{%
And they have therefrom other benefits and drinks. Will they not then give thanks?\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxix{%
And they have taken beside Allah gods, hoping that haply they may be succoured.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxx{%
They are not able to give them succour; whereas they shall be against them host brought forward.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxi{%
So let not their speech grieve thee. Verily We! We know whatsoever they keep secret and whatsoever they make known.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxii{%
Beholdest not man that We have created him from a sperm? Yet lo! he is a manifest disputer?\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxiii{%
And he propoundeth for us a similitude, and forgetteth his creation, He saith: who shall quicken the bones when they are decayed?\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxiv{%
Say thou:" He shall quicken them Who brought them forth for the first time, and He is of every kind of creation the Knower!\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxv{%
Who giveth you out of the green tree fire, and lo! ye kindle therewith.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxvi{%
Is not He who created the heavens and the earth able to create the like of these? Yea! He is the Supreme Creator, the Knower.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxvii{%
His affair, when He intendeth a thing, is only that He saith Unto it: be, and it becometh.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxviii{%
Wherefore hallowed be He in whose hand is the governance of everything, and Unto whom ye shall be returned.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcclxxxix{%
\basmalahen By the angels ranged in ranks.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxc{%
By the angels driving away.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxci{%
By the angels reciting the praise.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcii{%
Verily your God is One.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxciii{%
Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in- between the twain, and Lord of the easts.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxciv{%
Verily We! We have adorned the nearest heaven with an adornment: the stars.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcv{%
And have placed therein a guard against any Satan froward.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcvi{%
They cannot listen to the exalted assembly, and they are darted at from every side.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcvii{%
With a driving fusillade, and theirs shall be a torment perpetual;\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcviii{%
Except him who snatcheth away a word by stealth, and him then pursueth a glowing flame.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccxcix{%
Ask them thou: are they stronger in structure or those others whom We have created? Verily We! We have created them of a sticky clay.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccc{%
Aye! thou marvellest, and they scoff.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccci{%
And when they are admonished, they receive not admcnition.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccii{%
And when they behold a sign, they turn to scoffing.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccciii{%
And they say: this Qur'an is naught but magic manifest.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccciv{%
When we have become dead and have become dust and bones, shall we then verily be raised?\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccv{%
And also our forefathers?\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccvi{%
Say thou: and verily ye; shall then be despicable.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccvii{%
It shall be but one shout, lo! they shall be staring.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccviii{%
And they will say: Ah! woe be Unto us! this is the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccix{%
This is the Day of Judgment which ye were wont to belie.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccx{%
Gather together those who did wrong and their comrades and that which they were wont to worship\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxi{%
Beside Allah, and lead them on to the path of the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxii{%
And stop them; verily they are to be questioned:\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxiii{%
What aileth you that ye succour not one another?\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxiv{%
Nay! on that Day they will be entirely submissive.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxv{%
And they will advance toward each other mutually questioning.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxvi{%
They will say: verily ye! ye were wont to come Unto us Imposing.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxvii{%
They will say: nay! ye yourselves were not believers.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxviii{%
And we had over you no authority, but ye were a people exorbitant.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxix{%
So on us hath been justified the sentence of our Lord: verily we are to taste.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxx{%
We seduced you astray; verily we were ourselves the seduced ones.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxi{%
So verily on that Day they all in the torment will be sharers.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxii{%
Verily We! in this wise We deal with the culprits.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxiii{%
Verily when it was said Unto them: there is no god but Allah, they ever grew stiff-necked.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxiv{%
And they said: are we going to abandon our gods on account of a Poet distracted?\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxv{%
Aye! he hath come with the truth, and he confesseth to the sent ones.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxvi{%
Verily ye are going to taste a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxvii{%
And ye shall be required not except for that which ye have been doing;\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxviii{%
But the bondmen of Allah, the sincere ones -\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxix{%
Those! theirs shall be a provision known:\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxx{%
Fruits! And they shall be honoured.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxi{%
In Gardens of Delight.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxii{%
On couches, facing one another.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxiii{%
Round shall be passed a cup Unto them filled with limpid drink:\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxiv{%
White, a pleasure Unto the drinkers.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxv{%
No headiness there shall be therein, nor shall they be therewith Inebriated.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxvi{%
And with them shall be damsels of refraining looks, large- eyed\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxvii{%
As though they were eggs hidden.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxviii{%
Then they will advance Unto each other, mutually questioning.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxxxix{%
And a speaker from among them will say: verily there was Unto me a mate.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxl{%
Who said: art thou of those who confess to the doctrine of Resurrection:\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxli{%
When we are dead and have become dust and bones, are we indeed going to be requited?\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlii{%
Allah will say: will ye look down?\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxliii{%
Then he will look down and see him in the midst of the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxliv{%
And he will say: by Allah, thou hadst wellnigh causedest me to perish.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlv{%
And but for the favourcf my lord, I should have been of those brought forward.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlvi{%
Are we not then to die\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlvii{%
Save our first death, and are we not to be tormented?\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlviii{%
Verily this! that is the supreme achievement.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxlix{%
For the like of this, then, let the workers work.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccl{%
Is this better as an entertainment or the tree of Zaqqum?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccli{%
Verily We! We have made it a temptation for the wrong- doers.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclii{%
Verily it is a tree that springeth forth in the bottom of Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccliii{%
The fruit thereof is as though the hoods of the serpents.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccliv{%
And verily they must eat thereof and fill their bellies therewith.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclv{%
And thereafter verily they shall have thereon a draught of balling water.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclvi{%
And thereafter verily their return is Unto the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclvii{%
Verily they found their fathers gone astray.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclviii{%
So they in their footsteps are rushing.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclix{%
And assuredly there went stray before them many of the ancients.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclx{%
And assuredly We sent among them warners.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxi{%
So behold what wise hath been the end of those who were warned.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxii{%
Save the bondmen of Allah sincere.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxiii{%
And assuredly Nuh cried Unto us; and We are the Best of answerers!\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxiv{%
And We delivered him and his people from the great affliction.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxv{%
And his offspring! them We made the survivors.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxvi{%
And We left for him among the posterity.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxvii{%
Peace be on Nuh among the worlds.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxviii{%
Verily We! thus We recompense the well-doers.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxix{%
Verily he was of Our bondmen believing.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxx{%
Then We drowned the others.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxi{%
And verily of his sect was Ibrahim.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxii{%
Recall what time he came Unto his lord with a heart whole.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxiii{%
Recall what time he said Unto his father and his people: What is it that ye worship?\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxiv{%
Is it a falsehood-god beside Allah - that ye desire?\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxv{%
what, then, is your opinion of the Lord of the worlds?\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxvi{%
Then he glanced a glance on the stars.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxvii{%
And he said: verily I am about to be sick.\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxviii{%
So they departed from him turning their backs.\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxix{%
Then he slipped Unto their gods and said: eat ye not\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxx{%
What aileth ye that ye speak not?\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxi{%
Then he slipped Unto them striking them with the right hand.\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxii{%
Then they advanced toward him, hastening.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxiii{%
He said: worship ye that which carve.\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxiv{%
Whereas Allah hath created you and that which ye make?\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxv{%
They said. build for him a building and cast him into the flaming fire.\qt@no{(97)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxvi{%
And they devised a plot for him, but We made them the humble.\qt@no{(98)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxvii{%
And he said: verily I am going to my Lord who will guide me.\qt@no{(99)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxviii{%
My Lord! Bestow on me a son who will be of the righteous.\qt@no{(100)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdccclxxxix{%
Wherefore We gave him the glad tidings of a boy gentle.\qt@no{(101)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxc{%
And when he attained the age of, running with him, he said: O my son! verily I have seen in a dream that I am slaughtering thee; so look, what considerest thou? He said: O my father! do that which thou art commanded; thou shalt find me, Allah willing, of the patients.\qt@no{(102)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxci{%
Then when the twain had submitted themselves and he had prostrated him upon his temple.\qt@no{(103)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcii{%
We cried Unto him: O Ibrahim\qt@no{(104)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxciii{%
Of a surety thou hast fulfilled the vision. Verily We! thus We recompense the well-doers.\qt@no{(105)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxciv{%
Verily that! that was a trial manifest.\qt@no{(106)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcv{%
And We ransomed him with a mighty victim.\qt@no{(107)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcvi{%
And We left for him among the posterity:\qt@no{(108)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcvii{%
Peace be Unto Ibrahim:\qt@no{(109)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcviii{%
Verily We! thus We compense the well-doers.\qt@no{(110)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmdcccxcix{%
Verily he was one of Our believing bondmen.\qt@no{(111)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcm{%
And We gave him the glad tidings of Is-haq, a prophet, and of the righteous.\qt@no{(112)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmi{%
And We blessed him and Is-haq; and of their offspring are some well-doers and some who wrong themselves manifestly.\qt@no{(113)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmii{%
And assuredly We gave grace Unto Musa and Harun.\qt@no{(114)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmiii{%
And delivered them and their people from the great affliction.\qt@no{(115)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmiv{%
And We succoured them so that they became overcomers.\qt@no{(116)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmv{%
And We vouchsafed Unto the twain a Book luminous.\qt@no{(117)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmvi{%
And We led the twain on Unto the straight path.\qt@no{(118)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmvii{%
And We left for the twain among the posterity:\qt@no{(119)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmviii{%
Peace be Unto Musa and Harun.\qt@no{(120)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmix{%
Verily We! thus We recompense the well-doers.\qt@no{(121)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmx{%
Verily the twain were of Our bondmen believing.\qt@no{(122)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxi{%
And verily, llyas was one of the sent ones.\qt@no{(123)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxii{%
Recall what time he said Unto his people: fear ye not?\qt@no{(124)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxiii{%
Call ye upon Bal and forsake the Best of creators.\qt@no{(125)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxiv{%
Allah, your Lord and Lord of your forefathers?\qt@no{(126)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxv{%
Then they belied him, so verily they are to be brought up.\qt@no{(127)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxvi{%
Except the bondmen of Allah sincere.\qt@no{(128)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxvii{%
And We left for him among the posterity:\qt@no{(129)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxviii{%
Peace be Unto Elyasin.\qt@no{(130)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxix{%
Verily We! thus We recompense the well-doers.\qt@no{(131)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxx{%
Verily he was one of Our bondmen believing.\qt@no{(132)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxi{%
And verily Lut was of the sent ones.\qt@no{(133)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxii{%
Recall what time We delivered him and his household, all.\qt@no{(134)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxiii{%
Save an old woman among the lingerers.\qt@no{(135)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxiv{%
Then We annihilated the others.\qt@no{(136)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxv{%
And surely ye pass by them in the morning.\qt@no{(137)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxvi{%
And at night. Will ye not therefore reflect?\qt@no{(138)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxvii{%
And verily Yunus was Of the sent ones.\qt@no{(139)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxviii{%
Recall what time he ran away Unto a laden ship.\qt@no{(140)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxix{%
Then he joined the lots, and was of the condemned.\qt@no{(141)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxx{%
And a fish swallowed him, and he was reproaching himself.\qt@no{(142)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxi{%
And had he not been of those who hallow Him,\qt@no{(143)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxii{%
He would have tarried in the belly thereof till the Day when they are raised.\qt@no{(144)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxiii{%
Then We cast him on a bare desert whilst he was sick.\qt@no{(145)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxiv{%
And We caused to grow over him a tree, a gourd.\qt@no{(146)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxv{%
And We had sent him to a hundred thousand: rather they exceeded.\qt@no{(147)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxvi{%
And they believed, whrefore We let them enjoy life for a season.\qt@no{(148)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxvii{%
Now ask thou them: there for thy Lord daughters and for them sons?\qt@no{(149)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxviii{%
Or created We the angels females while they were witnesses?\qt@no{(150)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxxxix{%
Lo! verily it is of their falsehood that they say:\qt@no{(151)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxl{%
God hath begotten. Verily they are the liars.\qt@no{(152)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxli{%
Hath He chosen daughters above sons?\qt@no{(153)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlii{%
What aileth you? How judge ye?\qt@no{(154)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxliii{%
Will ye not then be admonished?\qt@no{(155)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxliv{%
Or, is there for you a clear warranty\qt@no{(156)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlv{%
Then bring your book, if ye say sooth.\qt@no{(157)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlvi{%
And they have made a kinship between Him and the jinn a kinship whereas the jinn assuredly know that they are to be brought up\qt@no{(158)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlvii{%
Hallowed be Allah from that which they ascribe to Him.\qt@no{(159)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlviii{%
Except the bondmen of Allah sincere.\qt@no{(160)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxlix{%
Wherefore verily neither ye nor that which ye worship,\qt@no{(161)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcml{%
Can tempt anyone to rebel against Him.\qt@no{(162)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmli{%
Save him Who is to roast in the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(163)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlii{%
Of us there is none but hath a station assigned.\qt@no{(164)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmliii{%
And verily we! we are ranged in ranks.\qt@no{(165)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmliv{%
And verily we! we halloW.\qt@no{(166)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlv{%
And they surely were wont to say:\qt@no{(167)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlvi{%
Had we but an admonition as had the ancients.\qt@no{(168)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlvii{%
Surefy we would have been the bondmen of God sincere.\qt@no{(169)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlviii{%
Yet they disbelieve therein. Presently they shall come to know.\qt@no{(170)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlix{%
And assuredly Our word hath already gone forth Our bondmen, the sent ones:\qt@no{(171)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlx{%
That verily they! they shall be made triumphant.\qt@no{(172)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxi{%
And verily Our host! they are to be overcome.\qt@no{(173)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxii{%
So turn thou aside from them for a season.\qt@no{(174)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxiii{%
And see them thou; they themselves shall presently see.\qt@no{(175)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxiv{%
Our torment seek they to hasten on!\qt@no{(176)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxv{%
Then when it descendeth Unto them face to, face, a hapless morn that shall be for those who were Warned.\qt@no{(177)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxvi{%
And turn thou aside from them for a season.\qt@no{(178)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxvii{%
And see thou: they themselves shall presently see.\qt@no{(179)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxviii{%
Hallowed be thine Lord, the Lord of Majesty, from that which they ascribe!\qt@no{(180)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxix{%
And peace be Unto the sent ones.\qt@no{(181)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxx{%
And all praise Unto Allah the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(182)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxi{%
\basmalahen Sad. By the Qur'an full of admonition.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxii{%
Verily those who disbelieve are in vainglory and shism.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxiii{%
How many a generation have We destroyed afore them, and they cried when there was not time of fleeing.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxiv{%
And they marvel that there should come Unto them a warner from among themselves. And the infidels say: this is a magician and a liar!\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxv{%
Maketh he the gods One God? Verily that is a thing astounding!\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxvi{%
The chiefs among them departed saying: go, and persevere in your gods; verily this is a thing designed.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxvii{%
We heard not thereof in the later faith; this is naught but an invention.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxviii{%
Hath Unto him the admonition been sent down from amongst us! Yea! they are in doubt concerning My admonition. Yea! they have not yet tasted My torment.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxix{%
Or, are with them the treasures of the mercy of thy Lord, the Bestower?\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxx{%
Or, is theirs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and that which is in-between the twain? If so, let them ascend by steps.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxi{%
Here there is a host of the confederates only to be defeated.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxii{%
Before them there have belied the people of Nuh and the 'Aad, and Fir'awn the owner of the stakes.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxiii{%
And the Thamud, and the people of Lut, and the dwellers of the wood; these were the confederates.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxiv{%
There was not one but belied the apostles, wherefore justified was My wrath.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxv{%
And these wait but for one shout, wherefrom there will be no deferment.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxvi{%
And they say: our Lord! hasten our portion unto us before the Day of Reckoning\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxvii{%
Bear thou with that which they say, and remember Our bondman, Da-ud, endured with strength; verily he was oft-returning onto Us.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxviii{%
Verily We so subjected the mountains that they should hallow Us with him at nightfall and sunrise.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmlxxxix{%
And the birds also, gathering all oft-returning onto Him on his account.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxc{%
And We made his dominion strong and vouchsafed him wisdom and decisive speech.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxci{%
And hath the tidings of the contending parties reached thee, when they walled the apartment?\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcii{%
When they went in unto Da-ud, he was frightened at them. They said: fear not we are two contending parties; one of us hath oppressed the other, so judge between us with truth, and be not iniquitious, and guide us unto the even path.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxciii{%
Verily this my brother hath nine and ninety ewes while I have one ewe; and he saith: entrust it to me, and he hath prevailed upon me in speech.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxciv{%
Da-ud said: assuredly he hath wronged thee in demanding thine ewe in addition to his ewes, and verily many of the partners oppress each other save such as believe and work righteous works, and few are they. And Da-ud imagined that We had tried him; so he asked forgiveness of his Lord, and he fell down bowing and turned in penitence.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcv{%
So We forgave him that; and verily for him is an approach with us, and a happy retreat.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcvi{%
O Da-ud! verily We have appointed thee a vicegerent in the earth, so judge between mankind with truth, and follow not desire, lest it cause thee to err from the path of Allah. Verily those who err from the path of Allah - Unto them shall be a severe torment, for they forgat the Day of Reckoning.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcvii{%
And We have not created the heaven and the earth and whatsoever is in-between the twain in vain." That is the opinion of those who disbelieve. And woe Unto those who disbelieve the Fire."\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcviii{%
Shall We make those who believe and work righteous works I i ke Unto the corrupters in the earth; Or Shall We make the God-fearing like Unto the wicked!\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmcmxcix{%
This is a Book We have sent down Unto thee, blest, that they may ponder the revelations thereof, and that there may be admonished men of understanding.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmm{%
And We vouchsafed Unto Da-ud Sulaiman. How excellent a bondman! j Verily he was oft-returning.'\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmi{%
Recall what time there were presented Unto him, at eventide, s coursers swift-footed.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmii{%
He said: verily I have loved the love of earthly good above the remembrance of my Lord until the sun hath disappeared behind the veil.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmiii{%
Bring them back Unto me; and he set about slashing their legs and necks.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmiv{%
And assuredly We tried Sulaiman, and set upon his throne a mere body. Thereafter he was penitent.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmv{%
He said: my Lord! forgive me, and bestow on me a dominion which no one may obtain beside me: verily Thou! Thou art the Bestower.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmvi{%
Then We subjected to him the wind: it ran gently by his command withersoever he directed.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmvii{%
And We subjected to him the evil ones: every builder and diver.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmviii{%
And others bound in fetters.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmix{%
This is Our gift, SO bestow thou or withhold, without rendering an account.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmx{%
And verily for him is an approach with us, and a happy end.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxi{%
And remember thou Our bondman Ayyub, what time he cried Unto his Lord: verily the Satan hath touched me with affliction and suffering.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxii{%
Stamp the ground with thy foot. yonder is water to wash in, cool, and water to drink.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxiii{%
And We bestowed on him his household and along with them the like thereof, out of mercy from us, and a remembrance Unto men of understanding.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxiv{%
And take in thine hand a handful of twigs, and strike therewith, and break not thine oath. Verily We! We found him patient. How excellent a bondman! Verily he was oft-returning.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxv{%
And remember thou Our bond men, Ibrahim and Is-haq and Ya'qub. owners of might ana insight.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxvi{%
Verily We! We distinguished them with a distinct quality: the remembrance of the Abode.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxvii{%
And verily they are with us of the elect of the excellent ones\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxviii{%
And remember Isma'il and Al-Yas'a and Zul-kifl: all of the excellent ones.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxix{%
This is an admonition, and verily for the God-feoring is a happy retreat:\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxx{%
Gardens Everlasting, whereof the portals remain opened for them.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxi{%
Therein they will recline; therein they will call for plenteous fruit and drink.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxii{%
And with them will be virgins of refraining looks and of equal age.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxiii{%
This it is that ye are promised for the Day of Reckoning.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxiv{%
Verily this is Our provision: there will be no ceasing thereof.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxv{%
This: and verily for the exorbitant there shall be an evil retreat:\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxvi{%
Hell, wherein they roast: a wretched couch.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxvii{%
This - let them taste it: scalding water and corruption.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxviii{%
And other torments, like thereof, conjoined.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxix{%
This is a crowd rushing in along with you; no welcome for them; verily they are to roast in the Fire.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxx{%
They will say nay! it is ye, for whom there is no welcome: it is ye who have brought it upon us. Evil shall be the resting-place.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxi{%
They Will say: our Lord! whosever hath brought this upon us, - Unto him increase doubly the torment of the Fire.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxii{%
And they will Say: what aileth us that we behold not men whom we were wont to count among the evil ones?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxiii{%
Took we them so unjustly for a butt of mockery, or are they deluding our eyes?\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxiv{%
Verily this is the very truth: the wrangling of the fellows of the Fire!\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxv{%
Say thou: I am but warner, and there is no god but Allah, the One, the Subduer.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxvi{%
Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in- between the twain, the Mighty, the Forgiver.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxvii{%
Say thou: it is a tiding mighty.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxviii{%
Ye are therefrom averting.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxxxix{%
I had no knowledge of the chiefs on high when they disputed;\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxl{%
Naught is revealed Unto me except that I am a warner manifest.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxli{%
Recall what time thy Lord said Unto the angels: verily I am about to create a human being from clay;\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlii{%
Then when I have formed him and breathed into him of My spirit, fall down before him prostrate.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxliii{%
The angels prostrated themselves, all of them.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxliv{%
Not so lblis. He grew stiffnecked and became of the infidels.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlv{%
Allah said: O Iblis! what preventeth thee from prostrating thyself before that which have created with both my hands? Becomest thou stiff-necked, or art thou of the exalted ones?\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlvi{%
He said: I am better than he: me Thou hast created of fire, and him Thou hast created of clay.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlvii{%
Allah said: get thee forth therefrom verify thou art driven away.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlviii{%
And verily My curse shall be on thee till the Day of Requital,\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxlix{%
He said: my Lord! respite me till the Day whereon they are raised up.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmml{%
Allah said: verily, thou art of those respited.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmli{%
Until the Day of the time appointed.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlii{%
He said: by Thy majesty, then, I shall surely seduce them, all.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmliii{%
Save Thy bondmen among them Sincere.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmliv{%
Allah said: the truth is, and it is the truth that I speak, -\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlv{%
That I shall fill Hell with thee and such of them as shall follow thee, all together.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlvi{%
Say thou: ask of you for it no hire, nor am I of the affecters.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlvii{%
It is naught but an admonition Unto the worlds.\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlviii{%
And ye shall surely come to know the truth thereof after a season.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlix{%
\basmalahen The revelation of this Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlx{%
Verily We! We have sent down the Book Unto thee With truth: wherefore worship thou Allah, making exclusion for Him in religion.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxi{%
LO! for Allah is the religion exclusive. And those who take patrons beside Him, saying: We Worship them not save in order that they may bring us nigh Unto God in approach - -verily Allah will judge between them concerning that wherein they differ. Verily Allah guideth not him who is a liar and ingrate.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxii{%
Had Allah willed to take a son, He could have chosen whatsoever He pleased out of that which He hath created. Hallowed be He! He is Allah the One, the Subduer.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxiii{%
He hath created the heavens and the earth with truth. He rolleth the night around the day, and rolleth the day around the night, and He hath subjected the sun and the moon: each running on for a term appointed! Lo! He is the Mighty, the Forgiver.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxiv{%
He created you Of a Single soul, and made his spouse therefrom; and of the cattle He sent down Unto you eight pairs. He createth you in the bellies of your mothers, one creation after creation, in a threefold darkness. Such is Allah, your Lord. His is the dominion, there is no god but He. Whither then turn ye away?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxv{%
If ye disbelieve, then verily Allah is Independent of you. And He approveth not of infidelity in His bondmen. And if ye return thanks He approveth of that in you. No burdened soul shall bear another's burthen. Thereafter Unto your Lord is Your return; and He shall declare Unto you that which ye have been Working. Verily He is the Knower of that which is in the breasts.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxvi{%
And when some hurt toucheth man, he calleth upon his Lord, turning Unto Him in penitence; then when He bestoweth upon him a favour from Himself, he forgetteth that for which he called on Him afore, and setteth up peers Unto Allah that He may lead astray others from His way Say thou: enjoy thou life in thy infidelity for a while, verily thou art of the fellows of the Fire.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxvii{%
Is he who is devout, in the watches of the night prostrating himself and standing, bewaring of the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of his Lord to be dealt with like a wicked infidel? Say thou: shall they who know and those who know not be held equal? It is only men of understanding who receive admonition.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxviii{%
Say thou: O Mine bondmen who believe! fear your Lord. For those who do good in this world there is good: and Allah's earth is spacious. Verily the patient shall be paid in full their hire without reckoning.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxix{%
Say thou: verily I am commanded to worship Allah, making for Him religion exclusive.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxx{%
And I am commanded this, in order I may be the first Of those who submit.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxi{%
Say thou: verily fear, if I disobeyed my Lord, torment of a Day mighty.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxii{%
Say thou: it is Allah I worship, making for Him my religion exclusive\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxiii{%
So worship whatsoever ye will, besidev him. Say thou: verily the losers are those who shall have lost themselves and their household" on the Day of judgment LO! that will be a loss manifest.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxiv{%
For them! above them shall be coverings of Fire and beneath them coverings. Therewith Allah affrighteth His bondmen. O My bondmen! wherefore fear Me.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxv{%
And those who avoid the devils lest they should worship them and turn Unto Allah in penitence, for them are glad tidings. Wherefore give thou glad tidings Unto My bondmen,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxvi{%
Who hearken Unto the word and follow that which is the exceLlent there of. These are they whom Allah hath guided, and those are men of understanding.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxvii{%
Is he then on whom is justified the decree of torment - wilt thou rescue him who is in the Fire?\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxviii{%
But those whofear their Lord, for them are lofty chambers with lofty chambers above them, built whereunder rivers flow: the promise of Allah, and Allah faileth not the appointment.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxix{%
Beholdest thou not that Allah sendeth down water from the heaven, and causeth it to enter springs in the earth, and thereafter produceth thereby corn various coloured. Thereafter it wirhereth, and thou beholdest it turn yellow; then He maketh it chaff. Verily herein is an admonition for men of understanding.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxx{%
Shall he then whose breast Allah hath expanded for Islam, so that he followeth a light from his Lord be as he whose heart is hardened? Then woe Unto those whose hearts are hardened against remembrance of Allah. They are in an error manifest.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxi{%
Allah hath revealed the most excellent discourse, a Book consimilar oft-repeated, whereat trembleth the skins of these who fear their Lord; then their skins and their hearts soften at the remembrance of Allah. This is Allah's guidance, wherewith He guideth whomsoever He will. And whomsoever Allah sendeth astray, for him there is no guide.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxii{%
Is he, then, who will shield himself with his face from the evil of torment on the Day of Resurrection be as he who is secure therefrom And it shall be said Unto the wrong-doers: taste ye that which ye have been earning.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxiii{%
Those before them belied, wherefore the torment came on them whence they knew not.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxiv{%
So Allah made them taste humiliation in the life of the world. And surely the torment of the Hereafter is greater - if they but know!\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxv{%
And assuredly We have propounded for mankind in this Qur'an all kinds of similitudes, that haply they may be admonished.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxvi{%
An Arabic Qur'an, wherein there is no crookedness, that haply they may fear.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxvii{%
Allah propoundeth a similitude: man having several partners,"quarelling, and a man wholly belonging to one man. Are the two equal in likeness? All praise Unto Allah. But most of them know not.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxviii{%
Verily thou art mortal, and verily they are mortals.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmlxxxix{%
Then verily on the Day of Resurrection, before your Lord ye shall contend.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxc{%
And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who fabricateth a lie against Allah, and belieth the truth when it cometh Unto him? Will not in Hell be an abode for the infidels?\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxci{%
And whosoever bringeth the truth, and whosoever giveth credence thereto - these! they are the God-fearing.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcii{%
Theirs will be whatsoever they will desire with their Lord: that is the hire of the well-doers.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxciii{%
That through this Promise Allah may expiate from them the worst of that which they may have worked, and may recompense them their hire for the best of that which they have been working.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxciv{%
Is not Allah sufficient for His bondman? Yet they would frighten thee with those beside Him? And whomsoever Allah sendeth astray, for him there shall be no guide.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcv{%
And whomsoever Allah guideth, for him there shall be no misleader. Is not Allah Mighty, and Lord of Retribution?\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcvi{%
And wert thou to ask them: who hath created the heavens and the earth? they will surely say: Allah. Say thou: bethink ye then that those whom ye call upon beside Allah, - could they if Allah intended some hurt for me, remove His hurt? or if He intended some mercy for me, could they withhold His mercy? Say thou: enough for me is Allah; in Him the trusting put their trust.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcvii{%
Say thou: my nation! work according to your condition; I am going to work in my way; presently ye shall come to know.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcviii{%
On whom cometh a torment humiliating him, and on whom alighteth a torment lasting.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmxcix{%
Verily We! We have sent down Unto thee the Book for mankind? with truth. Then whosoever receiveth guidance, it is for his soul and whosoever strayeth, strayeth only to its hurt; and thou art not over them a trustee.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmc{%
Allah it is who taketh away souls at the time of their death, and those which die not in their sleep: then He withhold those on which He hath decreed death, and sendeth back the rest for an appointed term. Verily herein are signs for a people who ponder.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmci{%
Have they taken others for intercessors beside Allah! Say thou: What! even though they own not aught and understand not?\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcii{%
Say thou: Allah's is intercession altogether. His is the dominion of the heavens and the earth; then Unto Him shall ye be returned.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmciii{%
And when Allah alone is mentioned, then shrink with eversion the hearts of those who believe not in the Hereafter, and when those beside Him are mentioned, lo! they rejoice.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmciv{%
Say thou: O Allah! Creator of the heavens and the earth! Knower of the hidden and the open! Thou shalt judge between Thy bondmen concerning that wherein they have been differing.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcv{%
And were those who did wrong to own all that is in the earth, and there with as much again, they shall surely seek to ransom themselves therewith from the evil of the torment on the Day of Judgment; and there shall appear Unto them from Allah that whereon they had not been reckoning,\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcvi{%
And there shall appear Unto them the evils that they earned, and there shall surround them that whereat they had been mocking.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcvii{%
When hurt toucheth a man he calleth on us, and thereafter, when We have changed it Unto a favour from Us, he saith: have been given itso only by force of my knowledge. Aye! it is a trial, but most of them know not.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcviii{%
Surely those who were before them said it, yet there availed them not that which they had been earning.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcix{%
And there befell them the evils of that which they had earned. And of these they who go wrong-anon will befall them the evils of that which they earn; nor can they frustrate.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcx{%
Know they not that Allahs expandeth provision for whomsoever He will, and stinteth it for whomsoever He will! Verily herein are signs for a people who believe.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxi{%
Say thou: my bondmen who have committed extravagance against themselves despair not of the mercy of Allah; verily Allah will forgive the sins altogether. Verily He! He is the Forgiving, the Merciful.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxii{%
And turn penitently Unto your Lord and submit Unto Him ere there cometh Unto you the torment, and then ye shall not be succoured.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxiii{%
And follow the best of that which hath been sent down Unto you from your Lord there cometh on you torment of a sudden, while ye perceive not.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxiv{%
Lest a soul should say: Alas! for that I have been remiss in respect of Allah, and I was but of the scoffers!\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxv{%
Or, lest it should say: had Allah but guided me, I should surely have been of the God-fearing!\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxvi{%
Or lest it should say, when it will behold the torment: were there for me a return I would be of the well-doers.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxvii{%
Yea! surely there came Unto thee My revelations, but thou beliedest them and wast stiff-necked and wast of the infidels.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxviii{%
And on the Day of Judgment thou Shalt see those who lied against Allah - their faces blackened. Is not in Hell the abode of the stiff-necked?\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxix{%
And Allah will deliver those who feared Him to their place of safety. Evil will not touch them, nor will they grieve.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxx{%
Allah is the Creator everything, And He is over everything a Trustee.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxi{%
His are the keys of the heavens and the earth and those who disbelieve in the revelations of Allah-those! they are the losers.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxii{%
Say thou: is it other than Allah that ye command me to worship! O ye pagans\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxiii{%
And assuredly it hath been revealed Unto thee and Unto those before thee: if thou associatest surely of non-effect shall be made thy work, and thou shalt surely be of the losers.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxiv{%
Aye! Allah must thou worship, and be among the thankful.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxv{%
And they estimated not Allah with an estimation due Unto Him whereas the whole earth shall be His handful on the Day of Judgment, and the heavens shall be rolled in His right hand. Hallowed be He and Exalted above that which they associate.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxvi{%
And the trumpet will be blown, when whosoever are in the heavens and whosoever are on the earth will swoon away, save him whomsoever Allah willeth. Then it shall be blown again, and lo! They will be standing, looking on.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxvii{%
And the earth will gleam with the light of its Lord, and the Record shall be set up, and the prophets and the witnesses will be brought and judgment will be given between them with truth, and they will not be wronged.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxviii{%
And each soul will be paid in full that which it hath worked; and He is the Best Knower of which they do.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxix{%
And those who disbelieve will be driven onto Hell in troops till, when they arrive thereto, the portals thereof will be opened, and the keepers thereof will say Unto them: came there not Unto you apostles from amongst you, rehearsing Unto you the revelations of you Lord and warning you of the meeting of this your Day? They shall say: Yea, but the word of torment hath been justified on the Infidels.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxx{%
It will be said: enter the portals Of Hell to be abiders therein. How ill, then, is the abode of the stiff-necked!\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxi{%
And those who feared their Lord Will be driven Unto the Garden in troops till, when they arrive thereto, and the portals thereof will be opened, the keepers thereof Will say Unto them: Peace be Unto you! excellent are ye! enter it as abiders.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxii{%
And they Will say: all praise Unto Allah, who hath fulfilled His promise Unto us and made us inherit this land, so that we may dwell in the Garden whereever we will! Excellent then is the hire of the workers!\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxiii{%
And thou wilt see the angels thronging round the Throne, hallowing the praise of their Lord. And judgment shall be given between them with truth: and it will be said: all praise Unto Allah, the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxiv{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxv{%
The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Knower. Forgiver of sin, and Accepter of repentance, severe in chastisement, Lord of power. There is no god but He; Unto Him is the journeying.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxvi{%
Forgiver of sin, and Acceptor of repentance severe in chastisement, Lord of Power. There is no god but He; unto Him is the journeying.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxvii{%
None dispute concerning the revelations of Allah save those who disbelieve, so let not beguile thee their going about in the cities.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxviii{%
The people of Nuh and the confederates after them belied their apostles before these, and each disbelieving community advanced toward their apostle that they may lay hold of him and disputed with vain speech that they may confute the truth thereby. Wherefore I laid hold of them; and how terrible was My chastisement!\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxxxix{%
And thus hath the Word of thy Lord been justified on those who disbelieve: that they shall be the fellows of the Fire.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxl{%
Those who bear the Throne and those who are round about it, hallow the praise of their Lord and believe in Him and ask forgiveness for those who believe, saying: our Lord! Thou comprehendest everything in mercy and knowledge, wherefore forgive these who repent and follow Thine path, and protect them from the torment of the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxli{%
Our Lord! make them enter the Everlasting Gardens Which Thou hast promised them, and also such of their fathers and their spouses and their offspring as verify Thou: Thou art the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlii{%
And protect them from evils. And whosoever Thou shalt protect from evils on that Day, him Thou hast of a surety taken into mercy and that: it is an achievement mighty.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxliii{%
Verily those who disbelieve-they will be cried Unto: surely Allah's abhorrence was greater than Is your abhorrence toward yourselves when ye were called Unto the belief, and ye disbelieved.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxliv{%
They will say: our Lord! Thou hast made us die twice, and Thou hast made us live twice now We confess our sins: there no getting out any way?\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlv{%
That is because when Allah alone was called upon ye disbelieved, and when some one was associated with Him ye believed. So the judgment is of Allah, the Exalted, the Great.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlvi{%
He it is who sheweth you His signs and sendeth down for you from the heaven provision. And none receiveth admonition save him who turneth in penitence.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlvii{%
Wherefore call Unto Allah, making religion for Him pure, though the infidels be averse.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlviii{%
He is Lofty in degrees, Lord of the Throne. He casteth the spirit of His command upon whomsoever He will of His bondmen, that he may warn people of the Day of Meeting.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxlix{%
The Day whereon they will appear: naught of them will be concealed from Allah, Whose is the dominion to-day? It is of Allah, the One, the Subduer.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcl{%
To-day each soul will be recompensed for that which it hath earned; no wrong-doing to-day; verily Allah is Swift at reckoning.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcli{%
Wherefore warn them thou of the Day of portending, whereon the hearts will be in the throats, choking: then will be for the wrong- doers no ardent friend nor an intercessor to be given heed to.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclii{%
He knoweth the fraudulence of the eyes, and that which the breasts conceal.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcliii{%
Allah decreeth with truth, while those whom they call upon beside Him cannot decree aught; verily Allah! He is the Hearer, the Beholder!\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcliv{%
Have they not travelled about in the land so that they may behold of what wise hath been the end of those who were before them? They were mightier than these in strength and in the traces in the land. Yet Allah laid hold of them for their sins, and from Allah they had none as protector.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclv{%
That was because their apostles were wont to bring them evidence, but they disbelieved; wherefore Allah laid hold of them. Verily He is strong, severe in chastisement.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclvi{%
And assuredly We sent Musa with Our signs and a manifest authority.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclvii{%
Unto Fir'awn and Haman and Qur'an, but they said: a magician, a liar.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclviii{%
And when he came to them with the truth from before Us, they said: slay the sons of those who have believed with him, and let their women live. And the plot of the infidels was naught but vain.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclix{%
And Fir'awn said: let me alone, that may slay Musa, and let him call upon his Lord. Verily fear that he may change your religion or that he may cause to appear in the land corruption.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclx{%
And Musa said: verily I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every stiff-necked person who believeth not in a Day of Reckoning.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxi{%
And a believing man of Fir'awn 's household, hiding his belief, said: would ye slay a man because he saith: my Lord is God, and hath come upto you with evidences from your Lord? If he is a liar, then upon him will be his lie, and if he is a truth-teller, then there will befall you some of that wherewith he threateneth you; verily God guideth not one who is an extravagant and a liar.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxii{%
O My people! yours is the the dominion to-day: ye being overcomers in the land; but who will succour us aginst the scourge of God if it cometh Unto us! Fir'awn said: I shew you only that which see, and I guide you but to the path of rectitude.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxiii{%
And he who believed said: O my people. verily I fear for you a fate like the day of the confederates.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxiv{%
Like the wont of the people of Nuh and A'ad and Thamud and those after them, and God intendeth not any wrong Unto His bondmen.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxv{%
And, O my people! verily fear for you a Day of Mutual Calling.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxvi{%
A Day whereon ye shall turn away retreating: for you there will be no protector from God; and whomsoever God sendeth astray for him there is no guide.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxvii{%
And assuredly there came Unto you Yusuf aforetime with evidences, yet ye ceased not to be in doubt concerning that which he brought Unto you, until when he died, ye said: God shall by no means raise an apostle after him. Thus Allah keepeth astray one who is extravagant and a doubter.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxviii{%
Those who wrangle concerning the signs of Allah without any authority that hath come Unto them. It is greatly abhorrent Unto Allah and Unto those who believe. Thus Allah sealeth up the heart of any stiff-necked, high-handed, person.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxix{%
And Fir'awn said: O Haman! build for me a tower that haply I may reach the ways of access\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxx{%
The way of access to the heavens so that may be apprised of the God of Musa, and verily I believe him to be a liar. And thus fair- seeming was made Unto FIr'awn the evil of his work, and he was hindered from the path. And the plot of Fir'awn ended only in ruin.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxi{%
And he who believed said: O my people! follow me, I shall guide you to the path of rectitude,\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxii{%
O My people! this life of the world Is but a possi enjoyment, and verily the Hereafter! that is the Abode of rest.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxiii{%
Whosoever worketh an evil, he shallnotberequited except the like thereof; and whosoever, male or female, worketh righteously, and is a believer-they will enter the Garden wherein they will be pro vided for without measure.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxiv{%
And, O my people! what aileth me that call you Unto deliverance, while ye call me Unto the Fire!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxv{%
Ye call me for this, that should O blaspheme against God and associate with Him that whereof have no knowledge, call you onto the Mighty, the\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxvi{%
Without doubt ye only call me Unto that which is not to be invoked in the world nor in the Hereafter; and verily our return shall be Unto God, and the extravagant! they shall be fellows of the Fire.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxvii{%
And anon ye shall remember that which am telling you. Confide my affair Unto God; verily God is the Beholder of His bondmen.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxviii{%
Wherefore Allah protected him from ills which they plotted, and there surrounded the family of Fir'awn the evil of torment.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxix{%
The Fire! They are exposed thereto morning and evening. And on the Day whereon the Hour will uprise, it will be said: cause the family of Fir'awn to enter the most grievous torment.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxx{%
And consider what time they will wrangle together in the Fire, and the oppressed will say Unto those who were stiff-necked: verily we have been Unto you a following, are ye going to avail us against a portion of the Fire?\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxi{%
Those who were stiff-necked will say: verily we are all in it; verily Allah hath judged between His bondmen.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxii{%
And those in the Fire will say Unto the keepers of Hell: supplicate your Lord that He may lighten for us a day of the torment.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxiii{%
They will say: came there not your apostles Unto you with evidences? They will say: Yea? They will say: supplicate then yourselves. And supplication of the infidels will be but in wandering.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxiv{%
Verily We! We shall surely succour Our apostles and those who believe, both in the life of the world and on a Day whereon the witnesses will stand forth.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxv{%
A Day whereon their excuse will not Profit the wrong- doers; and theirs Will be the curse and theirs the evil Abode.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxvi{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed Unto Musa the guidance, and We caused the Children of Isra'il to inherit the Book.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxvii{%
A guidance and an admonition Unto the men of understanding,\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxviii{%
Wherefore persevere thou. Verily the Promise of Allah is true and ask forgiveness for thy fault, and hallow the praise of thy Lord in the evening and in the morning.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmclxxxix{%
Verily those who wrangle concerning the revelations of Allah without an authority having come Unto them there is aught in their breasts save greatness Which they shall not reach. Seek refuge thou then in Allah verily He! He is the Hearer, the Beholder.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxc{%
The creation of the heavens and the earth is indeed greater than the creation of mankind; but most of man kind know not.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxci{%
Not equal are the blind and the seeing; nor those who believed and Work righteous works and the evil-doer. Little are ye admonished!\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcii{%
Verily the Hour is coming: there is no doubt thereof; yet most of mankind believe not.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxciii{%
And your Lord hath said: call Unto Me, and I shall answer your prayer. Verily those who are stiff-necked against My worship, anon they will enter Hell abject.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxciv{%
Allah it is who hath appointed for you the night that ye may repose therein, and day enlightening. Verily Allah is the Lord of Grace for mankind; bur most of mankind return not thanks.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcv{%
Such is Allah. your Lord, the Creator of everything there is no God but He. Wither then are ye straying away?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcvi{%
In this wise have those strayed who the signs of Allah were away want to gainsay.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcvii{%
Allah it is Who hath appointed for you the earth for a resting-place and the heaven for a structure, and fashioned you and fashioned you well, and provided you with goodly things. Such is Allah, your Lord. So blessed be Allah, the Lord of the worlds!\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcviii{%
He is the Living: there is no god but He so call upon Him, making religion pure for Him. All praise Unto Allah, the Lord of the worlds!\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcxcix{%
Say thou: verily I am forbidden that should worship these whom ye call upon beside Allah when evidences have come Unto me from my Lord, and I am commanded that I should submit to the Lord of the Worlds.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcc{%
He it is Who created you of dust, and thereafter of a drop, and thereafter of a clot, and thereafter He bringeth you forth as an infant, and thereafter He ordaineth that ye attain your full strength and thereafter that ye become old men-though some of you die before-and that ye attain the appointed term, and that haply ye may reflect.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcci{%
He it is Who causeth life and death. Then whensoever He decreeth an affair He only saith Unto it: be, and it becometh.\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccii{%
Observest thou not those who wrangle concerning the revelations of Allah: whither are they turning away?\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcciii{%
Those who belie the Book and that message wherewith We sent Our apostles, presently they shall come to know.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcciv{%
When shackles will be on their necks and also chains; they will be dragged.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccv{%
Into the balling water; then into the Fire they will be stocked.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccvi{%
Then it will be said Unto them: where are those whom ye have been associating\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccvii{%
Beside Allah? They will say: they have failed us: aye! we have not been calling upon aught afore. Thus doth Allah lead the infidels astray.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccviii{%
That is because ye had been exulting in the earth without right, and because ye had been strutting.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccix{%
Enter ye the gates of Hell as abiders therein. Hapless is the abode of the stiff-necked.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccx{%
Wherefore persevere thou; verily the promise of Allah is true; then whether We let thee see a part of that wherewith We have promised them, or whether We cause thee to die, Unto us they all will be caused to retvtn.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxi{%
Assuredly We have sent apostlesy before thee, of them are these whose store We have recounted Unto thee and these whose story We have net recounted Unto thee. And it was not possible for anv apostle that he should bring a sign san by Allah's leave. So when the commade of Allah cometh, judgment will be given with truth, and then will lose the followers of falsehood.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxii{%
Allah it is Who hath appointed for you cattle, that ye may ride on some of them, and eat of others\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxiii{%
And there are other benefits in them for you and that ye may attain thereby to any need that is in Your breasts and upon them and upon ships ye are borne.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxiv{%
And He sheweth you His signs. Which, then, of the signs of Allah shall ya deny?\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxv{%
Have they not travelled in the earth so that they may behold what wise hath been the end of those before them. They were more numerous than these, and mightier in strength and the traces in the land. But naught availed them of that which they had been earning.\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxvi{%
And when their apostles came Unto them with evidences, they exulted in the knowledge which was with them, and there surrounded them that which they had been mocking.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxvii{%
Then when they behold Our prowess, they said: we believe in Allah alone, and we disbelieve in that which with Him we have been associating.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxviii{%
But their belief profited them naught when they saw our prowess. This hath been Allah's dispensation that hath- been in regard to His bondmen. And then there were lost the infidels.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxix{%
\basmalahen Ha-Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxx{%
This is a revelation from the Compassionate, the Merciful -\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxi{%
A Book whereof the verses are detailed: an Arabic Qur'an: for a people who know:\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxii{%
A bearer of glad tidings and a warner. Yet most of them turn aside, so that they hearken not.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxiii{%
And they say: our hearts are under veils from that whereUnto thou callest us, and in our ears there is heaviness, and betwixt us and thee there is a curtain; work thou then, verily we are Workers.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxiv{%
Say thou: I am only a human being like Unto you: only it is revealed Unto me that your God is but One God, wherefore take the straight path Unto Him and seek forgiveness of Him. And woe be Unto the associators.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxv{%
Who give not the poor-rate; and they! in the Hereafter, they are disbelievers.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxvi{%
Verily those who believe and work righteous works - Unto them shall be a hire unceasing.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxvii{%
Say thou: are ye indeed those who disbelieve in Him who hath created the earth in two days, and set up Unto Him peers? That is the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxviii{%
And He placed therein mountains firmly rooted rising above it, and blessed it, and ordained therein the sustenance thereof, all this in four days: comglete: this for the inquirers.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxix{%
Thereafter turned He to the heaven and it was as smoke, and said Unto it and Unto the earth: come ye twain, willingly or loth. They said: we come willingly.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxx{%
Then He decreed them as seven heavens in two days, and revealed Unto each heaven the command thereof; and We bedecked the nether heaven with lamps and placed therein a guard. That is the ordinance of the Mighty, the Knower.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxi{%
Then if they Still turn away, say thou; I warn you of a calamity like the calamity of the 'Aad and Thamud.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxii{%
Recall what time the apostles came Unto them from before them and behind them, saying: worship none save Allah. They said: had our Lord listed, He surely would have sent down angels, so verily in that wherewith ye have been sent we are disbelievers altogether.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxiii{%
As for the tribe of 'Aad - they grew stiff-necked on the earth without justification, and said: who is mightier than we in strength? Saw they not that Allah who created them,-He was Mightier than they in strength? And Our signs they were wont to gainsay.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxiv{%
Wherefore We sent upon them a raging wind in days inauspicious, that We might make them taste the torment of humiliation in the life of the world; and surely the torment of the Hereafter will be more humiliating, nor will they be succoured.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxv{%
And as for the tribe of the Thamud We guided them but they preferred blindness to the guidance, wherefore the bolt of the torment of abjection laid hold of them because of that which they had been earning.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxvi{%
And We delivered those who believed and had been fearing.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxvii{%
And warn them of the Day whereon the enemies of Allah will be gathered Unto the Fire; and they will be set in bands.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxviii{%
Until when they come to it, their ears and their sights and their skins will bear witness against them of that which they had been working.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxxxix{%
And they will say Unto their skins: wherefore bear ye witness against us They will say: Allah hath caused us to speak, Who causeth everything to speak, and Who created you the first time and Unto whom ye are now caused to return.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxl{%
Ye have not been taking cover against yourselves lest your ears and your eyes and your skins should bear witness against you, but ye imagined that Allah not much knew of that which ye were working.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxli{%
That thought of yours which ye formed concerning Your Lord, hath ruined you, and ye have become of the losers.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlii{%
Then if they are patient, the Fire is their home, and if they seek to please Allah, they will not be of those who are allowed to please Allah.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxliii{%
And We have assigned Unto them some companions who made fairseeming Unto them that which was before them and that which was behind them justified upon them was the Word Pronounced on the communities of the jinn and mankind who passed away before them; verily they were the losers.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxliv{%
And those who disbelieve say: hearken not Unto this Qur'an and babble therein, haply ye may overcome.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlv{%
Wherefore We will surely cause those who disbelieve to taste a severe tor ment, and We will surely requite them the worst of that which they have been working.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlvi{%
That is the meed of the enemies of Allah: the Fire. Therein is their home of Abidence: a meed forasmuch as Our revelations they were wont to gainsay.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlvii{%
And those who disbelieve will say: our Lord! show us those, of the jinn and mankind, who led us astray and we will place them underneath our feet that they may be of the nithermost.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlviii{%
Verily those who say: our Lord is Allah, and have thereafter stood fast by it,- upon them there shall come down the angels: fear not, nor grieve, and rejoice in the tidings of the Garden which ye have been promised.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxlix{%
We are your friends in the life of the world and in the Hereafter; there in yours will be whatsoever your souls desire, and therein yours shall be whatsoever ye call for.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccl{%
And entertainment from the Forgiving, the Merciful.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccli{%
And who is better in speech than he who summoneth Unto Allah, and worketh righteously, and saith: verily I am one of the Muslims.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclii{%
Nor can good and evil be equal. Repel thou evil with that which is goodly then behold he between whom and thee there was enmity, will be as though he was a warm friend.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccliii{%
And none attaineth that except those who are patient; and none attaineth that except the owner of mighty good fortune,\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccliv{%
And if there inciteth thee an incitement from the Satan then seek refuge in Allah. Verily He! He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclv{%
And of His signs are the night and the day and the sun and the moon. So prostrate not yourselves Unto the sun nor the moon. but prostrate yourselves Unto Allah who hath created them, if it is He alone whom ye are worshipping.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclvi{%
And if they grow stiff-necked, then verily those who are with thy Lord, hallow Him night and day, and they weary not.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclvii{%
And of His signs is that thou beholdest the earth lowly, and when We send down thereon water, it stirreth to life and groweth. Verily He who quickeneth is the Quickener of the dead. Verily He is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclviii{%
Verily those who blaspheme Our revelations are not hid from Us. Is he then who will be cast into the Fire better or he who cometh secure on the Day of Resurrection? Work whatsoever ye will; Verily He is of that which ye work the Beholder.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclix{%
Verily those who disbelieve in the Admonition when it cometh Unto them are themselves to blame. Verily it is a Book mighty.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclx{%
Falsehood cannot come at it from before it or behind it It, a revelation from One Wise and Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxi{%
Naught is said Unto thee save that which was said Unto the apostles afore thee. Verily thy Lord is Owner of forgiveness and Owner of afflictive chastisement.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxii{%
And had We made it a recital in a foreign tongue, they would have surely said: wherefore are the verses thereof not detailed? A foreign tongue and an Arab! Say thou: Unto those who have believed it is a guidance and a healing: and those who believe not, - in their ears there is a heaviness, and Unto them it is blindness. These are they who are cried Unto from a place far-off.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxiii{%
And assuredly We vouchsafed Unto Musa the Book, and difference arose concerning it; and had not a word gone forth from thy Lord, the affair would have been decreed between them. And verily they are in regard thereto in doubt and dubitating.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxiv{%
Whosoever worketh righteously it is for his soul, and whosoever worketh evil it is against it. And thine Lord is not an oppressor Unto His bondmen.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxv{%
Unto Himl is remitted the knowledge of the Hour. And not a fruit cometh forth from the knops thereof; neither doth a female bear or bring forth but with His knowledge. And on the Day whereon He will call Unto them: where are my associates. they will say: we protet Unto Thee, none of us is a witness thereof.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxvi{%
And there will fail them those whom they had been calling upon aforetime, and they will perceive that there is for them no shelter.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxvii{%
Man is not wearied of praying for worldly good, and if there tcucheth him an evil, he is despondent, despairing.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxviii{%
And, surely, if We cause him to taste mercy from Us after affliction hath touched him, he is sure to say: this is my own, and I deem not that the Hour will everarise, and were I to be brought back to my Lord, verily there will be for me, with Him, an excellent condition. But We shall surely declare Unto those who disbelieve that which they have worked, and We shall surely make them taste a torment rough..\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxix{%
And when We shew favour Unto man, he turneth aside and withdraweth on his side, and when evil toucheth him, then he is full of prolonged prayer.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxx{%
Say thou: bethink ye! if it is really from Allah and then ye disbelieve therein, then who is further astray than one who is in schism far-off?\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxi{%
Anon We shall shew them Our signs in the regions and in their ownselves until it becometh manifest Unto them that it is the truth. Sufficeth it not in regard to thy Lord, that He is over everything Witness?\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxii{%
Lo! they are in doubt concerning the meeting with their Lord: Lo! He Is of everything the Encompasser!\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxiii{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxiv{%
Ain. Sin. Qaf.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxv{%
In this wise revealeth Unto thee and Unto those before thee, Allah the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxvi{%
His is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, and He is the Exalted, the Grand.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxvii{%
Well-nigh the heavens might be rent in sunder from above them. And the angels hallow the praise of their lord and ask forgiveness for these on the earth. Lo! Verily Allah! He is the Forgiver, the Merciful!\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxviii{%
And those who take Patrons beside Him, Allah is Warden over them, and thou art not over them a trustee.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxix{%
And thus We have revealed Unto thee a Qur'an in Arabic, that thou mayest warn the mother of towns and those around it, and that thou mayest warn them of a Day of Assembling whereof there is no doubt. A party will be in the Garden, and a party in the Blaze.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxx{%
And had Allah willed, He would have made them one community; but He causeth whomsoever He will to enter into His mercy. And the wrong doers! for them there shall be no patron or helper.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxi{%
Have they taken patrons besides Him! But Allah! He is the Patron, HE quickeneth the dead, and He is over every-thing Potent.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxii{%
And whatsoever it be wherein ye differ the decision thereof is with Allah; such is Allah, my Lord: in Him put my trust and Unto Him I turn in penitenance.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxiii{%
The Creator of the heavens and the earth: He hath made for you mates of yourselves, and of the cattle also mates, whereby He diffuseth you. Not like Unto Him is aught, and He is the Hearer, the Beholder!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxiv{%
His are the keys of the heavens and the earth. He expandeth provision for whomsoever He will and stinteth. Verily; He is of everything the Knower.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxv{%
He hath instituted for you in religion that which He had enjoined upon Nuh, and which We have revealed Unto thee, and which We had enjoined upon Ibrahim and Musa and Isa, saying: establish the religion, and be not divided therein. Grievous Unto the associaters is that Unto which thou callest them. Allah chooseth for Himself whomsoever He will and guideth Unto Himself whomsoever turneth in penitence.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxvi{%
And they divided not until after knowledge had come to them, through spite between themselves; And had not a word gone forth from thy Lord for an appointed term, the affair would surely have been judged between them. And verily those who have been made inheritors of the Book after them are in doubt thereof dubitating.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxvii{%
Wherefore Unto that summon thou, and be steadfast as thou hast been commanded, and follow not their desires. And say thou: I believe in whatsoever Allah hath sent down of the Book, and I am commanded that I should do justice between you; Allah is our Lord and your Lord; Unto us our works, and Unto you your works; let there be no contention between us and you; Allah will assemble us, and Unto Him is the return.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxviii{%
And those who contend respecting the religion of Allah after it hath been acknowledged, their contention is void in the sight of their Lord, and upon them shall befall wrath, and theirs shall be a severe torment.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcclxxxix{%
Allah it is Who hath sent down the Book with the truth and the balance. And what shall make thee know the Hour may haply be nigh.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxc{%
Only those who believe not therein seek to hasten it, and those who believe are fearful thereof and know that it is the truth. Lo! verily these who debate concerning the Hour are in error far-off.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxci{%
Allah is Gentle Unto His bondmen: He provideth for whomsoever He will, and He is the Strong, the Mighty.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcii{%
Whosoever seeketh the tillage of the Hereafter Unto him We shall give increase in his tillage; and whosoever seeketh the tillage of the world We shall give him somewhat thereof, and in the Hereafter his shall be no portion.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxciii{%
Have they associate-gods who have instituted for them a religion which Allah hath not allowed? And had there net been a decisive Word, the affair would have been judged between them. And verily the wrong-doers? theirs shall be a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxciv{%
Thou shalt see the wrong-doers fearful on account of that which they have earned, and it is sure to befall them. And those who believe and work righteous works will be in meadows of the Gardens theirs will be whatsoever they list, in the presence of their Lord. That! that is the supreme grace.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcv{%
That is that whereof Allah giveth the glad tidings Unto His bondmen who believe and work righteous works, Say thou: I ask of you no hire therefor save affection in respect of kinship. And whoso ever earneth a good deed We shall increase Unto him good in respect thereof; verily Allah is Forgiving, Appreciative.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcvi{%
Say they: he hath fabricated a lie concerning God! Now, if Allah willed, He would seal thine heart. And Allah abolisheth falsehood and establisheth truth by His words; verily He is the Knower of that which is in the breasts.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcvii{%
And He it is Who accepteth repentances from His bondmen, and pardoneth the evil deeds and knoweth that which ye do.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcviii{%
And He answereth those who believe and work righteous works and increaseth Unto them of His grace. And the infidels! theirs shall be a severe torment.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccxcix{%
And had Allah expanded the provision for His bondmen they surely would have rebelled in the earth, but He sendeth down by measure as He willeth; verily He is, in respect of His bondmen. Aware and Beholder.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccc{%
And He it is Who sendeth down the rain after men have despaired, and spreadeth abroad His mercy. And He is the Patron of all, the Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccci{%
And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth and of the moving creatures which He hath dispersed in the twain. And He is for their assembling whensoever He will Potent.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccii{%
And whatsoever of affliction befalleth you is owing to that which your hands have earned; and He pardoneth much.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccciii{%
And ye cannot frustrate His Punishment in the earth; and there is for you beside Allah neither protector nor helper.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccciv{%
And of His signs are the ships in the sea like landmarks.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccv{%
If He willeth He causeth the wind to cease so that they keep still on the back thereof; verily therein are signs for every patient, grateful person.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccvi{%
Or He may destroy them because of that which they have earned, and He may pardon many of them.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccvii{%
And those who dispute in respect of Our revelations may know that for them there is a place of shelter.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccviii{%
So whatsoever things are vouchsafed Unto you are but a Passing enjoyment for the life of the world, and that which is with Allah, better and more lasting, is for those who believe and in their Lord put their trust.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccix{%
And those who avoid heinous sins and indecencies, and when they are wroth forgive.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccx{%
And those who answer the call of their Lord and establish prayer and whose affair being matter of counsel among themselves, and who of that wherewith We have provided them expend.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxi{%
And those who, when they are oppressed vindicate themselves.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxii{%
The meed of an ill-deed is an ill the like thereUnto; but whosoever pardoneth and amendeth, his hire is on Allah; verily He approveth not the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxiii{%
And whosoever vindicateth him self after wrong done him these! against them there is no way of blame.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxiv{%
The way of blame is only against those who wrong mankind, and rebel in the earth without justice; these! for them is a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxv{%
And whosoever forbeareth and forgiveth -that verily is of the firmness of affairs.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxvi{%
And whomsoever Allah will send astray, for him there will be no protecting friend to take His place. And thou wilt behold the wrong- doers when they behold the torment saying: is there Unto return any way?\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxvii{%
And thou wilt behold them set up before it, downcast with ingominy ond looking with stealthy glance. And those who believe will say: verily the losers are they who have lost themselves and their housefolk on the Day of Resurrection. Lo! verily the wrong-doers will be in a a torment lasting.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxviii{%
And they shall have no patrons succouring them beside Allah. And whomsoever Allah sendeth astray for him there will be no way.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxix{%
Answer the call of Your Lord afore there cometh Unto you a Day for which there is no averting from Allah. Ye will have no place of refuge on that Day, nor there will be for you any denying of Your guilt.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxx{%
If then they turn away, then We have not sent thee to be a warden over them, on thee is naught but preaching. And verily We! when We cause man to taste of mercy from Us he exulteth thereat; and if an ill befalleth them because of that which their hands have sent on, then verily man becometh ingrate.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxi{%
Allah's is the dominion of the heavens and the earth. He createth whatsoever He Will. He bestoweth females upon whomsoever He will, and bestoweth males upon whomsoever He Will.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxii{%
Or He conjoineth them males and females; and He maketh barren whomsoever He will; verily He is Knower, Petent.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxiii{%
And it is not Possible for a human being that Allah should speak Unto him otherwise than by revelation or from behind a veil, or that He sendeth a messenger, so that he revealeth by His command whatsoever He will; verily He is Exalted, Wise.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxiv{%
Even so We have revealed Unto thee a spirit of Our command; thou knewest not whatsoever the Book was, nor whatsoever the faith; We have made it a light wherewith We guide whomsoever We will of Our bondmen. And verily thou guidest Unto a straight path.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxv{%
The path of Allah, Whose is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth. Lo! Unto Allah trend all affairs.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxvi{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxvii{%
By this luminous Book.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxviii{%
Verily We! We have made it an Arabic Qur'an that haply ye may reflect.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxix{%
And verily it is, in the Original Book before Us, indeed exalted.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxx{%
Shall We then take away from you the Admonition because ye are a people extravagant?\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxi{%
And how many a prophet We sent among the ancients.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxii{%
And not a prophet came Unto them but him they were wont to mock.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxiii{%
Wherefore We destroyed peoples mightier than these in prowess; and there hath gone forth the example of the ancients.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxiv{%
And if thou askest them: who hath created the heavens and the earth? they will surely say: created them the Mighty, the Knower.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxv{%
Who hath made for you the earth a bed, and hath made for you paths therein that haply ye may be directed.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxvi{%
And Who sendeth down from the heaven water in measure; then We quicken a dead land therewith: even so ye shall be brought forth.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxvii{%
And Who hath treated the pairs, all of them, and appointed for you from ships and cattle things whereon ye ride.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxviii{%
That ye mount firmly on the backs thereof, and then may remember the favour of your Lord When ye mount thereon, and may say: hallowed be He Who hath subjected this Unto us, and we for it were not fit.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxxxix{%
And verily Unto our Lord we are to return.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxl{%
And they appoint for Him from His bondmen a part! Verily man is an ingrate manifest.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxli{%
Hath He taken for Himself from whatsoever He hath created daughters, and hath honoured you with sons.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlii{%
And when there is announced Unto any of them the birth of that which he likeneth Unto the Compassionate, his countenance remaineth darkened the whole day and he is wroth inwardly."\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxliii{%
Hath He taken to Himself that which is reared in ornaments, and is in contention not plain?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxliv{%
And they make the angels who are the bondmen of the Compassionate females. Have they witnessed their creation? Their testimony will be written down, and they will be questioned.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlv{%
And they say: had the Compassionate willed we should not have worshipped them. They have no knowledge thereof; they are only guessing.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlvi{%
Have We vouchsafed Unto them any Book before this, so that they are to it holding fast?\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlvii{%
Nay! they say: verily we have found our fathers on a certain way, and verily by their footsteps we are guided.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlviii{%
And in this wise We sent not before thee into any city a warner but the affluent thereof said: verily we! we found our fathers on a certain way and verily their footsteps we are following.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxlix{%
The warner said: What! even though bring you a better guidance than that which ye found your fathers upon They said: verily in that wherewith ye are sent we are disbelievers.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccl{%
Wherefore We took revenge on them. Behold, then how hath been the end of the beliers?\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccli{%
And recall what time Ibrahim said Unto his father and his people: verily I am quit of that which ye worship.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclii{%
Save Him Who hath created me, and then He would guide me.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccliii{%
And he made it a word lasting among his posterity that haply they should return.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccliv{%
Aye! I let these and their fathers enjoy life, until there hath come Unto them the truth and an apostle manifest.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclv{%
And when the truth cometh Unto them, they say this is magic, and verily we are therein disbelievers.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclvi{%
And they say: wherefore hath not this Qur'an been revealed to a man of the two cities who was great.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclvii{%
Shall they apportion their Lord's mercy? It is We Who have apportioned among them their livelihood in the life of the War, and raised some of them over others in degrees, so that one of them may take another as a serf; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than that which they amass.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclviii{%
And were it not that mankind would have become one community, We should make for those who disbelieve in the Compassionate roofs of silver for their houses and silver stair ways whereby they ascend.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclix{%
And silver doors for their houses, and silver couches whereon they recline,\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclx{%
And ornament of gold. And yet all that would have been but a pro vision Of the life of the World; and the Hereafter with thy Lord is for the Godfearing.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxi{%
And whosoever blindeth himself to the admonition of the Compassionate, We assign Unto him a Satan, and he becometh his companion.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxii{%
And verily they hinder them from the way, whilst they deem that they are rightly guided.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxiii{%
Until when he cometh Unto Us, he will say. Ah! would that there had been between me and thee, the distance of the east and the west an evil companion\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxiv{%
And it Will profit you not today, because ye have done wrong, that ye are in the torment sharers.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxv{%
Wherefore canst thou make the deaf to hear, or canst thou guide the blind or him who is is error manifest?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxvi{%
And if We take thee away. We shall surely take vengeance on them.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxvii{%
Or if We shew thee that wherewith We threaten them, verily We are going to prevail over them.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxviii{%
Hold thou fast wherefore to that which is revealed Unto thee: verily thou art on the straight path. s\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxix{%
And verily it is an admonition Unto thee and thy people; and presently ye will be questioned.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxx{%
And ask thou Our apostles whom We sent before thee: appointed We gods, beside the Compassionate, to be worshipped?\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxi{%
And assuredly We sent Musa with Our signs Unto Fir'awn and his chiefs, and he said: verily I am an apostle of the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxii{%
Then when he came Unto them with Our signs, behold! at them they were laughing.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxiii{%
And not a sign We shewed them but it was greater than the like thereof; and We laid hold of them with the torment that haply they might turn.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxiv{%
And they said: magician! supplicate thy Lord for us for that which He hath covenanted with thee; verily we shall let ourselves be guided.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxv{%
Then When We had removed from them the torment, behold they were breaking their promise.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxvi{%
And Fir'awn proclaimed among his people, saying: O my people! is not mine the dominion of Mis and witness yonder rivers flowing underneath me? See ye not?\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxvii{%
Aye! I am better than this one who is depicable, and well- nigh cannot make himself plain.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxviii{%
Wherefore, then, have bracelets of gold not been set upon him, and wherefore have not angels come with him accompanying\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxix{%
Then he incited his people and they obeyed him; verily they were ever a transgressing people.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxx{%
So when they vexed Us, We took vengeance on them, and We drowned them all.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxi{%
And We made them a precedent and an ensample Unto those after.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxii{%
And when the son of Maryam is held up, an example, behold! thy people thereat cry out.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxiii{%
And they say: are our gods better, or is he? They mention him not to thee save for disputation. Aye! they are a people contentious.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxiv{%
He is naught but a bondman: him We favoured, and him We made an ensample Unto the Children of Israil.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxv{%
And had We willed We could have appointed angels born of you in the earth to succeed each other.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxvi{%
And verily he is a sign of the Hour wherefore dubitate not thereof, and follow Me: this is the straight path.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxvii{%
And let not the Satan hinder you; verily he is Unto you an enemy manifest.\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxviii{%
And when Isa came with; evidences, he said: of a surety I have come Unto you with Wisdom, and to expound Unto you some of that wherein ye differ; so fear Allah and obey me.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmccclxxxix{%
Verily Allah! He is my lord and your Lord, so worship Him: this is the straight path.\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxc{%
Then the sects differed among themselves. Woe then Unto those who do Wrong because of the torment of an afflictive Day.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxci{%
They await but the Hour: that it should come upon them of a sudden, while they perceive not.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcii{%
The intimate friends on that Day Will be hostile Unto one another save the God-fearing.\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxciii{%
O My bondmen! no fear shall be on you Today, nor shall ye grieve\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxciv{%
Ye who believed in Our revelations and were Muslims.\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcv{%
Enter the Garden, ye and your spouses, joyfully.\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcvi{%
Passed round amongst them will be dishes of gold and goblets, and therein will be whatsoever souls desire and eyes delight in; and ye will be therein abiders.\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcvii{%
This is the Garden which ye have been made to inherit for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcviii{%
For you therein will be fruits in plenty whereof ye will eat.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcccxcix{%
Verily the culprits in Hell's torment will be abiders.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcd{%
It shall not be abated from off them, and they will be therein despondent.\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdi{%
And We wronged them not, but they have been the wrong- doers themselves.\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdii{%
And -they will cry: O keeper let thy Lord make an end of us. He will say: verily ye shall bide\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdiii{%
Assuredly We brought the truth Unto you, but most Of you are to the truth averse.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdiv{%
Have they determined an affair? then verily We are also determining.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdv{%
Bethink they that We hear not their secrets and whispers? Yea! We do, and Our messengers present with them write down.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdvi{%
Say thou: had the Compassionate a son, shall be the first of his worshippers.\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdvii{%
Hallowed be the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, from that which they ascribe!\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdviii{%
So let them thou alone wading and sporting until hey meet the Day which they are promised.\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdix{%
And He it is Who is God in the heavens and God in the earth, and He is the Wise, the Knower.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdx{%
And blest be He Whose is the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in-between the twain, and with Him is knowledge of the Hour, and Unto Him ye will be made to return.\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxi{%
And those whom they call upon beside Him own not the power of intercession save those who have borne witness to the truth and who know.\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxii{%
And wert thou to ask them who created them, they will surely say: God. Witherward then are they deviating!\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxiii{%
And We hear his saying: my Lord! verily these are a people who believe not.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxiv{%
Wherefore turn thou aside from them, and say: peace. presently they shall come to know.\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxv{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxvi{%
By the luminious Book.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxvii{%
Verily We have sent it down on a blessed night, verily We were to become warners.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxviii{%
Therein is decreed every affair of wisdom\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxix{%
As a command from before Us. Verily We were to become senders:\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxx{%
A mercy from thy Lord. Verily He! He is the Hearer, the Knower.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxi{%
Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in- between the twain, if only ye would be convinced.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxii{%
There is no god but He. He quickeneth and causeth to die: your Lord and Lord of your forefathers.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxiii{%
Aye! they're in doubt sporting.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxiv{%
So wait thou day whereon the heaven will bring forth a manifest smoke:\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxv{%
Covering the people's this shall be a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxvi{%
Our Lord! remove from us the torment, verily we shall become believers.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxvii{%
How can there be an admonition Unto them, when surely there came Unto them an apostle manifest!\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxviii{%
Yet they turned away from him and said: one tutored, one distraced.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxix{%
Verily We shall remove the torment for a while; but verily ye shall revert.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxx{%
On the Day whereon We assault them with the greatest assault, verily We shall take vengeance.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxi{%
And assuredly afore them We proved Fir'awn's people, and there came Unto them an apostle honoured.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxii{%
Saying: restore to me the bondmen of Allah, verily I am Unto you an apostle trusted.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxiii{%
And saying exalt not yourselves against Allah; verily I have come Unto you with an authority manifest.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxiv{%
And verily I have sought refuge in my Lord and your Lord lest ye stone me.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxv{%
And if ye will not believe in me, then let me alone.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxvi{%
Then he called upon his Lord. these are a people guilty.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxvii{%
So depart thou with My bondmen by night; verily ye shall be pursued.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxviii{%
And leave thou the sea divided: verily they are a host to be drowned.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxxxix{%
They left - how many! - of gardens and springs.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxl{%
And cornfields and goodly positions.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxli{%
And the delights which they had been enjoying!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlii{%
Even so And We caused to inherit them another people.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxliii{%
And the heavens and the earth wept not over them, nor were they respited.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxliv{%
And assuredly We delivered the Children of Isra'il from an ignominous torment\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlv{%
From Fir'awn; verily he was haughty and of the extravagant.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlvi{%
And assuredly We elected them with knowledge above the worlds.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlvii{%
And We vouchsafed Unto them signs wherein was a manifest favour.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlviii{%
Verily these! they say:\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxlix{%
There is naught but our first death, and we shall not be raised again.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdl{%
Bring then our fathers if ye say so.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdli{%
Are they better Or the people of Tubba and those afore them? We destroyed them; verily they were culprits.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlii{%
And We created not the heavens and the earth and all that is in-between the twain sporting.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdliii{%
We created them not save with a purpose but most of them know not.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdliv{%
Verily the Day of Distinction is the term appointed for all of them.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlv{%
A Day whereon a friend shall not avail a friend at all, nor shall they be helped.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlvi{%
Save those on whom Allah will have mercy. Verily He! He is the Mighty, the Merciful.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlvii{%
Verily the tree of Zaqqum:\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlviii{%
Food of the sinner.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlix{%
Like the dregs of all! It shall seethe in the bellies:\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlx{%
As the seething of boiling water.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxi{%
Lay hold of him, and drag him Unto the midst of the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxii{%
Then pour upon his head the torment of balling water.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxiii{%
Taste thou! thou art indeed mighty, honoured!\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxiv{%
Verily this is that whereof ye were wont to doubt.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxv{%
Verily the God-fearing will be in a place secure\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxvi{%
Amidst gardens and springs.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxvii{%
Attired in fine silk and brocade, facing each other.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxviii{%
Even so. And We shall pair them with fair damsels large- eyed.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxix{%
They will call therein for every kind of fruit in security.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxx{%
They will not taste death therein, except the first death; and He will preserve them from the torment of the Flaming Fire.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxi{%
A bounty from thy Lord. That! that is the supreme achievement.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxii{%
And We have made it easy in thy language; they might haply be admonished.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxiii{%
Wait thou then; verily they also are waiting.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxiv{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxv{%
The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxvi{%
Verily in the heavens and the earth are signs Unto the believers.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxvii{%
And in the creation of yourselves and of the beasts that He hath scattered over the earth, are signs Unto a people who are convinced.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxviii{%
And in the alternation of night and day and that which Allah sendeth down of provision from the heaven and thereby quickeneth the earth after the death thereof and the turning about of the winds, are signs Unto a people who reflect.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxix{%
These are the revelations of Allah which We rehearse Unto thee with truth: in what discourse then, after Allah and His revelations, will they believe?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxx{%
Woe Unto every liar, sinner!\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxi{%
Who heareth the revelations of Allah rehearsed Unto him, and yet persisteth with stiff-neckedness as though he heard them not. Announce thou Unto him, then, a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxii{%
And when he cometh to know aught of Our revelations, he taketh it scoffingly. These! theirs shall be a torment ignominous;\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxiii{%
Before them is Hell; naught will avail them of that which they earned, nor those whom they took for patrons beside Allah. Theirs shall be a torment mighty.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxiv{%
This Book is guidance, and those who disbelieve in the revelations of their Lord, theirs shall be torment of calamity, afflictive.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxv{%
Allah it is Who hath subjected the sea for your sake, that the ships may run thereon by His command and that ye may seek of His grace, and that haply ye may return thanks.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxvi{%
And He hath subjected for your sake whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, the whole from Himself. Verily herein are signs Unto a people who ponder.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxvii{%
Say thou Unto those who believe, let them forgive those who hope not for the days of Allah, that He may requite a community for that which they have been earning.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxviii{%
Whosoever worketh righteously, worketh for himself; and whosoever doth evil, doth against himself; then Unto your Lord ye will be made to return.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdlxxxix{%
And assuredly. We vouchsafed Unto the Children of Israil the Book and the wisdom and the propherhood, and We provided them with good things and preferred them above the worlds.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxc{%
And We vouchsafed Unto them evidences of the affair. And they differed not except after the knowledge had come Unto them, through spite among themselves. Verily thy Lord will decide between them on the DaY of Judgment concerning that wherein they have been differing.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxci{%
And thereafter We have placed thee upon the law of the religion; so follow it thou, and follow not the vain desires of those who know not.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcii{%
Verily they cannot avail thee at all against Allah. And verily the wrong doers! friends are they one Unto another. And Allah is the Friend of the God-fearing.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxciii{%
This Book is an enlightenment Unto mankind and a guidance, and a mercy Unto a People who are convinced.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxciv{%
Deem those who commit ill deeds that We shall make them as those who believe and work righteous Works? Equal is their life and their death! How ill they judge!\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcv{%
And Allah hath created the heavens and the earth with purpose and that every soul may be recompensed for that which it hath earned. And they will not be wronged.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcvi{%
Beholdest thou him who taketh for his god his own vain desire, and Allah hath sent him astray despite his knowledge, and hath sealed up his hearing and his heart, and hath set on his sight a covering? Who will guide him after Allah? Will ye not then be admonished?\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcvii{%
And they say: there is no naught but our life of the world; die and we live; and naught destroyeth us save Time. And they have no knowledge thereof: they do but guess.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcviii{%
And when Our manifest revelations are rehearsed Unto them, their argument is no other than that they say bring our fathers, if ye say sooth.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmcdxcix{%
Say thou: Allah keepeth you alive, then He shall cause you to die, then He shall assemble you on the Day of Resurrection whereof there is no doubt; but most of mankind know not.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmd{%
And Allah's is the dominion of the heavens and the earth; and on the Day whereon the Hour arriveth, then shall lose the followers of falsehood.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdi{%
And thou shalt behold each community kneeling; each community shall be summoned to its Book. Today, shall be recompensed for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdii{%
This Book of Ours speaketh against you with truth; verily We have been setting down whatsoever ye have been working.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdiii{%
Then, as for those who believed and worked righteous works, their Lord will cause them to enter into His mercy: that is a manifest achievement.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdiv{%
And as for those who disbelieved: Were not My revelations rehearsed Unto you? but ye were stiff necked, and ye were a people guilty.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdv{%
And when it was said; verily Allah's promise is, true, and the Hour! there is no doubt thereof, ye said: we know not what the Hour is, we imagine it naught but an opinion, and we are not convinced.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdvi{%
And there will appear Unto them the evils Of that which they had worked, and there will surround them that whereat they had been mocking.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdvii{%
And it will be said: Today shall forget you, even as ye forgat the meeting of this your Day, and your abode will be the Fire, and none ye will have as helpers.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdviii{%
That is because ye took the revelations of Allah scoffingly, and there beguiled you the life of the world. Today, therefore, they will not be taken forth therefrom, nor will they be suffered to please Allah.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdix{%
All praise, then, Unto Allah, Lord of the heavens and Lord of the earth, Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdx{%
And His alone is the Majesty in the heavens and the earth, and He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxi{%
\basmalahen Ha. Mim.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxii{%
The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxiii{%
We created not the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in-between the twain save with truth, and for a term stated. And those who disbelieve are from that whereof they are warned backsliders.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxiv{%
Say thou: bethink ye: whatsoever ye call upon beside Allah- show me whatsoever they have created of the earth? Or have they any partnership in the heavens? Bring me a Book before this, Or some trace of knowledges if ye say sooth.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxv{%
And who is more astray than he who calleth beside Allah, Unto such as will answer it not till the Day of Resurrection and who are of their call unaware.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxvi{%
And when mankind will be gathered they will become Unto them enemies and of their worship they will become deniers.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxvii{%
And when Our manifest revelations are rehearsed Unto them those who disbelieve say of the truth when it hath come to them: this is magic manifest.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxviii{%
Say they: he hath fabricated it. Say thou: if I have fabricated it, then ye cannot avail me against Allah in aught. He is the Knower of that which ye utter thereof; He sufficeth as a witness between me and you; and He is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxix{%
Say thou: I am not an innovator among the apostles, nor I know whatsoever shall be done with me or with you; I only follow that which is revealed Unto me, and am but a warner manifest.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxx{%
Say thou: bethink ye: if it is from Allah while ye disbelieve therein and a witness from the Children of Isra'il beareth witness to the like thereof and believeth, while ye are still stiff necked, then who is further astray than you? Verily Allah guideth not a wrong-doing people.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxi{%
And those who disbelieve say of those who believe: had it been good, they would not have preceded us thereto. And when they have not let themselves be guided thereby, they say: this is an ancient falsehood.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxii{%
And before it there hath been the Book of Musa, a guide and a mercy. And this a Book confirming it, in Arabic speech, that it may warn those who have done wrong and as glad tidings Unto the well-doers.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxiii{%
Verily those who say: our Lord is Allah, and thereafter stand fast thereto, no fear shall come upon them, nor shall they grieve.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxiv{%
Those are the fellows of the Carden: abiders therein: a recompense for that which they have been working.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxv{%
And We have enjoined upon man kindness Unto the parents: with hardship his mother beareth him and with hardship she bringeth him forth, and the bearing of him and the weaning of him is thirty months, until, when he attaineth his full strength and attaineth the age of forty years, he saith: my Lord! grant me that may give thanks for the favour wherewith. Thou hast favoured me and my parents and that may work righteously such as Thou mayest approve; and be Thou good Unto me in my progeny, verily have turned Unto Thee repentant, and verily I am of those who submit.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxvi{%
Those are they from whom We shall accept the best of that which they have worked, and their misdeeds We shall pass by: among the fellows of the Garden: a true promise this, which they have been promised.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxvii{%
And he who saith Unto his parents: fie upon you both! threaten me ye that I shall be taken forth, whereas generations have passed away before me? and the twain implore Allah's assistance woe Unto thee! come to believe! verily the promise of Allah is true; yet he saith: naught is this but fables of the ancients."\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxviii{%
Those are they upon whom hath been justified the saying about the communities of the Jinn and mankind who have passed away before them; verily they are ever the losers.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxix{%
And for each are ranks according to that which they have worked, that He may repay them in full for their works; and they shall not be wronged.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxx{%
And on the Day whereon those who disbelieve shall be placed before the Fire: ye made away with your good things in your life of the world, and ye enjoyed yourselves therewith so Today ye shall be requited with the torment of ignominy, for that ye have been growing stiff-necked on the earth without justification, and for that ye have been transgressing.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxi{%
And remember thou the brother of the Aad when We warned his people in the sandhills - and surely there have passed away warners before him and after him - saying: worship none save Allah, verily I fear for you the torment of a mighty Day.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxii{%
They said: art thou come Unto us that thou mayest turn us aside from our gods? then bring thou upon us that wherewith thou threatenest us, if thou art of the truth-tellers.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxiii{%
He said: the knowledge is only with Allah, and I preach Unto you that wherewith I have been sent, but I see you are a people given to ignorance.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxiv{%
Then when they beheld it as an overpeering cloud tending toward their valleys they said: yonder is an overpeering cloud bringing us rain. Nay it is that which ye sought to be hastened: a wind wherein is a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxv{%
It shall annihilate everything by the command of its Lord. Wherefore they became such that naught could be seen save their dwellings Thus We requite a nation of the culprits.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxvi{%
And assuredly We had established them in that flourishing condition wherein We have not established you, and We had appointed for them hearing and sight and hearts; yet their hearing and sight and heart availed them not at all, they became wont to gainsay the revelations of Allah, and surrounded them that whereat they had been mocking.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxvii{%
And assuredly We have destroyed the cities round about you. and We have variously propounded our signs, that haply they might return.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxviii{%
Then wherefore succoured them not those whom they had taken for gods beside Allah, as a means of approach? Aye! they failed them. And that was their lie, that which they had been fabricating.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxxxix{%
And recall what time We turned towards thee a company Of the Jinns hearkening Unto the Qur'an. So when they came in the presence thereof they said: give ear. Then when it was ended, they turned back to their people as warners.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxl{%
They said: O our people! verily we have hearkened Unto a Book sent down after Musa, confirming that which was before it, guiding Unto the truth and a straight path.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxli{%
O our people! answer Allah's summoner and believe in him; He shall forgive you your sins and shall shelter you from a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlii{%
And whosoever answereth not Allah's summoner, he cannot frustrate His vengeAnce on the earth, and for him there will be, beside Him, no patrons. Those are in error manifest.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxliii{%
Bethink they not that Allah Who created the heavens and the earth and was not fatigued with the creation thereof, is able to quicken the dead? Aye! verily He is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxliv{%
And on the Day whereon those who disbelieve will be placed before the Fire: is this not real? They will say: yea, by our Lord. He will say: taste wherefore the torment, for ye have been disbelieving.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlv{%
Bear thou then with patience even as the apostles, endued with resolution bear with patience, and seek not to hasten on for them. On the Day whereon they will behold that wherewith they are threatened, it will seem to them as though they had tarried but an hour of the day. A proclamation this: so none will be destroyed save the nation of transgressors.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlvi{%
\basmalahen Those who disbelieve and hinder others from the way of Allah, He shall send their works astray.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlvii{%
And those who believe and work righteous works and believe in that which hath been revealed Unto Muhammad -and it is the truth from their Lord- He shall expiate their misdeeds from them and shall make good their state.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlviii{%
That is because those who disbelieve follow the falsehood, and those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. And thus Allah propoundeth Unto mankind their similitude.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxlix{%
Now when ye meet those who disbelieve, smite their necks until when ye have slain them greatly, then make fast the bonds; then, thereafter let them off either freely or by ransom, until the war layeth down the burthens thereof. That ye shall do. And had Allah willed, He would have vindicated Himself against them, but He ordained fighting in order that He may prove you one by the other. And those who are slain in the way of Allah, He shall not send their works astray.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdl{%
Anon He shall guide them, and shall make good their state.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdli{%
And He shall make them enter the Garden; He shall have made it known, Unto them.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlii{%
O ye who believe! if ye and shall succour Allah, He shall succour you make firm your feet.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdliii{%
And those who disbelieve, downfall shall be theirs, and He shall send astray their Works.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdliv{%
That is because they detest that which Allah hath sent down, and so He shall make of non-effect their works.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlv{%
Have they not travelled then on the earth so that they might see how hath been the end of those before them! Allah annihilated them. And for the infidels theirs shall be the like fate therefore.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlvi{%
That is because Allah is the patron of those who believe, and because the infidels! no patron is theirs.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlvii{%
Verily Allah shall cause those who believe and work righteous works to enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow. And those who disbelieve enjoy themselves and eat even as the cattle eat, and the Fire shall be the abode for them.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlviii{%
And many a city, mightier In strength than the city which drave thee forth, We destroyed them, and there was no helper of theirs.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlix{%
Is he then who standeth, on an evidence from his Lord like Unto him whose evil of work is made fair-seeming for him and those who follow their lusts?\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlx{%
A likeness of the Garden which hath been promised to the God-fearing: therein are rivers of water incorruptible, and rivers of milk whereof the flavour changeth not, and rivers of wine: a joy Unto the drinkers; and rivers of honey clarified. theirs therein shall be every kind of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. ShAll Persons enjoying such bliss be like Unto those who are abiders in the Fire and are given to drink boiling water so that it mangleth their entrails?\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxi{%
Of them are some who listen to thee, until, when they go forth from before thee, they say Unto those who have been vouchsafed knowledge, what is that he hath said just now? Those are they whose hearts Allah hath sealed up and they follow their lusts.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxii{%
And those who are guided He increaseth Unto them guidance, and giveth them their piety.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxiii{%
Await they but the Hour, that it should come upon them on a sudden? Tokens thereof are already come, so how shall it be with them when there cometh Unto them their admonition!\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxiv{%
So know thou that there is no god save Allah, and ask forgiveness for thy fault and for believing men and believing women. And Allah knoweth well your moving about and your place of rest.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxv{%
And those who believe say wherefore hath not a Surah been revealed? Then when there is sent down a Surah firmly constructed, and fighting is mentioned therein, thou seest those in whose hearts is a disease looking at thee with the look of one swooning Unto death. So also for them!\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxvi{%
Their obedience and speech are known. Then when the affair is determined, if even then they gave credence Unto Allah, it would have been better for them.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxvii{%
Then, belike ye are, if ye turn to cause corruption in the earth away, and to sever your kinship.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxviii{%
Those are they whom Allah hath cursed, and then hath deafened them and blinded their sights.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxix{%
Ponder then they not on the Qur'an, or are on the hearts locks thereof?\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxx{%
Verily those who have apostated on their backs after the guidance had become manifest Unto them, the devil hath embellished this apostacy for them and hath given them false hopes.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxi{%
That is because they said Unto those who detest that which Allah hath revealed: we shall obey you in part of the affair; and Allah knoweth their talking in secret.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxii{%
How then shall it be when the angels shall take them away at death smiting their faces and their backs!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxiii{%
That is because they followed that which angered Allah and detested His good-will; so He made their works of non-effect.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxiv{%
Deem those in whose hearts is a disease that Allah will never bring to light their secret malevolence?\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxv{%
And if We willed, We would surely shew them Unto thee, so that thou shouldst surely know them by their marks. And thou shalt surely know them by the mode of their speech. And Allah knoweth your works.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxvi{%
And of a surety We shall prove you all until We know the strivers among you and the steadfast, and We shall prove your states.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxvii{%
Verily those who have disbelieved and have hindered others from the way of Allah and have opposed the apostle after the guidance had become manifest Unto them, shall not hurt Allah at all, and anon He shall render their works of non effect.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxviii{%
Ye who believe! obey Allah and obey the apostle, and render not Your works vain.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxix{%
Verily those who disbelieve and hinder others from the way of Allah and then die as infidels, Allah shall by no means forgive them.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxx{%
Wherefore faint not, nor cry out for peace; and ye shall be triumphant. And Allah is with you, and He will not defraud you of your works.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxi{%
The life of the world is but a sport and a pastime. And if ye believe and fear, He will give you your hire, and will not require of you your substance.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxii{%
If He required it of you and importuned you, ye would be niggardly, and He will bring to light your secret malevolence.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxiii{%
Behold! ye are those who are called to expend in the way of Allah, then there are of you some who are niggardly. And whosoever is niggardly is niggardly only to himself. And Allah is Self-sufficient, and ye are the needy. And if ye turn away, He will substitute for you another people, and then they will not be the likes of you.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxiv{%
\basmalahen Verily We! a victory We have given thee, a manifest victory.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxv{%
That Allah may forgive thee that which hath preceded of thy fault and that which may come later, and may accomplish the more His favour on thee, and may keep thee guided on the straight path.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxvi{%
And that Allah may succour thee with a mighty succour.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxvii{%
He it is Who sent down tranquillity into the hearts of the believers that they might increase belief Unto their belief. And Allah's are the hosts of the heavens and the earth and Allah is ever Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxviii{%
He hath ordained war in order that He may cause the believing men and the believing women enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow, as abiders therein, and that He may expiate from them their misdeeds. And that is with Allah ever an achievement mighty.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdlxxxix{%
And that He may chastise the hypocritical men and the hypocritical women and the associaters and the associatresses, the thinkers of evil thought concerning Allah. Unto them shall befell the evil turn of fortune, and Allah shall be wroth with them and shall curse them, and He hath gotten ready for them Hell: an ill destination!\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxc{%
And Allah's are the hosts of the heavens and the earth, and Allah is ever Mighty, Wise.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxci{%
Verily We! We have sent thee as a witness and a bearer of glad tidings and a warner.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcii{%
That ye may believe in Allah and His apostle, and may assist Him and honour Him, and may hallow Him at dawn and evening.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxciii{%
Verily those who swear fealty Unto thee, only swear fealty Unto Allah: the hand of Allah is over their hands. So whosoever breaketh his oath, breaketh it only to his soul's hurt; and whosoever fulfilleth that which he hath convenanted with Allah, him anon He shall give a mighty hire.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxciv{%
Those who lagged behind of the desert Arabs Will presently say Unto thee: our properties and our households kept us occupied, so ask thou forgiveness for Us. They say with their tongues that which is not in their hearts. Say thou: who can avail you in aught against Allah, if He intended you hurt or intended you benefit? Yea! Allah is of that which ye work ever Aware.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcv{%
Yea! ye imagined that the apostle and the believers would never return to their households, and that became fair-seeming in your hearts, and ye bethought an evil thought, and ye became a people doomed.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcvi{%
And whosoever believeth not in Allah and His apostle then verily We have gotten ready for the infidels a Blaze.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcvii{%
And Allah's is the dominion of the heavens and the earth. He forgivEth whomsoever He Will and tormenteth whomsoever he will; and Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcviii{%
Those who lagged behind will presently, When ye march forth to take spoils, leave us, we shall follow say you. They intend to change the word of Allah. Say thou: ye shall by no means follow us; thus hath Allah said afore. Then they will say: Aye! ye envy us. Aye! little it is they are wont to understand.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdxcix{%
Say thou Unto those who lagged behind of the desert Arabs: surely ye shall be summoned against a people endued with exceeding violence then ye will fight them or they will submit. Then if ye obey, Allah will give ye a goodly hire; but if ye turn away even as ye turned away aforetime. He will torment you with a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdc{%
There is no blame upon the blind, nor is there blame upon the lame, nor is there blame upon the sick. And whosoever obeyeth Allah and His apostle, He will cause him enter Gardens where under rivers flow; and whosoever turneth away, him He shall torment with a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdci{%
Assuredly well-pleased was Allah with the believers when they sware fealty Unto thee under the tree, and he knew that which was in their hearts, wherefore He sent down tranquillity on them, and rewarded them with a victory near at hand.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcii{%
And spoils in abundance that they are taking. And Allah is ever Mighty, Wise.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdciii{%
Allah hath promised you abundant spoils that ye shall take, and these He hath hastened to you, and hath restrained the hands of people from you, that it may be a sign Unto the believers, and that He may guide you to a straight path.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdciv{%
And He promiseth another victory, over which ye have as yet no power: Allah hath surely encompassed it; and Allah is over everything ever Potent.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcv{%
And had those who disbelieve fought against you, surely they would have turned their backs, and then they would have found no patron nor helper.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcvi{%
That hath been the dispensation of Allah with those who passed away aforetime; and thou shalt not find in the dispensation of Allah any change.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcvii{%
And He it is Who restrained their hands from you and Your hands from them, in the vale of Makka so, after He had made you superior to them; and Allah is of that which ye work ever a Beholder.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcviii{%
They were those who disbelieved and hindered you from the Sacred Mosque and hindered the detained offering that it should arrive at the goal thereof. And had it not been for believing men and believin women whom ye knew not, and that ye might have trampled on them and thus there might have befallen you crime on their account unwittingly. He had not restrained your hands from them. But this He did that He might bring into His mercy whomsoever He will. Had they been distinguished one from another, surely We had tormented those who disbelieved among them with a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcix{%
When those who disbelieve had put in their hearts a zeal, the zeal of Paganism, then Allah sent down His tranquillity upon His apostle and upon the believers, and kept them fixed on the way of piety, and they were worthy thereof and meet therefor; and Allah is of everything ever Knower.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcx{%
Assuredly did Allah shew a true vision to His apostle in very truth; ye shall surely enter the Sacred Mosque, if Allah willeth, secure, having your heads shaven and your hair cut, and ye shall not fear. He knoweth that which ye know not; wherefore He appointed, beside that, a victory near at hand.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxi{%
He it is Who hath sent His apostle with the guidance and the true religion that He may make it prevail over all other religions, and Allah sufficeth as a Witness.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxii{%
Muhammad is the apostle of Allah. And those who are with him are stern against the infidels and merciful among themselves; Thou beholdest them bowing down and falling prostrate, seeking grace from Allah and His goodWill Mark of them is on their faces from the effect of prostration: such is their similitude in the Taurat. And their similitude in the lnjil: like Unto a sown corn that putteth forth its shoot and strengtheneth it, and swelieth, and riseth upon the stalk thereof delighting the sowers. Such are the early Muslims described that He may enrage the infidels with them. Allah hath promised Unto those among them who believe and work righteous works, forgiveness and a mighty hire.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxiii{%
\basmalahen O ye who believe! be not forward in the presence of Allah and His apostle, and fear Allah; verily Allah is Hearing, Knowing.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxiv{%
Ye who believe raise not your voices above the voice of the prophet, nor shout loud Unto him in discourse as ye shout loud Unto one another, lest your works may be rendered of non-effect, while ye perceive not.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxv{%
Verily those who lower their voices in the presence of the apostle of Allah -those are they whose hearts Allah hath disposed Unto piety: theirs will be forgiveness and a mighty hire.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxvi{%
Verily those who call aloud Unto thee from without the inner apartments, most of them reflect not."\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxvii{%
And had they had patience till thou camest forth Unto them, it had surely been best for them; and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxviii{%
ye who believe! if an evil-doer Came Unto you with a report, then inquire strictly, lest ye hurt a people in ignorance and repent thereafter of that which ye have done.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxix{%
And know that verily among you is the apostle of Allah. Were he to obey you in many affairs, ye would surely be in trouble but Allah hath endeared belief to you and hath made it fair-seeming in your hearts, and hath rendered detestable Unto you infidelity and wickedness and disobedience. These! they are the men of rectitude.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxx{%
Through grace from Allah and His favour; and Allah is Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxi{%
And if two parties of the believers fall to mutual fighting, then make reconciliation between the twain. Then if one of them rebelleth against the other, fight that Party which rebelleth till it returneth Unto the affair of Allah; then if it returneth, make reconciliation between the twain with justice and be equitable; verily Allah loveth the equitable.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxii{%
The believers are but brethren; wherefore make reconciliation between your brethren and fear Allah, that haply ye may be shewn mercy.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxiii{%
O ye who believe! let not one group scoff at another group, belike they may be better than they are, nor let some women scoff at other women, belike they may be better than they are. And traduce not one another, nor revile one another by odious appellations! ill is the name of sin after belief. And whosoever will not repent, then those, they are the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxiv{%
O ye who believe! avoid much suspicion; verily some suspicion is a sin. And espy not, nor backbite one another: would any of you love to eat the flesh of his dead brother? Ye detest that. And fear Allah verily Allah is Relenting, Merciful.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxv{%
O Humankind verily We! We have created you Of a male and female, and We have made you nations and tribes that ye might know one another. Verily the noblest of you with Allah is the most God-fearing of you; verily Allah is Knowing, Aware,\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxvi{%
The desert Arabs say: we have believed. Say thou: believe not, but rather say: We have submitted; and belief hath not yet entered into your hearts. And if ye obey Allah and His apostle, He shall not diminish from you aught Of you, wOrks verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxvii{%
The believers are only those who believed in Allah and His apostle and thereafter doubted not, and strave with their riches and their persons in the cause of Allah. Those! they are the truthful.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxviii{%
Say thou: Would ye appraise Allah of your religion, whereas Allah knoweth whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, and Allah is of everything Aware!\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxix{%
They make it a favour Unto thee that they have surrendered. Say thou: deem not your surrender a favour Unto me; nay! Allah hath conferred a favour Unto you inasmuch as He hath guided you to belief, if ye are sincere.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxx{%
Verily Allah knoweth the Unseen of the heavens and the earth; and Allah is the Beholder of that which ye work.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxi{%
\basmalahen Qaf. By the Qur'an glorious, We have sent thee as a warner.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxii{%
Aye! they marvel that there hath come Unto them a warner from among themselves; so the infidels Say: this is a thing wondrous!\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxiii{%
Shell We be brought back when we are dead and have become dust? That is a return remote!\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxiv{%
Surely We know that which the earth consumeth of them, and with Us is, Book preserved.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxv{%
Aye! they belie the truth when it cometh Unto them; wherefore they are in an affair confused.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxvi{%
Have they not looked up to the heaven above them, in what wise We have constructed and bedecked it, and that therein is no rift?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxvii{%
And the earth! We have spread it forth, and have cast therein firm mountains, and have caused to grow therein of every beauteous kind of plants:\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxviii{%
An insight and an admonition for every bondman penitent.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxxxix{%
And We have sent down from the heaven water brest wherewith We have caused gardens to grow and the grain reaped.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxl{%
And tall date-palms laden with clusters ranged.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxli{%
As a provision for our bondmen; and therewith We have quickened a dead land. Even so will be the coming forth.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlii{%
And before them the people of Nuh belied, and so did the dwellers Of Rass and the Thamud.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxliii{%
And the A-ad, and Fir'awn. and the brethren of Lut.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxliv{%
And the dwellers in the wood, and the people of Tubba. Each one belied the apostles, wherefore fulfilled was My judgement.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlv{%
Are We then wearied with the first creation? Aye! they are in dubiety regarding a new creation.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlvi{%
And assuredly We have created man and We know whatsoever his soul whispereth Unto him, and We are nigher Unto him than his jugular vein.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlvii{%
Behold! when the two receivers receive-one on the right hand and one on the left a sitter.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlviii{%
Not a word he uttereth but there is with him a watcher ready.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxlix{%
And the stupor of death will come in truth: this is that which thou hast been shunning.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcl{%
And the trumpet will be blown: this is the Day of the Threatening.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcli{%
And there shall come every soul therewith shall be a driver and a witness.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclii{%
Assuredly thou wast in neglect thereof; now We have removed from off thee thy veil, so thy sight Today is piercing.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcliii{%
And his companion will say: this is that which with me is ready.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcliv{%
Cast ye twain into Hell every Person rebellious, contumacious.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclv{%
Hinderer o fgood, trespasser, doubter\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclvi{%
Who set up with Allah another god. So cast him ye twain into the torment severe.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclvii{%
His companion will say: O our Lord! caused him not to transgress but he was himself in error far off.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclviii{%
Allah will say: wrangle not in My presence, and had already proferred Unto you the threat.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclix{%
The Word will not be changed in My presence, nor am an oppressor at all Unto My bondmen.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclx{%
Mention the Day whereon We shall say Unto the Hell: art thou filled? and it will say: is there yet any addition?\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxi{%
And brought nigh will be the Garden Unto the God-fearing, not far-off.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxii{%
This is that which ye were promised: for every oft- returning heedful one.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxiii{%
That feareth the Compassionate in the unseen and cometh to Him with a heart penitent:\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxiv{%
Enter it in peace. This is the Day of Abidence.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxv{%
Theirs therein will be whatsoever they list; and with Us will be yet more.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxvi{%
And how many a generation have We destroyed before them, who were mightier in power than they, and they traversed the cities! No place of refuge could they find.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxvii{%
Verily herein is an admonition Unto him who hath a heart, or giveth ear while he is heedful.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxviii{%
And assuredly We created the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is in between the twain in six days, and there touched Us naught of weariness.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxix{%
So bear thou patiently with that which they say, and hallow the praise of thine Lord before the rising of the sun and before its setting.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxx{%
And in the night-time hallow Him, and also after the prescribed prostration.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxi{%
And hearken thou: the Day whereon the caller will call from a place quite near.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxii{%
The Day whereon they will surely hear the shout - that is the Day of coming forth.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxiii{%
Verily We! it is We Who give life and cause death, and Unto Us is the journeying.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxiv{%
That shall be the Day whereon the earth will be cleft from off them as they hasten forth. That shall be a gathering Unto Us easy.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxv{%
We are the best Knower of that which they say, and thou art not over them over them tyrant. Wherefore admonish thou by the Qur'an him who feareth My threat.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxvi{%
\basmalahen By the dipersing winds that disperse.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxvii{%
And the clouds bearing a load.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxviii{%
And the ships that glide with ease.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxix{%
And the angels who distribute the affair.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxx{%
Verily that wherewith ye are threatened is surely true.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxi{%
And verily the Requital is surely to befall.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxii{%
By the heaven full of paths.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxiii{%
Verily ye are in a divided opinion.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxiv{%
Turned aside therefrom is who is turned aside.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxv{%
Perish the conjecturers\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxvi{%
Those who are in heedlessness neglectful.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxvii{%
They ask: when is the Day of Requital coming?\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxviii{%
It will be the Day whereon in the Fire they will be burned\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdclxxxix{%
Taste your burning: this is that which ye sought to be hastened.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxc{%
Verily the God-fearing will be amid Gardens and water- springs.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxci{%
Taking that which their Lord will vouchsafe Unto hem. Verily they have been before that well-doers.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcii{%
Little of the night they were wont to slumber.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxciii{%
And in the dawns they prayed for forgiveness.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxciv{%
And in their substance was the right of the beggar and non- beggar.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcv{%
And on the earth there are signs for those who would be convinced.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcvi{%
And also in Your own selves. Behold ye not?\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcvii{%
And in the heaven is Your provision and that which ye are promised.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcviii{%
By the Lord of the heaven and the earth it is sure, even as it is a fact that ye are speaking.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcxcix{%
Hath there come Unto thee the story of Ibrahim's honoured guests?\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcc{%
When they came in Unto him, and said:'peace!' he said: 'peace'! - people unknown.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcci{%
Then he turned away privately Unto his household, and brought a calf fatted.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccii{%
And he set it before them, and said: wherefore eat ye not?\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcciii{%
Then he conceived a fear of them. They said: fear not. And they gave him the tidings of a youth knowing.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcciv{%
Then his wife drew near vociferating, and smote her face, and said: an old barren woman!\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccv{%
They said: even so saith thine Lords Verily He! He is the Wise, the Knower.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccvi{%
He said: what then is your errand! O ye sent ones!\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccvii{%
They said: verily we are sent Unto a people, guilty.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccviii{%
That we may send down upon them stones of baked clay.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccix{%
Marked, from before thy Lord, for extravagant.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccx{%
Thus We brought forth from there in who were believers.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxi{%
And We found not therein more than one house of the Muslims.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxii{%
And We left therein a sign for those who fear the afflictive torment.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxiii{%
And in Musa also was a lesson, when We sent him Unto Fir'awn with authority manifest.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxiv{%
Then he turned away with his court, and said: a magician or a madman.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxv{%
Then We laid hold of him and his hosts and flung them into the sea, and he was reproachable.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxvi{%
And in `A-ad also was a lesson, when We sent against them the barren wind.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxvii{%
It left not aught whereon it came but it made it as matter decayed.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxviii{%
And in Thamud's also was a lesson, when it was said Unto them: enjoy yourselves for a season.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxix{%
Then they disdained the command of their Lord; wherefore the bolt laid hold of them even while they looked on.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxx{%
So they were not able to stand, nor could they help themselves.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxi{%
And the people of Nuh We destroyed aforetime; verily they were a people transgressing.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxii{%
And the heaven! We have built it with might, and verily We are powerful.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxiii{%
And the earth! We have stretched it forth beneath; an excellent Spreader are We!\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxiv{%
And of every thing We have created pairs, that haply ye may remember.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxv{%
Flee therefore Unto Allah; verily I am Unto you from Him a warner manifest.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxvi{%
And set not up another god with Allah; verily I am Unto you from Him a warner manifest.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxvii{%
Likewise, there came not an apostle Unto those before them but they said: a magician or a madman!\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxviii{%
Have they bequeathed its Unto each other! Nay! they are a people contumacious.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxix{%
So turn away thou from them, not thou art blameworthy.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxx{%
And admonish, for verily admonition profiteth the believers.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxi{%
And have not created the Jinn and mankind but that they should worship Me.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxii{%
I seek not any provision from them, nor I desire that they should feed Me.\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxiii{%
Verily Allah! He is the Provider, Owner of power, Firm.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxiv{%
So verily Unto those who do wrong there is a portion like Unto the portion of their fellows; wherefore let them not ask Me to hasten on.\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxv{%
Woe, then, Unto those who disbelieve in their Day which they are promised.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxvi{%
\basmalahen By the mount.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxvii{%
By the book inscribed.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxviii{%
In parchment unrolled.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxxxix{%
By the House Frequented.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxl{%
By the roof elevated.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxli{%
By the sea overflowing.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlii{%
Verily the torment of thine Lord is sure to befalls\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxliii{%
Of it there is no averter.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxliv{%
On the Day whereon the heaven will shake with an awful shaking.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlv{%
And the mountains will move away with an awful movement.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlvi{%
Woe, then, will be on that Day to the beliers\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlvii{%
Those who in wading sport themselves.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlviii{%
On the Day whereon they will be pushed into Hell-Fire with a dreadful push.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxlix{%
This is the Fire which ye were wont to believe.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccl{%
Is this magic? or ye still see not clearly!\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccli{%
Roast therein; endure it or endure it not, thereof it is equal Unto you. Ye are only being requited for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclii{%
Verily the God-fearing will bein Gardens and Delight.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccliii{%
Rejoicing in that which their Lord hath vouchsafed Unto them; and their Lord will protect them from the torment of the Flame.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccliv{%
Eat and drink with relish for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclv{%
Reclining on couches ranged. And We shall couple them with maidens wide eyed.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclvi{%
And those who believe and whose progeny follow them in belief. We shall cause their progeny to join them, and We shall not diminish Unto them aught of their own work. Every man is for that which he hath earned a pledge.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclvii{%
And We shall increasingly give them fruit and meat such as they desire.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclviii{%
They will therein snatch from one another a cup; therein will be neither vain babble nor sin.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclix{%
And there will go round on them youths appointed to attend them as though they were pearls hidden.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclx{%
And they will advance Unto each other asking questions.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxi{%
They will say: verily we were aforetime, midst our household, ever in dread.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxii{%
Wherefore Allah hath obliged us, and hath protected us from the torment of the Scorch.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxiii{%
Verily we were wont to pray Unto Him aforetime; verily He! it is He, the Benign, the Merciful.'\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxiv{%
Wherefore admonish thou! thou art not, by the grace of thy Lord, a soothsayer or a madman.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxv{%
Or say they: a poet for whom we wait some adverse turn of fortune!\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxvi{%
Say thou: waits verily I am, with you, among the waiters.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxvii{%
Enjoin them their understandings to this? or are they a people conumacious?\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxviii{%
Or say they: he hath fabricated it: aye they will not believe.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxix{%
Let them bring a discourse like thereUnto, if they say sooth.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxx{%
Have they not been created by aught, or are they the creators?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxi{%
Created they the heavens and the earth! Aye! they will not be convinced.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxii{%
Are with them the treasures of thy Lord! or are they the dispensers?\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxiii{%
Have they a stairway whereby they overhear? Then let their listener bring an authority manifest.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxiv{%
Hath He daughters and ye sons?\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxv{%
Or askest thou a hire from them so that they are with debt laden?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxvi{%
Is with them the Unseen, and they write it down!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxvii{%
Seek they to lay a plot? Then those who disbelieve it is they who shall be plotted against.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxviii{%
Is theirs a god beside Allah? Hallowed be Allah from that which they associate!\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxix{%
And if they should see a fragment of the heaven falling down, they would say: it is only clouds piled up.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxx{%
Wherefore let them alone, till they meet their Day whereon they shall swoon.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxi{%
A Day whereon their plotting will avail them not at all, nor will they be succoured.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxii{%
And verily for those who do wrong there is a torment before that; but most of them know not.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxiii{%
And wait thou patiently the judgment of thy Lord; verily thou art before Our eyes; and hallow the praise of thy Lord when thou uprisest.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxiv{%
And in the night also hallow Him, and at the setting of the stars.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxv{%
\basmalahen By the star when it setteth.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxvi{%
Your companion hath not gone astray, nor hath he erred.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxvii{%
And he speaketh not of his own desire.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxviii{%
It is but a revelation revealed.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcclxxxix{%
One of mighty powers hath taught it him.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxc{%
One strong of make. Then he stood straight.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxci{%
While he was on the uppermost horizon.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcii{%
Thereafter he drew nigh, then he let himself down.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxciii{%
Till he was two bows length off or yet nearer.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxciv{%
Thus He revealed Unto His bondman whatsoever He revealed.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcv{%
The heart lied not in that which he saw.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcvi{%
Will ye therefore dispute with him concerning that which he hath Seen?\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcvii{%
And assuredly he saw him at another descent.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcviii{%
Nigh Unto the lote-tree at the boundary.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccxcix{%
Nigh thereto is the Garden of Abode.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccc{%
When that covered the lote-tree which covered it.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccci{%
The sight turned not aside, nor it exceeded.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccii{%
Assuredly he beheld of the sign of his Lord, the greatest.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccciii{%
Have ye then considered Al-Lat and AL-'uzza:\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdccciv{%
And Manat the other third?\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccv{%
What!-Unto YOu the males and Unto Him the females?\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccvi{%
That indeed is a division unfair!\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccvii{%
They are but names which ye have named, ye and your fathers, for which Allah hath sent down no authority. They follow but their fancy, and that which pleaseth their souls; whereas assuredly there hath come Unto them from their Lord the guidance.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccviii{%
Shall man have whatsoever he wisheth for!\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccix{%
Allah's is the last and the first.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccx{%
And many soever are angels in the heavens whose intercession shall not avail at all save after Allah hath given leave for whomsoever He listeth and pleaseth.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxi{%
Verily those who believe not in the Hereafter name the angels with the names of females.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxii{%
And they have no knowledge thereof; they follow but a vain opinion, and verily a vain opinion attaineth not aught of the truth.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxiii{%
Wherefore withdraw thou from him who turneth away from Our admonition and seeketh not but the life of the world.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxiv{%
That is their highest point of knowledge. Verily thine Lord! it is He Who is the Best Knower of him who strayeth from His way, and He is the Best Knower of him who letteth himself be guided.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxv{%
And Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, that He may recompense those who do evil for that which they worked and reward those who do good with good.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxvi{%
They are those who avoid enormities of sin and abominations save the minor offences. Verily thy Lord is of vast for giveness: He is Best Knower of you when He produced you out Of the earth, and when ye were embryos in the bellies of your mothers. So justify not yourselves; He is the Best Knower of him who feareth Him.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxvii{%
Observedest thou him who turned away?\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxviii{%
And gave little, and then stopped?\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxix{%
Is with him knowledge of the unseen so that he seeth?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxx{%
Hath he not been told of that which is in the writs of Musa.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxi{%
And of Ibrahim who faithfully fulfilled?\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxii{%
To wit, that a burthened soul shall not bear the burthen of another.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxiii{%
And that for man shall be naught save that wherefor he endeavoureth.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxiv{%
And that his endeavour shall be presently observed.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxv{%
Thereafter he shall be recompensed therefor with the fullest recompense.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxvi{%
And that Unto thy Lord is the goal.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxvii{%
And that it is He Who causeth to laugh and causeth to weep.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmdcccxxviii{%
And that it is He Who causeth to die and causeth to live.\qt@no{(44)}}%
