Nought but the saying: peace! peace!\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmvi{%
And the fellows on the right hand; how be happy shall the fellows on the right hand be!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmvii{%
Midst lote-trees thornless.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmviii{%
And plantains laden with fruit.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmix{%
And a shade ever-spread.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmx{%
And water everflowing.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxi{%
And fruit abundant.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxii{%
Neither ending nor forbidden.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxiii{%
And carpets raised.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxiv{%
Verily We! We have created those maidens by a creation.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxv{%
And have made them virgins.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxvi{%
Loving, of equal age.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxvii{%
For the fellows on the right hand.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxviii{%
A multitude from the ancients.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxix{%
And a multitude from the later generations.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxx{%
And the fellows on the left hand; how miserable Shall the fellows on the left hand be!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxi{%
Amidst scorching wind and scalding water.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxii{%
And the shade of black smoke.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxiii{%
Neither cool nor pleasant.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxiv{%
Verily they have been heretofore affluent.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxv{%
And they have been persisting in the heinous offence.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxvi{%
And they were wont to say: when we have died and become dust and bones, shall we, then, verily be raised?\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxvii{%
We and our fathers of old?\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxviii{%
Say thou: verily the ancients and those of later generations:\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxix{%
Are going to be assembled on the appointed time of a Day Known.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxx{%
Then verily ye, O ye erring, denying people.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxi{%
Shall surely eat of the tree of Az-Zqqum.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxii{%
And shall fill therewith your bellies.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxiii{%
And shall be drinkers thereon of boiling water.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxiv{%
Drinkers even as the drinking of thirsty camels.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxv{%
This shall be their entertainment on the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxvi{%
We! it is We Who created you: wherefore confess ye not?\qt@no{(57)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxvii{%
Behold! - that which ye emit.\qt@no{(58)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxviii{%
Create him ye, or are We the Creator?\qt@no{(59)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxxxix{%
We! it is We Who have decreed death Unto you all. And We are not to be outrun.\qt@no{(60)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxl{%
That We may substitute others like Unto you and produce you into that which ye know not.\qt@no{(61)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxli{%
And assuredly ye have fully known the first Production Wherefore heed ye not?\qt@no{(62)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlii{%
Behold! - that which ye sow.\qt@no{(63)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxliii{%
Cause it ye to grow, or are We the Grower?\qt@no{(64)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxliv{%
If We willed, surely We would make it chaff, so that ye would be left wondering.\qt@no{(65)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlv{%
Verily we are undone.\qt@no{(66)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlvi{%
Aye! we are deprived!\qt@no{(67)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlvii{%
Behold! - the water which ye drink:\qt@no{(68)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlviii{%
Send it down ye from the raincloud, or are We the Sender down?\qt@no{(69)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxlix{%
If We willed, surely We would make it brackish. Wherefore give ye not thanks?\qt@no{(70)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmml{%
Behold! - the fire which ye strike out:\qt@no{(71)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmli{%
Produce ye the tree thereof, or are We the Producer?\qt@no{(72)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlii{%
We! it is We Who made it a reminder and a provision Unto the campers.\qt@no{(73)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmliii{%
Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty.\qt@no{(74)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmliv{%
I swear by the setting of the stars -\qt@no{(75)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlv{%
And verily that is a mighty oath, if ye but knew!\qt@no{(76)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlvi{%
That it is a Recitation honourable.\qt@no{(77)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlvii{%
In a Book Hidden.\qt@no{(78)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlviii{%
Which none can touch except the purified.\qt@no{(79)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlix{%
It is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(80)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlx{%
Is it this discourse that ye hold lightly?\qt@no{(81)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxi{%
And make it your provision that ye should belie it?\qt@no{(82)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxii{%
Wherefore then - when the soul cometh up to the wind-pipe -\qt@no{(83)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxiii{%
And ye are then looking on.\qt@no{(84)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxiv{%
And We are nigher Unto him than ye are, but ye behold not-\qt@no{(85)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxv{%
Wherefore then, if ye are not to be requited\qt@no{(86)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxvi{%
Cause ye it not to return, if ye say sooth?\qt@no{(87)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxvii{%
Then if he be of the broughtnigh.\qt@no{(88)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxviii{%
For him shall be comfort, and fragrance and a Garden of Delight.\qt@no{(89)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxix{%
And if he be of the fellows on the right hand,\qt@no{(90)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxx{%
Then: peace Unto thee, for thou art of those on the right hand.\qt@no{(91)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxi{%
And if he be of the beliers, the erring,\qt@no{(92)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxii{%
Then an entertainment of boiling water.\qt@no{(93)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxiii{%
And roasting in a Blaze.\qt@no{(94)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxiv{%
Verily this! this is the very truth.\qt@no{(95)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxv{%
Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty!\qt@no{(96)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxvi{%
\basmalahen Whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth halloweth Allah; and He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxvii{%
His is the dominion of the heavens and the earth; He giveth life and He causeth to die; and He is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxviii{%
He is the First and the Last, and the OutWard and the inward, and He is of everything the Knower.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxix{%
He it is Who created the heavens and the earth in six days; then He established Himself on the Throne. He knoweth whatsoever plungeth into the earth and whatsoever cometh forth therefrom, and whatsoever descendeth from the heaven and whatsoever ascendeth thereto; and He is with you wheresoever ye be. And Allah is of whatsoever ye work a Beholder.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxx{%
His is the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and Unto Allah will all affairs be brought back.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxi{%
He plungeth the night into the day, and plungeth the day into the night, and He is the Knower of whatsoever is in the breasts.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxii{%
Believe in Allah and His apostle, and expend of that whereof He hath made you successors to. Those of you who believe and expend - theirs shall be a great hire.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxiii{%
And what aileth you that ye believe not in Allah whereas the apostle is calling you to believe in your Lord, and He hath already taken your bond, if ye are going to be believers?\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxiv{%
He it is Who sendeth down Unto His bondman manifest signs that He may bring you forth from darknesses into the light; and verily Allah is Unto you Tender, Merciful.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxv{%
And what aileth you that ye expend not in the way of Allah, when Allah's shall be the inheritance of the heavens and the earth! Those among you who expended and fought before the victory shall not be held equal They are mightier in rank than those who expended and fought afterwards; Unto each hath Allah promised good; and Allah is of whatsoever ye work Aware.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxvi{%
Who is he that will lend Allah a goodly loan, so that He may multiply it for him, and his shall be a hire honourable?\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxvii{%
Mention the Day whereon thou shalt see the believing men and believing women, their light running before them and on their right hands: glad tidings Unto you To-day: Gardens whereunder rivers flow, abiders therein they will be. That! it is the mighty achievement.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxviii{%
It shall be the Day whereon the hypocritical men and hypocritical women will say Unto those who believe: wait for us that we may borrow some of your light. Then betwixt them there will be set a high wall, wherein will be a door, the inside whereof hath mercy, while the outside thereof is toward the torment.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmlxxxix{%
They will cry unto them: have we not been with you? They will say: 'yea! but ye tempted your souls, and ye Waited, and ye dubitated, and your vain desires beguiled you until the affair of Allah came, and in respect to Allah the beguiler beguiled you.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxc{%
To-day therefore no ransom will be accepted of you nor of those who openly disbelieved; your abode is the Fire; that is your companion; a hapless destination.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxci{%
Is not the time yet come unto those who believe, that their hearts should humble themselves to the admonition of Allah and to the truth which hath come down, and that they become not as those who were vouchsafed the Book aforetime, and the time become extended unto them, and so their hearts became hard? And many of them are transgressors\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcii{%
Know that Allah quickeneth earth after the death thereof. Surely We have propounded unto you the signs, that haply ye may reflect.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxciii{%
Verily the alms-giving men and alms-giving women--and they are lending unto Allah a goodly lone--it shall be multiplied for them and theirs shall be a hire honourable.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxciv{%
And those who believe in Allah and His apostles - those! they are the saints and martyrs in the sight of their Lord; theirs will be their full hire and their light. And those who disbelieved and belied Our signs--they shall be the fellows of the Blaze.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcv{%
Know that the life of the world is but a play and a pastime, and an adornment and a self-glorification among you and vying in respect of riches and children; as the likeness of vegetation after rains whereof the growth pleaseth the husbandmen, then it withereth and thou seest it becoming yellow, then it becometh chaff. And in the Hereafter there is both a grievous torment and forgiveness from Allah and His pleasure, and the life of the world is but a vain bauble.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcvi{%
Strive with one another in hastening toward forgiveness from your Lord and toward a Garden whereof the width is as the width of the heavens and the earth, gotten ready for those who beiieve in Allah and His apostles. This is the grace of Allah; He vouchsafeth It Unto whomsoever He will; and Allah is Owner of mighty grace.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcvii{%
Naught of distress befalleth the earth or your persons but it is inscribed in the Book even before We have created them. Verily with Allahs that is easy.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcviii{%
This is announced lest ye sorrow for the sake of that which hath escaped you, or exult over that which He hath vouchsafed Unto you: And Allah loveth not any vainglorious boaster:\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmxcix{%
Ihey who are niggardly and command mankind to niggardliness. And whosoever turneth away, then verily Allah! He is the Self-sufficient, the praise-worthy.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmc{%
Assuredly We sent Our apostles with evidences, and We sent down With them the book and the balance, that people might observe equity. And We sent down iron wherein is great violence and also advantages Unto mankind, and that Allah may know him who succoureth Him, unseen, and His apostles. Verily Allah is Strong, Mighty.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmci{%
And assuredly We sent Nuh and Ibrahim, and We placed in the posterity of the twain the prophecy and the Book. Then of them some are guided ones, and many of them are transgressors.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcii{%
Thereafter in their footsteps We caused Our apostles to follow, and We caused lsa, son Of Maryam, to follow them, and We vouchsafed Unto him the Injil, and We placed In the hearts of those who followed him tenderness and mercy. And asceticism! they innovated it- We prescribed it not for them Only seeking Allah's pleasure yet they tended it not with tendence due thereto. So We vouchsafed Unto such of them as believed their hire, and many of them are transgressors.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmciii{%
O ye who believe! fear Aliah and believe in His apostle; He will vouch safe Unto you two portions of His mercy and will appoint for you a light wherewith ye will walk, and He will forgive you. And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmciv{%
This He will award that the people of the Book may know that they control naught of the grace of Allah, and that the grace is in Allah's hand; He vouchsafeth it Unto whomsoever He wilt, And Allah is Owner of mighty grace.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcv{%
\basmalahen Of a surety Allah hath heard the saying of her that disputed with thee concerning her husband and bewailed Unto Allah; and Allah hath heard your mutual discourse. Verlly Allah Is Hearing, Beholding.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcvi{%
As to those among you who put away their wives by pronouncing zihar their mothers they are not. Their mothers are but those who gave them birth; and verily they utter a saying disputable and false. And verily Allah is Pardoning, Forgiving.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcvii{%
Those who put away their wives by pronouncing zihar and thereafter would retract that which they have said, then upon them is the freeing of a slave before the twain touch each other. That is that wherewith ye are exhorted; and Allah is of whatsoever ye work Aware.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcviii{%
And whosoever findeth not a slave to free on him is the fasting for two months in succession before the twain touch each other, and on him who is not able to do so is the feeding of sixty needy ones. That is in order that ye may believe in Allah and His apostle; and these are the ordinances of Allah. And for the infidels is a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcix{%
Verily those who oppose Allah and His apostle shall be abased even as those before them were abased; and of a surety We have sent down manifest signs. And for the infidels will be a torment ignominious.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcx{%
On the Day whereon Allah will raise them all together and declare Unto them that which they have worked. Allah hath taken count thereof, whilst they forget it. And Allah is over everything a Witness.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxi{%
Observest thou not that Allah knoweth whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth! There is no whispering among three but He is their fourth, nor among five but He is their sixth, nor fewer than that nor more but He is with them wheresoever they may be; and thereafter He will declare Unto them, on the Day of Judgment, that which they have worked. Verily Allah is of everything Knower.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxii{%
Observest thou not those who were forbidden whispering and they afterwards returned to that which they had been forbidden; and they whisper Unto each Other of sin, transgression and disobedience reward the apostle! And when they came Unto thee, they greet thee with that wherewith Allah greeteth thee not, and say within themselves: wherefore god tormented us not for that which we say? Sufficient Unto them is Hell, where in they will roast: a hapless destination!\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxiii{%
O ye who believe! when ye whisper together, whisper not of sin, transgression and disobedience toward the apostle; but whisper for virtue and piety. And fear Allah Unto Whom ye will be gathered.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxiv{%
Whisper is only from the Satan that he may grieve those who believe; and he can harm them not at all save with the leave of Allah. Wherefore in Allah let the believers trust.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxv{%
O ye who believe! when it is said Unto you: make room in your assemblies, then make room; Allah will make room for you. And when it is said: rise up, then rise up; Allah will exalt those who believe among you and those who are vouchsafed knowledge, in degrees. And Allah is of whatsoever ye work Aware.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxvi{%
O ye who believe! when ye go to whisper with the apostle, offer alms before your whispering; that is better for you and purer. Then if ye find not the wherewith, then verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxvii{%
Shrink ye at your offering the alms before your whispering! Then, when ye could do it not, and Allah relented toward you, establish prayer and pay the poor-rate and obey Allah and His apostle. And Allah is Aware of that which ye work.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxviii{%
Beholdest thou not those who take for friends a people with whom Allah is angered? They are neither of you nor of them, and they swear to a lie while they know.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxix{%
Allah hath gotten ready for them a torment grievous; verily vile is that which they have been working.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxx{%
They have taken their oaths as a shield, and they have hindered others from the way of Allah; wherefore theirs shall be a torment ignominious.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxi{%
There will not avail them against Allah their riches or their children at all. Th are the fellows of the Fire; therein they will be abiders.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxii{%
This shall befall on a Day whereon Allah shall raise them all together; then they will swear Unto Him even as they swear Unto you, deeming themselves up on aught. Lo! verily they! they are the liars.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxiii{%
The Satan hath overpowered them, and so hath caused them to forget the remembrance of Allah. These are the band of the Satan. Lo! verily it is the Satan's band that shall be the losers.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxiv{%
Verily those; who oppose Allah and His apostle - they are among the lowest.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxv{%
Allah hath prescribed: surely shall overcome, and My apostles. Verily Allah is strong, Mighty.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxvi{%
Thou shalt not find a people who believe in Allah and the Last Day befriending those who oppose Allah and His apostle, even though they be their fathers or their sons or their brethren or their kindred. These! He hath inscribed faith on their hearts and hath strengthened them with a spirit from Him: and He shall make them enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow as abiders therein. Allah is well pleased with them, and they are well pleased with Him. These are Allah's band. Lo! verily it is the Allah's band that are the blissful.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxvii{%
\basmalahen Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth halloweth Allah, and He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxviii{%
He it is that drave forth those of the people of the Book who disbelieved from their homes at the first gathering, Ye imagined no that they would go -forth; and they imagined that their fortresses would protect them against Allah. Wherefore Allah came upon them whence they reckoned not, and cast terror in their hearts so that they made their houses desolate with their own hands and the hands of the believers. So learn a lesson. O ye endued with insight!\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxix{%
And had not Allahg prescribed banishment for them, surely He would have tormented them in the world; and theirs in the Hereafter is the torment of the Fire.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxx{%
That is because they opposed Allah and His apostle, and whosoever opposeth Allah, then verily Allah is Stern in chastisement.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxi{%
Whatsoever fine palms ye cut down or left standing on roots there of, it was by the leave of Allah, and in order that He might abase the transgressors.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxii{%
And as to that which Allah restored Unto His apostle from them, ye rushed neither horse nor camel upon it but Allah giveth His apostles mastery over whomsoever He will. And Allah Is -over everything potent.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxiii{%
Whatsoever Allah may restore Unto His apostle from the people of the cities is due Unto Allah and Unto the apostle and Unto the near of kin and the orphans and the needy and the wayfarer, so that it may not be confined to the rich among you. And whatsoever the apostle giveth you, take; and whatsoever he forbiddeth you, refrain from. And fear Allah; verily Allah is Stern in chastisement.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxiv{%
And it is due Unto the poor Muhajirs who have been driven forth from their homes and their substance, seeking grace from Allah and His goodwill and succouring Allah and His apostle. These! they are the truthful.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxv{%
And it is also due Unto those who are settled in the dwelling and the faith before them, loving those who have migrated Unto them, and finding in their breasts no desire for that which hath been given them, and preferring them above themselves even though there was want amongst them. And whosoever is Preserved from covetousness of his soul, then those! - they are the blissful.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxvi{%
And it is also due Unto those who came after them, saying: 'Our Lord! forgive us and our brethren who have preceded us in the faith, and place not in our hearts any rancour toward those who had believed. Our Lord! verily Thou art Tender, Merciful.'\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxvii{%
Beholdest thou not: those who dissemble saying Unto their brethren who disbelieve among the people of the Book: if ye are driven forth we shall surely go forth with you, and we, shall not ever obey anyone in your respect, and if ye are attacked, we shall surely succour you. And Allah beareth witness that surely they are liars.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxviii{%
Surely if they are driven forth, they shall not; go forth with them, and surely if they are attacked, they shall succour them, not, and even ifs they succoured them they would turn their backs; and then they shall not be succoured.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxxxix{%
Surely ye are more awful in their breasts than Allah. That is because they are a people who understand not.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxl{%
They shall not fight against you, not even together, except in fenced townships or from behind walls. Their violence among themselves is strong; thou deemest them enjoined, whereas their hearts are diverse. That is because they are a people who reflect not.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxli{%
They are like those a little before them; they tasted the ill-effect of their affair, and theirs shall be a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlii{%
They are like the Satan, when he saith Unto man: 'disbelieve,' then, when he disbelieveth, saith: verily I am quit of thee, verily I fear Allah, the Lord of the Worlds.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxliii{%
Wherefore the end of the twain will be that they will be in the Fire, as abiders there in; that is the meed of the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxliv{%
O ye who believe! fear Allah, and let every soul look to that which it sendeth forward for the morrow. And fear Allah; veril Allah is Aware of that which ye work.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlv{%
And be not as those who forgot Allah, wherefore He caused them to forget their own souls. Those! they are the transgressors.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlvi{%
Not equal are the fellows of the Fire and the fellows of the Garden. Fellows of the Garden! they are the achievers!\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlvii{%
Had We sent down this Qur'an upon a mountain, thou wouldst surely have seen it humbling itself and cleaving in sunder for fear of Allah. Such similitudes We propound Unto mankind that haply they may reflect.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlviii{%
He is Allah, there is no God but He; Knower of the unseen and the seen. He is the Compassionate, the Merciful.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxlix{%
He is Allah, there is no God but He, the Sovereign, the Holy, the Author of Safety, the Giver of Peace, the Protector, the Mighty, the Mender, the Majestic. Hallowed be Allah from all that they associate!\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcl{%
He is Allah, the Creator, the Maker, the Fashioner; His are the excellent names. Him halloweth whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth, and He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcli{%
\basmalahen O ye who believe! take not Mine enemy and your enemy for friends, showing affection toward them, whilst they of a surety disbelieve in that which hath come Unto you of the truth, and have driven forth the apostle and yourselves because ye believe in Allah, your Lord, if ye have come forth to strive in My way and to seek My goodwill. Ye secretly show them affection, while I am best Knower of that which ye conceal and that which ya make known! And whosoever of you doth this, he hath surely strayed from the straight path.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclii{%
Should they come upon you, they will be enemies Unto you and will stretch out against you their hands and their tongues with evil; and fain would they that ye should disbelieve.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcliii{%
There will profit you neither your kindred nor your children on the Day of Resurrection. He shall decide between; and Allah is of that which ye you work Beholder.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcliv{%
Surely there hath been an excellent pattern for you in Ibrahim and those with him, when they said Unto their people; verily we are quit of you and of that which ye worship beside Allah; we renounce you; and surely there hath appeared between us and you hostility and hatred for evermore until ye believe in Allah alone, - except the saying of Ibrahim Unto his father: surely I shall beg forgiveness for thee, and I have no power with Allah for thee at all. Our Lord! in Thee we put our trust, and Unto Thee we turn, and Unto Thee is the journeying.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclv{%
Our Lord! make us not a trial for those who disbelieve, and forgive us, our Lord! verily Thou! Thou art the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclvi{%
Assuredly there hath been in them for you an excellent pattern-for him who hopeth for Allah and the last Day. And whosoever turneth away, then verily Allah! He is the Self-sufficient, the Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclvii{%
Belike Allah may appoint between you and those of them whom ye hold as enemies affection. And Allah is Potent, and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclviii{%
Allah forbiddeth you not that ye should deal benevolently and equitably with those who fought not against you on accouct of religion nor drave you out from your homes; verily Allah loveth the equitable,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclix{%
Allah only forbiddeth you with regard to those who fought against you on account of religion and drave you out from your homes and helped in driving you out, that ye should befriend them. And whosoever shall befriend them, then those! they are the wrong-doers.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclx{%
O ye who believe! when believing women come Unto you as emigrants examine them. Allah is the best Knower of their faith. Then if ye know them to be true believers, send them not back Unto the infidels; they are not lawful Unto them, nor are they lawful Unto them. And give them that which they have expended. Nor is it any crime in you if ye marry them when ye have given their hires. And hold not to the ties of the infidel women, and ask back that which ye have expended, and let them ask back that which they have expended. That is the judgment of Allah; He judgeth between you, And Allah is Knowing, Wise.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxi{%
And if any of your wives hath been left with the infidels, and then ye have retaliated, then give Unto those whose wives have gone away the like of that which they have expended, and fear Allah in whom ye are believers.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxii{%
O Prophet! when believing women come Unto thee swearing fealty Unto thee, that they shall not associate aught with Allah, nor they shall steal, nor they shall commit fornication, nor they shall slay their children, nor they shall produce any falsehood that they have fabricated between their hands and feet, nor they shall disobey thee in anything reputable, then accept thou their fealty, and pray to Allah for their forgiveness. Verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxiii{%
O ye who believe! befriend not a people against whom Allah is Wroth. Surely they have despaired of tHe Hereafter even as have despaired the entombed of the infidels. S\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxiv{%
\basmalahen Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth halloweth Allah. And He is the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxv{%
O ye who believe! wherefore say ye that which ye do not?\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxvi{%
Most odious it is Unto Allah that ye should Say that which ye do not.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxvii{%
Verily Allah loveth those who fight in His way drown up in ranks, as though they were a structure well compacted.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxviii{%
And recall what time Musa said Unto his people: O my people! wherefore hurt ye me, When surely ye know that verily I am Allah's apostle Unto you! Then when they sweryed, Allah made their hearts swerve; and Allah guideth not a transgressing people.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxix{%
And recall what time Isa, son of Maryam, said: children of Israi'l! verily I am Allah's apostle Unto you, confirming the Taurat which was before me, and giving the glad tidings of an apostle who cometh after me: his name will be Ahmad. Then when he brought Unto them evidences, they said: this is magic manifest.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxx{%
And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who fabricateth against Allah a lie even as he is summoned Unto Islam? And Allah guideth not a wrongdoing people.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxi{%
Fain would they extinguish the light of Allah is with their mouths and Allah is going to perfect His light, even though averse may be the infidels.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxii{%
He it is Who hath sent His apostle with the guidance and the true religion, that He may make it triumph over all religion, even though averse may be associaters.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxiii{%
O ye who believe! shall direct you to a merchandise that will deliver you from a torment afflictive?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxiv{%
It is that ye should believe in Allah and His apostle and strive in the way of Allah with your riches and Your lives That is best for you, if ye only knew!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxv{%
He will forgive you your sins, and make YOu enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow, and happy abodes in Gardens Everlasting. That is the mighty achievement.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxvi{%
And also another blessing which ye love: succour from Allah and a speedy victory. And bear thou the glad tidings Unto the believers.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxvii{%
O ye who believe! be Allah's helpers, even as 'Isa, son of Maryam, said Unto the disciples: who shall be my helpers Unto Allah? The disciples said: we are Allah's helpers. Then a part of the Children of Israil believed, and part disbelieved. Then We strengthened those who believed against their foe; wherefore they became triumphant.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxviii{%
\basmalahen Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth halloweth Allah, the Sovereign, the Holy, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxix{%
He it is Who hath raised amdist the unlettered ones an apostle from among themselves, rehearsing Unto them His revelations and purifying them and teaching them the Book and Wisdom, though they have been aforetime in error manifest.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxx{%
And also others of them who have not yet joined them. And He is the Mighty; the Wise.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxi{%
That is the grace of Allah: He vouchsafeth it on whomsoever He will. And Allah is the Owner of mighty Grace.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxii{%
The likeness of those who were laden with the Taurat and then they bare it not, is as the likeness of the ass bearing tomes. Hapless is the likeness of the people who belie the signs of Allah. And Allah guideth not a wrong doing people. J\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxiii{%
Say thou: O ye e who are Judaised! if ye imagine at ye are the friends of Allah above mankind, then wish for death if ye be truthful.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxiv{%
And they will never wish there for, because of that which their hands have sent forward. And Allah is the Knower of he wrong-doers.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxv{%
Say thou: verily the death which ye flee from! then verily it will meet you and thereafter ye will be brought back Unto the Knower of the unseen and the seen, and He will declare Unto you that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxvi{%
O ye who believe! when the call to prayer is made on the day of Friday then repair Unto the remembrance of Allah and leave off bargaining. That is better for you if ye know\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxvii{%
Then, when the prayer is ended, disperse in the land and seek of Allah's grace, and remember Allah much, that haply ye may thrive.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxviii{%
And when they beheld merchandise or sport, they flocked thereto, and left thee standing. Say thou: that which is with Allah is better than sport and better than merchandise; and Allah is the Best of providers.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmclxxxix{%
\basmalahen When the hypocrites come Unto thee, they say: we bear witness that thou art indeed the apostle of Allah. Allah knoweth that thou art indeed His apostle, and Allah beareth witness that; the hypocrites are indeed liars.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxc{%
They have taken their oaths for a shield; then they turn away men from the way of Allah. Verily vile is that which they have been working.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxci{%
That is, because they believed, and thereafter disbelieved, wherefore their hearts are sealed, so that they understand not.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcii{%
And when thou beholdest them, their persons please thee: and if they speak, thou listenest to their discourse; they are as though they were blocks of wood propped up. They deem every shout to be against them. They are the enemy; so beware of them. Perish them Allah! whither are they deviating!\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxciii{%
And when it is said Unto them: come! that the apostle of Allah may ask forgiveness for you, they twist their heads, and thou beholdest them retire, while they are stiff-necked.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxciv{%
Equal it is Unto them: whether thou askest forgiveness for them or askest not forgiveness for them, Allah shall forgive them not. Verily Allah guideth not a transgressing people.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcv{%
They are the ones who say: expend not on those who are with Allah's apostle, that they may disperse; whereas Allah's are the treasures of the heavens and the earth; yet the hypocrites understand not.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcvi{%
They say: surely, if we return to Madina the mightier shall drive out the meaner thence: whereas might is Allah's and His apostle's and the believers; yet the hypocrites know not.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcvii{%
O ye who believe let not your riches or your children divert you from the remembrance of Allah. And whosoever doth that then those! they are the losers.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcviii{%
And expend of that wherewith We have provided you afore death cometh Unto one of you, and he saith: 'my Lord! wouldst Thou not defer me for a short term, so that I would give alms and become of the righteous.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcxcix{%
And Allah deferreth not a soul when its term- hath come; and Allah is Aware of that which ye do.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcc{%
\basmalahen Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth halloweth Allah. His is the dominion; and His is the praise; and He is over everything potent.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcci{%
He it is Who hath created you; then of you some are Infidels and of you some are believers; and Allah is of that which ye Work Beholder.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccii{%
He hath created the heavens and the earth with truth, and hath formed you, and hath made-your forms goodly; and Unto Him Is the return.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcciii{%
He knoweth whatsoever is In the heavens and the earth, and He knoweth whatsoever ye keep secret, and whatsoever ye make known; and Allah is the Knower of whatsoever is in the breasts.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcciv{%
Hath not the tidings reached you of those who disbelieved aforetime, and so tasted the evil consequence of their affair, and theirs will be a torment afflictive?\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccv{%
That was because their apostles were wont to come Unto them with evidences, but they said: shall a mere human bein guide us? Wherefore they disbelieved and turned away; and Allah needed them not. And Allah is Self Sufficient, Praiseworthy.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccvi{%
Those who dlsbelieve assert that they shall not be raised. Say thou 'Yea! by my Lord, ye shall surely be raised, and then Unto you shall be declared that which ye have worked; and that is for Allah easy.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccvii{%
Wherefore believe in Allah and His apostle and the Light which We have sent down: And Allah is of that which ye work Aware.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccviii{%
Remember the Day whereon He shall assemble you, the Day of Assembly; that shall be the Day of Mutual Loss and Gain. And whosoever believeth in Allah and worketh righteously from him He will expiate His misdeeds and will make him enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow, as abiders therein for evermore. That is the mighty achievement.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccix{%
And they who disbelieve and belie Our Signs! those shall be fellows of the Fire, as abiders therein; a hapless destination.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccx{%
No calamity befalleth save by Allah's leave. And whosoever believeth in Allah, his heart He guideth. And Allah is of everything Knower.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxi{%
Obey Allah and obey the apostlle; then if ye turn away, on Our apostle is only the preaching manifest.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxii{%
Allah! there is no God but He! In Allah, therefore, let the believers put their trust.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxiii{%
O ye who believe! verily of your wives and your children there is an enemy Unto you; wherefore beware of them. And if ye pardon and pass over and forgive, then verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxiv{%
Your riches and your children are but a temptation; and Allah! with Him is a mighty hire.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxv{%
Wherefore fear Allah as much as ye are able, and hearken and obey, and expend, for the benefit of your souls. And whosoever is protected from niggardliness of his soul - those! they are the blissful.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxvi{%
If ye lend Unto Allah a goodly loan, He will multiply it Unto you and will forgive you; and Allah is Appreciator, Forbearing.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxvii{%
Knower of the unseen and the seen, the Mighty, the Wise.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxviii{%
\basmalahen O Prophet! when ye divorce women, divorce them before their waitrng-period; and count the waiting period; and fear Allah, your Lord. Drive them not out of their houses, nor should they go forth, unless they commit a manifest indecency. These are the bounds of Allah; and whosoever trespasseth the bounds of Allah, hath surely wronged himself. Thou knowest not, that haply Allah may hereafter bring something new to pass.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxix{%
Then when they have attained their term, either retain them reputably, or part from them reputably, and take as witnesses two just men from among you, and set up your testimony for Ailah. Thus is exhorted he who believeth in Allah and the Last Day. And whosoever feareth Allah He maketh for him an outlet.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxx{%
And He provideth for him from whence he reckoneth not upon. And whosoever putteth his trust in Allah He will suffice him. Verily Allah is sure to attain His purpose, and Allah hath appointed Unto everything a measure.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxi{%
And as to such of your women as have despaired of menstruation, if ye be in doubt thereof, their waiting period is three months, as also of those who have not yet menstruated. And as to those with burthens, their term is when they lay down their burthen. And whosoever feareth Allah, He maketh his affair Unto him easy.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxii{%
That is the commandment of Allah which He hath sent down Unto you. And whosoever feareth Allah, He Will expiate his misdeeds from him, and will magnify for him his hire.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxiii{%
Lodge them wheresoever ye lodge yourselves; according to your means; and hurt them not so as to straiten them. And if they are with burthen, expend on them until they lay down their burthen. Then, if they suckle their children for you, give them their hire, and take counsel together reputably. And if ye make hardship for one another, then another woman will suckle for him.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxiv{%
Let the man of means expend according to his means; and whosoever is stinted in his subsistence let him expend of that which Allah hath given him. Allah tasketh not a soul except according to that which He hath vouchsafed it. Anon Allah will appoint after hardship ease.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxv{%
And how many a city trespassed the commandment of its Lord and His apostles! Wherefore We reckoned with them a stern reckoning, and We tormented them With a torment unheard of.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxvi{%
Wherefore they tasted the evil consequence of their affair, and the end of their affair was loss.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxvii{%
Allah hath gotten ready for them a grievous torment; so fear Allah, O men of understanding! those who have believed. Surely He hath sent down Unto you an admonition.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxviii{%
An apostle reciting Unto you the revelations of Allah as evidences, that he may bring forth those who believe and work righteous works from darknesses into light. And whosoever believeth in Allah and worketh righteously, him He will cause to enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow, as abiders for evermore. Surely Allah hath made for him an excellent provision.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxix{%
Allah it is Who hath created seven heavens, and of the earth the like thereof; the commandment cometh down between them, that ye may know that Allah is over everything Potent, and that Allah! He encompasseth everything in knowledge.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxx{%
\basmalahen O prophet! why makest thou unlawful that which Allah hath made lawful Unto thee, seeking the good-will of thy wives! And Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxi{%
Surely Allah hath ordained for you absolution from your oaths; and Allah is your Patron and He is the Knower, the Wise.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxii{%
And recall what time the Prophet confided a story Unto one of his spouses, then she disclosed it, and Allah apprised him thereof, he made known part thereof and Withheld part. Then, when he had apprised her of it, she said: who hath acquainted thee therewith! He said the Knower, the Aware hath acquainted me.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxiii{%
If ye twain turn Unto Allah repentant, it is well, surely your hearts are so inclined, and if ye support each other against him, then verily Allah! his friend is He and Jibril and so are the righteous believers; and furthermore the angels are his aiders.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxiv{%
Belike his Lord, if he divorce you, will give him in exchange wives better than you, Muslims, believers, devout, penitent, worshippers, given to fasting, both non-virgins and virgins.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxv{%
O ye who believe! protect yourselves and your households from a Fire the fuel whereof is mankind and stones, over which are angels, stern, strong; they disobey not Allah in that which He commandeth them, and do that which they are commanded.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxvi{%
O ye who disbelieve! excuse not yourselves To-day; ye are only being requited for that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxvii{%
O ye who believe! turn Unto Allah with a sincere repentance. Belike your Lord will expiate from you your misdeeds and cause you to enter Gardens whereunder rivers flow, on the Day whereon Allah will not humiliate the prophet and those who believe with him. Their light will be running before them and on their right hands, and they will say: our Lord! perfect for us our light, and forgive us; verily Thou art over everything Potent.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxviii{%
O Prophet! strive hard against the infidels and the hypocrites, and be stern Unto them. And their abode is Hell: a hapless destination!\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxxxix{%
Allah propoundeth for those who disbelieve the similitude of the wife of Nuh and the wife of Lut. They were under two of our righteous bondmen; then they defrauded them. Wherefore the twain availed them naught against Allah, and it was said: enter ye twain the Fire with those who enter.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxl{%
And Allah propoundeth for those who believe the similitude of the wife Of Fir'awn, when she said: 'my Lord! build me in Thine presence a house in the Garden, and deliver me from Fir'awn and his handiwork, and deliver me from the transgressing people.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxli{%
And the similitude of Maryram daughter of lmran, who preserved her chastity, wherefore We breathed in it Of Our Spirit. And she testified to the words of her Lord and His Books and she was of the devout.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlii{%
\basmalahen Blest be He in whose hand is the dominion, and He is over everything Potent.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxliii{%
Who hath created death and life that He might prove you, as to which of you is excellent in work. And He is the Mighty, the Forgiver.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxliv{%
Who hath created seven heavens in storeys. Thou shalt not behold in the Compassionates creation any over-sight; then repeat thy look, beholdest thou any crack?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlv{%
Then repeat thy look twice over, and thy look will return Unto thee dim and It will have become wearied out.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlvi{%
And assuredly We have bedecked the nearest heaven with lamps, and We have made them missiles for satans: and for them We have gotten ready the torment of the Blaze.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlvii{%
And for those who disbelieve in their Lord will be the torment of Hell; and a hapless destination!\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlviii{%
When they will be cast thereinto, they will hear thereof a braying even as it balleth up,\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxlix{%
Well-nigh it bursteth with rage. So oft as a company is cast thereinto, the keepers thereof will ask them: came there not Unto you a warner?\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccl{%
They will say: yea! surely there came a warner Unto us, but we belied, and said: God hath not sent down aught, are naught but in a great error.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccli{%
And they will say: had we been wont to hearken or to reflect, we had not been among the fellows of the Blaze.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclii{%
So they shall confess their sin. Far away they-be, the fellows of the Blaze!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccliii{%
Verily those who dread their Lord unseen, theirs shall be forgiveness and a great hire.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccliv{%
And whather ye keep your discourse secret or publish it, verily He is the Knower of that which is in the breasts.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclv{%
Shall not He Who hath created know? And He is the Subtile, the Aware.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclvi{%
He it is Who hath made the earth Unto you subservient, so go forth in the regions thereof, and eat of His provision. And Unto Him is the Resurrection.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclvii{%
Are ye secure that He who is in the heaven will not sink the earth with you and then it should quake?\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclviii{%
Or are ye secure that He Who is in the heaven will not send against you a whirlwind? Anon ye shall know what wise hath been My warning.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclix{%
And assuredly those before them belied; then what wise hath been My wrath!\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclx{%
Behold they not the birds above them, outstretching their wings and they also withdraw them? Naught holdeth them except the Compassionate. Verily He is of everything Beholder.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxi{%
Who. is he that can be an army Unto you and succour you, beside the Compassionate! The infidelsjb are but in delusion.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxii{%
Who is he that can provide for you, should He withhold His provision? Aye! they persists in perverseness and aversion.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxiii{%
Is he, then, who goeth about grovelling upon his face better directed, or he who walketh evenly on a straight path?\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxiv{%
Say thou: He it is who hath brought you forth and hath endowed you with hearing and sights and hearts. Little thanks it is ye give!\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxv{%
Say thou: He it is Who hath spread you over the earth, and Unto Him ye shall be gathered.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxvi{%
And they say: when will this promise be fulfilled, if ye say sooth?\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxvii{%
Say thou: the knowledge is only with Allah, and but a warner manifest.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxviii{%
But when they will behold it proximating sad will be the countenances of those who disbelieve, and it will be said: this is that which ye have been calling for.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxix{%
Say thou: bethink ye if Allah destroy me and those with me; or have mercy on us, who will protect the infidels from a torment afflictive?\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxx{%
Say thou: He is the Compassionate; in Him we have believed, and in Him we have put our trust. -And anon ye will know who it is that is in error manifest.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxi{%
Say thou: bethink ye, were your water to be sunk away, who then could bring you water welling-up?\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxii{%
\basmalahen Nun By the pen and by that which they inscribe.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxiii{%
Thou art nor, through the grace of thy Lord, mad.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxiv{%
And verily thine shall be a hire unending."\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxv{%
And verily thou art of a high and noble disposition.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxvi{%
Anon thou wilt see and they will see:\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxvii{%
Which of you is afflicted with madness.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxviii{%
Verily thy Lord! He is the best Knower of him who strayeth from His path, and He is the best Knower of the guided one,\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxix{%
Wherefore obey not thou the beliers.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxx{%
Fain would they that thou shouldst be pliant, so that they will be pliant.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxi{%
And obey not: thou any swearer ignominous.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxii{%
A defamer, spreader abroad of slander.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxiii{%
Hinderer of the good, trespasser; sinner.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxiv{%
Gross, and therewithal ignoble-\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxv{%
Because he is owner of riches and children.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxvi{%
When Our revelations are rehearsed Unto him, he saith: fables of the ancients.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxvii{%
Anon We shall brand him on snout.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxviii{%
Verily We! We have proved them even as We proved the fellows of a garden when they swarethat they would surely reap it in the morning.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcclxxxix{%
And they made not the exception.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxc{%
Wherefore an encircling visitation visited it even as they slept on.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxci{%
Then in the morning it became as though it had been reaped.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcii{%
Then they cried out Unto each other in the morning,\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxciii{%
Saying: go out betimes to your tilth if ye would reap.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxciv{%
So they went off speaking to each other in a low voice:\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcv{%
Let there not enter upon you today any needy man.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcvi{%
And they went out betimes determined in purpose.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcvii{%
Then when they beheld it, they said: verily we have strayed.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcviii{%
Aye! it is we who are deprived!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccxcix{%
The most moderate of them said: said I not Unto you, wherefore hallow him ye not!\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccc{%
They said: hallowed be Our Lord! verily we have been wrong- doers.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccci{%
Then they turned to each other reproaching\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccii{%
They said: woe Unto us! verily we! we have been arrogant.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccciii{%
Belike our Lord may exchange for us better garden than this; verily we are Unto our Lord beseechers.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccciv{%
Such is the torment. And the torment of the Hereafter is far greater; if they but knew.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccv{%
Verily for the God-fearing, are with their Lord Gardens of Delight.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccvi{%
Shall We then make the Muslims like the culprits?\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccvii{%
What aileth you? How ill ye judge!\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccviii{%
Is there with you a Book wherein ye study:\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccix{%
That therein is yours that which. ye may choose?\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccx{%
Or have ye oaths from us reaching to the Day of Resurrection, that you shall be that which ye judge?\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxi{%
Ask then, which of them will stand thereof a surety?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxii{%
Have they associate gods? Then let them produce their associate gods if they say sooth!\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxiii{%
Remember the Day whereon the shank shall be bared and they shall be called upon to Prostrate themselves, but they shall not be able.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxiv{%
Downcast will be their looks; abjectness will overspread them. Surely they had been called upon to Prostrate themselves while yet they were whole.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxv{%
Let Me alone with him who belieth this discourse; step by step We lead them on when they perceive not.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxvi{%
And I bear with them; verily My contrivance is sure.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxvii{%
Askest thou a hire from them so that they are laden with debt?\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxviii{%
Is with them the unseen, so that they write down?\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxix{%
Be patient thou, then, with thy Lord's judgment, and be thou not like him of the fish, when he cried out while he was in anguish.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxx{%
Had not grace from his Lord reached him, he had surely been cast into the wilderness in a plight.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxi{%
Then his Lord chose him and made him of the righteous.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxii{%
And those who disbelieve well-nigh cause thee to stumble with their looks when they hear the Admonition, and they say: verily he is mad.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxiii{%
While it is naught but an admonition Unto the worlds.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxiv{%
\basmalahen The Inevitable Calamity!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxv{%
What is the Inevitable Calamity?\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxvi{%
And what shall make thee know that which the Inevitable Calamity is.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxvii{%
The tribes of Thamud and 'Aad belied the Striking Day.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxviii{%
As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the outburst.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxix{%
And as for 'Aad they were destroyed by a wind, furious. roaring.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxx{%
To which He subjected them for seven nights and eight days in succession, so that thou mightest have seen men during it lying prostrate, as though they were stumps of palms ruined.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxi{%
Beholdest thou any of them remaining?\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxii{%
And Fir'awn and those before him and the overturned cities committed sin.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxiii{%
And they disobeyed their Lord's apostle, so He laid hold of them with a grip increasing.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxiv{%
Verily We! when the water rose, We bare you upon the traversing ark.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxv{%
That We might make it Unto you an admonition, and thot it might be retained by the retaining ears.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxvi{%
And when the Trumpet shall sound a single blast.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxvii{%
And the earth and the mountains shall be borne and the twain shall be crushed with a single crash.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxviii{%
Then on that Day shall happen the Event.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxxxix{%
And the heaven shall be rent in sunder, it on that Day shall be frail.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxl{%
And the angels shall be on the borders thereof; and on that Day eight shall bear over them the Throne of thy Lord.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxli{%
The Day whereon ye shall be mustered nothing hidden by you shall be hidden.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlii{%
Then as to him who will be vouchsafed his book in his right hand, he shall say: here! read my book!\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxliii{%
Verily I was sure that I should be a meeter of my reckoning.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxliv{%
Then he shall be in a life well-pleasing -\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlv{%
In a Garden lofty.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlvi{%
Clusters whereof shall be near at hand.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlvii{%
Eat and drink with benefit for that which ye sent on beforehand in dayspast.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlviii{%
Then as to him who shall be vouchsafed his book in his left hand, he shall say: Oh! would that I had not been vouchsafed my book.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxlix{%
Nor known whatever was my reckoning!\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccl{%
Oh, would that it had been the ending!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccli{%
My riches have: availed me not;\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclii{%
There hath perished from me my authority.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccliii{%
Lay hold of him and chain him;\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccliv{%
Then in the Scorch roast him\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclv{%
Then, in a chain whereof the length is seventy Cubits, bind him.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclvi{%
Verily he was wont not to believe in Allah, the Mighty.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclvii{%
Nor he urged on others the feeding of the poor.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclviii{%
Wherefore for him here this Day there is no friend.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclix{%
Nor any food save filthy corruption.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclx{%
None shall eat it but the sinners.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxi{%
I swear by that which ye see.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxii{%
And that which ye see not.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxiii{%
That it is surely the speech brought by messenger honourable.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxiv{%
And it is not the speech of a poet. Little it is that ye believe\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxv{%
Nor is it the speech of a sooth- sayer. Little are ye admonished.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxvi{%
It is a Revelation from the Lord of the worlds.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxvii{%
And if he had forged concerning us some discourses.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxviii{%
We surely had lain hold of him by the right hand.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxix{%
And then severed his life-vein.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxx{%
And not one of you would have withheld us from punishing him.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxi{%
And verily it is an Admonition Unto the God-fearing.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxii{%
And verily We! We know that some among you are beliers thereof.\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxiii{%
And verily it shall be an occasion of anguish Unto the infidels.\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxiv{%
And verily it is the truth of assured certainty.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxv{%
Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxvi{%
\basmalahen There hath asked an asker for the torment about to befall.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxvii{%
The infidels, of which there is no averter.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxviii{%
From Allah, Owner of the ascending steps.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxix{%
Whereby the angels ascend Unto Him and also the spirit, On a Day whereof the measure is fifty thousand years.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxx{%
Wherefore be thou patient with a becoming patience.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxi{%
Verily they behold it afar off.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxii{%
And We behold it nigh.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxiii{%
It shall befall on a Day whereon the heaven shall become like Unto dregs of oil.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxiv{%
And then the mountains shall become like Unto wool dyed.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxv{%
And not a friend shall ask a friend,\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxvi{%
Though they shall be made to see one another. Fain would the guilty ransom himself from the torment of that Day by his children.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxvii{%
And his spouse and his brother.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxviii{%
And his kin that sheltered him.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmccclxxxix{%
And all who are on the earth; so that this might deliver him.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxc{%
By no means! Verily it is a Flame.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxci{%
Flaying off the scalp-skin.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcii{%
It shall calll him who turneth back and backslideth.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxciii{%
And masseth and then hoardeth.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxciv{%
Verily man is formed impatient.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcv{%
When evil toucheth him, he is bewailing.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcvi{%
And when good toucheth him he is begrudging.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcvii{%
Not so are the prayerful.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcviii{%
Who are at their prayer constant.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcccxcix{%
And those in whose riches is a known right.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcd{%
For the beggar and the destitute.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdi{%
And those who testify to the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdii{%
And those who are fearful of their Lord's torment -\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdiii{%
Verily the torment of their Lord is not a thing to feel secure from.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdiv{%
And those who of their private parts are guards.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdv{%
Save in regard to their spouses or those whom their right hands own; so verily they are not blameworthy -\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdvi{%
And whosoever seeketh beyond that, then it is those who are the trespassers\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdvii{%
And those who of their trusts and their covenant are keepers.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdviii{%
And those who stand firm in their testimonies.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdix{%
And those who of their prayer are observant.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdx{%
Those shall dwell in Gardens, honoured.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxi{%
What aileth those who disbelieve, toward thee hastening.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxii{%
On the right and on the left, in companies?\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxiii{%
Coveteth every man of them, that he shall enter the Garden of Delight?\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxiv{%
By no means! veriiy We! We have created them from that which they know.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxv{%
I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests, that, vierly We are Able.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxvi{%
To replace them by others better than they; and We are not to be outrun.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxvii{%
Wherefore let thou them alone plunging in vanity and sporting until they meet their Day which they are promised.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxviii{%
The Day whereon they shall come forth from the sepulchres hastily, as though they were to an altar hurrying.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxix{%
Downcast shall be their looks; abjectness shall overspread them. Such is the Day which they are promised.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxx{%
\basmalahen Verily We! We sent Nuh Unto his people saying: warn thy people ere there come Unto them torment afflictive.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxi{%
He said: O my people! verily I am Unto you a warner manifest.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxii{%
Worship Allah, and fear Him, and obey me.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxiii{%
He will forgive you your sins, and will defer you to an appointed term. Verily the term of Allah when it cometh shall not be deferred, if ye but knew.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxiv{%
He said: my Lord! verily have called my people night and day.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxv{%
And my calling hath only increased them in fleeing.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxvi{%
And verily so oft as I call them, that Thou mayest forgive them, they place their fingers into their ears, and wrap themselves with their garments, and persist, and are stiff-necked.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxvii{%
Then verily have called Unto them publicly:\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxviii{%
Then verily spake Unto them openly, and secretly also I addressed them.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxix{%
And I said: ask forgiveness of your Lord; verily He is ever Most Forgiving.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxx{%
He will send the heaven upon you copiously;\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxi{%
And He will add Unto you riches and children and will appoint Unto you gardens and will appoint Unto you rivers.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxii{%
What aileth you that ye expect not in Allah majesty!\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxiii{%
And surely He hath created you by stages.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxiv{%
Behold ye not in what wise Allah hath created seven heavens in storeys.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxv{%
And hath placed the moon therein for a light, and hath made the sun a lamp?\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxvi{%
And Allah hath caused you to grow from the earth as a growth.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxvii{%
And thereafter He will cause you to return thereinto, and He will bring you forth a forthbringing.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxviii{%
And Allah hath made the earth Unto you an expanse.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxxxix{%
That of it ye may traverse the ways open.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxl{%
Nuh said. my Lord! verily they have disobeyed me and followed them whose riches and children have only increased them in loss.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxli{%
And who have plotted a tremendous plot\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlii{%
And who have said: ye shall not leave your gods; nor Shall ye leave Wadd nor Suwa', nor Yaghuth, nor Ya'uq nor Nasr.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxliii{%
And surely they have misled many. And increase Thou these wrong-doers in naught save error.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxliv{%
And because of their misdeeds they were drowned, and then they were made to enter a Fire. Then they found not for themselves, beside Allah, any helpers.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlv{%
And Nuh said: my Lord! leave not upon the earth of the infidels one inhabitant.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlvi{%
Verily if Thou shouldst leave them, they Will mislead Thine bondmen and will beget not save sinning infidels,\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlvii{%
My Lord! forgive me and my parents and him who entereth my house as a believer, and believing men and believing women, and increase not the wrong-doers in aught save ruin!\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlviii{%
\basmalahen Say thou: it hath been revealed Unto me that a company of the Jinn listened, and said, verily we have listened to a Recitation wondrous.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxlix{%
Guiding Unto rectitude; wherefore we have believed therein, and we shall by no means associate with our Lord anyone.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdl{%
And He - exalted be the majesty of our Lord!-hath taken neither a spouse nor a son.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdli{%
And the foolish among us were wont to forge lie against Allah exceedingly.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlii{%
And verily we! we had imagined that humankind and Jinn would never forge against Allah a lie.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdliii{%
And persons among humankind have been seeking refuge with persons of the Jinn, so that they increased them in evil disposition.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdliv{%
And indeed they imagined, even as ye imagined, that Allah will not raise any one.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlv{%
And we sought to reach the heaven; then we found it filled with a strong guard and darting meteors.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlvi{%
And we were wont to sit on seats therein to listen; but whosoever listeneth now findeth for him a dartin meteor in wait.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlvii{%
And we know not whether evil is boded for those who are on the earth, or whether their Lord intendeth for them a right direction.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlviii{%
And of us there are some righteous, and of us are some otherwise; we have been following very diverse.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlix{%
And we known that we cannot frustrate Allah in the earth, nor can we frustrate Him by flight.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlx{%
And when we heard the Message of guidance, we believed therein; and whosoever believeth in his Lord, he shall fear neither diminution nor wrong.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxi{%
And of us some are Muslims, and of us some are deviators. Then whosoever hath embraced Islam - such have endeavoured after a Path of rectitude.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxii{%
And as for the deviators, for Hell they shall be fuel.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxiii{%
And had they kept to the path surely We would have watered them with rain plenteous.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxiv{%
That We might try them there by. And whosoever turneth aside from the remembrance of his Lord, him He shall thrust into a torment vehement.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxv{%
And the prostrations are for Allah; wherefore call not along with Allah anyone.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxvi{%
And when the bondman of Allah stood calling upon Him, they well nigh pressed on him stifling.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxvii{%
Say thou: I simply call upon Allah, and I associate not with Him any-one.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxviii{%
Say thou: 'verily own not for you power of hurt nor of benefit\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxix{%
Say thou: 'verily none can protect me from Allah, nor can I find beside Him any refuge.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxx{%
Mine is but the publishing from Allah and His messages; and whosoever disobeyeth Allah and His apostle, his portion verily is the Hell-Fire as abiders therein for evermore.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxi{%
They shall go on denying until they; behold that which they are promised wherefore then they shall know who were weaker in protectors and fewer in number.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxii{%
Say thou: know not whather that which ye are promised is nigh, or whether my Lord hath appointed for it a distant term.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxiii{%
He is the Knower of the unseen, and He discloseth not His unseen Unto anyone.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxiv{%
Save Unto an apostle chosen. And then He causeth to go before him and behind him a guard.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxv{%
That He may know that they have preached the message of their Lord. And He comprehendeth whatever is with them, and He keepeth count of everything numbered.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxvi{%
\basmalahen O thou enwrapped!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxvii{%
Stay up the night long save a little -\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxviii{%
A half thereof, or abate a little thereof,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxix{%
Or increase thereto. And intone the Qur'an with a measured intontion. s\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxx{%
Verily We! anon We shall cast upon thee a weighty word.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxi{%
Verily the rising by night! it is most curbing and most conducive to right speech.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxii{%
Verily there is for thee by day occupation prolonged.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxiii{%
And remember thou the name of thy Lord, and devote thyself to Him with an exclusive devotion.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxiv{%
Lord of the east and the west! No God is there but He! Wherefore take Him for thy trustee.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxv{%
And bear thou with patience whatsoever they say, and depart from them with a becoming departure.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxvi{%
And let Me alone with the beliers, owners of ease: and respite thou them a little.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxvii{%
Verily with us are heavy fetters and Scorch.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxviii{%
And a food that choketh and a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdlxxxix{%
On a Day whereon the earth and the mountains shall quake, and the mountains shall become a sand-heap poured forth.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxc{%
Verily We! We have sent Unto you an apostle, a witness over you, even as We sent Unto Fir'awn an apostle.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxci{%
Then Fir'awn disobeyed the apostle, wherefore We laid hold of him with a painful hold.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcii{%
How then, if ye disbelieve, shall ye escape, on a Day which shall make children grey-headed.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxciii{%
And the heaven shall be split there in. His promise needs must be fulfilled.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxciv{%
Verily this is an admonition; let him therefore, who will, choose a way Unto his Lord.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcv{%
Verily thy Lord knoweth that thou stayest up near two- thirds of the night, Or half thereof, or a third thereof, and also a party of those who are with thee. And Allah measureth the night and the day. He knoweth that ye can compute it not, He hath relented toward you. Wherefore recite now of the Qur'an, so much as is easy. He knoweth that there will be among you some diseased, and others shall be travelling in the land seeking grace of Allah, and others shall be fighting in the way of Allah. Wherefore recite thereof so much as is easy; and establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and lend Unto Allah a goodly loan. Whatsoever good ye shall send on for your souls, ye shall find it with Allah, better and greater in reward. And ask forgiveness of Allah; verily Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcvi{%
\basmalahen O thou enveloped?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcvii{%
Arise, and warn.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcviii{%
And thine Lord magnify!\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcdxcix{%
And thine raiment purify.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmd{%
And pollution shun.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdi{%
And bestow not favour that thou mayest receive more.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdii{%
And for the good-will of thy Lord be thou patient.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdiii{%
Then when the horn shall be blown,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdiv{%
That shall be - that Day-a day hard.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdv{%
For the infidels, not easy.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdvi{%
Let Me alone with him whom I created lonely.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdvii{%
And for whom I appointed wealth extended.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdviii{%
And sons present by his side.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdix{%
And for whom I smoothed everything.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdx{%
And who yet coveteth that shall increase.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxi{%
By no means! Verily he hath been Unto Our signs a foe.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxii{%
Anon I shall afflict him with a fearful woe.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxiii{%
Verily he considered, and devised.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxiv{%
Perish he! How moliciously he devised!\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxv{%
And again perish he! How maliciously he devised!\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxvi{%
Then looked he,\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxvii{%
Then frowned he and scowled.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxviii{%
Then turned he back, and grew stiff-necked.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxix{%
Then he said: naught is this but magic from of old;\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxx{%
Naught is this but the word of Man.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxi{%
Anon shall I roast him into the Scorching Fire.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxii{%
And what knoweth thou that which the Scorching Fire?\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxiii{%
It shall not spare, nor leave.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxiv{%
. Scorching the skin.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxv{%
Over it are appointed nineteen.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxvi{%
And We have appointed none but the angels to be wardens of the Fire. And their number we have made only a trial for those who disbelieve, so that those who are vouchsafed the Book may be convinced, and that those who believe may increase in faith, and that those who are vouchsafed the Book and the believers may not doubt, and that those in whose hearts is a disease and the infidels may say: what meaneth Allah by this description! In this wise Allah sendeth astray whomsoever He will, and guideth whomsoever He will. And none knoweth the hosts of thy Lord but He. And it is naught but an admonition Unto man.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxvii{%
By no means! By the moon,\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxviii{%
By the night when it with draweth.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxix{%
By the morning when it brighteneth.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxx{%
Verily it is one of the greatest woes.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxi{%
A warning Unto humankind -\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxii{%
A warning Unto him of you who shall go forward or who chooseth to lag behind.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxiii{%
Every soul will be a pledge for that which it hath earned,\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxiv{%
Save the fellows of the right.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxv{%
In Gardens; they shall be asking,\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxvi{%
Concerning the culprits:\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxvii{%
What led you into the Scorching Fire?\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxviii{%
They will say. 'we have not been of those who prayed.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxxxix{%
And we have not been feeding the poor.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxl{%
And we have been wading with the waders.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxli{%
And we have been belying the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlii{%
until there came to us the certainty.\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxliii{%
Then there will not Profit them intercision of the interceders,\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxliv{%
What aileth them, therefore, that they are from the Admonition turning away?\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlv{%
As though they were asses startled."\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlvi{%
Fleeing away from a lion.\qt@no{(51)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlvii{%
Aye! every one of them desireth that: he should be vouchsafed scrolls expanded.\qt@no{(52)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlviii{%
By no means! Aye, they fear not the Hereafter.\qt@no{(53)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxlix{%
By no means! Verily this Qur'an is an Admonition.\qt@no{(54)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdl{%
So whosoever willeth may heed it.\qt@no{(55)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdli{%
And they shall not heed unless Allah Willeth. He is the Lord of piety. and the Lord of forgiveness\qt@no{(56)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlii{%
\basmalahen I swear by the Day of Resurrection.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdliii{%
And I swear by the self-reproaching soul.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdliv{%
Deemest man that We shall not assemble his bones?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlv{%
Yea! WE are Able to put together evenly his finger-tips.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlvi{%
Aye! man desireth that he may sin before him.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlvii{%
He asketh: when will the Day of Resurrection be?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlviii{%
When, then, the sight shall be confounded.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlix{%
And the moon shall be ecliped.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlx{%
And the sun and the moon shall be joined.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxi{%
On that Day shall man say: whither is the fleeing.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxii{%
By no means! NO refuge!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxiii{%
Unto thy Lord that Day is the recourse.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxiv{%
To man will be declared on that Day that which he hath sent on and left behind.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxv{%
Aye! man against himself shall be an enlightenment.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxvi{%
Although he may put forth his pleas.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxvii{%
Move not thy tongue therewith that thou mayest hasten therewith.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxviii{%
Verily upon us is the collecting thereof and the reciting thereof.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxix{%
Wherefore when We reciteit, follow thou the reciting thereof.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxx{%
And thereafter verily upon us is is the expounding thereof.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxi{%
By no means! Verily ye love the Herein.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxii{%
And leave the Hereafter.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxiii{%
Countenances on that Day shall be resplendent,\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxiv{%
Looking toward their Lord.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxv{%
And countenances on that Day shall be scowling.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxvi{%
Imagining that there will befall them a waiste-breaking calomity.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxvii{%
By no means! When it cometh up to he collar-bone.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxviii{%
And it is cried. who can charm?\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxix{%
And he bethinketh that it is the time of parting.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxx{%
And one shank is entangled with the other shank.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxi{%
Unto thy Lord that Day is the drive.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxii{%
He neither believed nor prayed,\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxiii{%
But he belied and turned away.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxiv{%
Then he departed Unto his house hold conceitedly.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxv{%
Woe Unto thee; woe!\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxvi{%
Again, woe Unto thee, woe!\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxvii{%
Deemest man that he is to be left uncontrolled?\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxviii{%
Was he not a sperm of emission emitted?\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdlxxxix{%
Then he became a clot; then He created him and formed him.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxc{%
And made of him the two sexes, male and female.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxci{%
Is not That One then Able to quicken the dead?\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcii{%
\basmalahen Surely there hath come upon man a space of time when he was not a thing worth mentioning.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxciii{%
Verily We! We created man from a sperm of mixtures, that We might prove him, wherefore We made him hearing, seeing.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxciv{%
Verily We! We shewed him the way; then he becometh either thankful or ingrate.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcv{%
Verily We! We have gotten ready for the infidels chains and collars and a Blaze.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcvi{%
Verily the pious shall drink of a cup whereof the admixture is like Unto camphor.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcvii{%
From a fountain whence the bondmen of Allah will drink, causing it to gush abundantly.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcviii{%
They fulfill their vow and dread a Day the evil whereof shall be widespreading.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdxcix{%
And they feed with food, for love of Him, the needy, and the orphan and the captive.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdc{%
Saying: we feed you only for the sake of Allah; we desire not from you any recompense or thanks.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdci{%
Verily we dread from our Lord a Day grim and distressful.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcii{%
Wherefore Allah shall preserve them from the evil of that Day, and shall cause them to meet brightness and joy.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdciii{%
And shall recompense them for that which they patiently bare with a Garden and silken garment.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdciv{%
Reclining therein upon couches, they shall behold therein neither sun nor hurting cold.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcv{%
And close upon them will be the shades thereof, and low will hang the clusters thereof greatly.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcvi{%
And brought round amongst them will be vessels of silver and also goblets of glass.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcvii{%
Godblets of silver, they shall have filled them to exact measure.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcviii{%
And therein they shall be given to drink of a cup whereof the admixture will be ginger.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcix{%
From a fountain therein, named Salsabil.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcx{%
And there shall go round Unto them youths ever-young. When thou seest them thou wouldst deem them pearls unstrung.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxi{%
And when thou lookest them thou shalt behold delight and a dominion magnificent.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxii{%
Upon them shall be garments of fine green silk and of brocades. And adorned they shall be with bracelets of silver: and their Lord shall give them drink a beverage pure.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxiii{%
Verily this is for you by way of recompense, and your endeavour hath been accepted.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxiv{%
Verily We! it is We Who have revealed Unto thee the Qur'an, a gradual revelation.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxv{%
Wherefore persevere thou with the commandment of thy Lord, and obey not thou of them, any sinner or ingrate.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxvi{%
And remember thou the name of thy Lord in the morning and in the evening.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxvii{%
And during the night - worship Him; and hallow Him the livelong night.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxviii{%
Verily those love the Herein, and leave in front of them a heavy day.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxix{%
It it We Who creared them and made them firm of make. And whenever We list, We can replace them with others like Unto them.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxx{%
Verily this is an admonition; then whosoever Will, may choose a way Unto his Lord.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxi{%
And ye will not, unless Allah willeth. Verily Allah is ever Knowing, Wise.'\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxii{%
He maketh whomsoever He listeth to enter His mercy. And the wrong-doers! for them He hath gotten ready a torment afflective.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxiii{%
\basmalahen By the winds sent forth with beneficence.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxiv{%
And those raging swiftly;\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxv{%
By the spreading winds spreading.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxvi{%
And the scattering wind scattering.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxvii{%
And those winds that bring down the remembrance.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxviii{%
By way of excuse or warning.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxix{%
Verily that which ye are promised is about to befall.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxx{%
So when stars are effaced.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxi{%
And when the heaven is cloven asunder.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxii{%
And when the mountains are carried away by wind.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxiii{%
And when the apostles are collected at the appointed time,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxiv{%
For what day is it timed?\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxv{%
For the Day of Decision.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxvi{%
And what knowest thou what the Day of Decision is?\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxvii{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxviii{%
Destroyed We not the ancients?\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxxxix{%
Thereafter We shall cause to follow them the latter ones.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxl{%
In this wise We do with the culprits.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxli{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlii{%
Created We you not of water despicable,\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxliii{%
Which We placed in a depository safe.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxliv{%
Till a limit known?\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlv{%
So We decreed. How excellent are We as decreers!\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlvi{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlvii{%
Have We not made the earth a receptacle.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlviii{%
Both for the living and the dead,\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxlix{%
And have placed therein firm and tall mountains and given you to drink of water fresh\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcl{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcli{%
'Depart Unto that which ye were wont to belie.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclii{%
Depart Unto the shadow three branched:\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcliii{%
Neither shading nor availing against the flame.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcliv{%
Verily it shall cast forth sparks like Unto a castle.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclv{%
As though they were camels yellow tawny.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclvi{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclvii{%
This is a Day whereon they shall not be able to speak.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclviii{%
Nor shall they be permitted so that they might excuse themselves.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclix{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclx{%
This is the Day of Decision, We have assembled both ye and the ancients.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxi{%
If now ye have any craft, try that craft upon Me.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxii{%
Woe on the day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxiii{%
Verily the God-fearing shall be amid shades and springs,\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxiv{%
And fruits such as they shall desire.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxv{%
'Eat and drink with relish that which ye have been working.\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxvi{%
Verily We! in this wise We recompense the well-doers.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxvii{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxviii{%
'Eat and enjoy a little; verily ye are culprits.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxix{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(47)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxx{%
And when it is said Unto them: 'bow down, they bow not down.\qt@no{(48)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxi{%
Woe on that day Unto the beliers!\qt@no{(49)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxii{%
In what discourse, then, after it, will they believe?\qt@no{(50)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxiii{%
\basmalahen Of what ask they?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxiv{%
Of the mighty Announcement,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxv{%
Concerning which they differ.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxvi{%
By no means! anon they shall know.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxvii{%
Again, by no means! anon they shall know.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxviii{%
Have We not made the earth an expanse.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxix{%
And the mountains as stakes?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxx{%
And We have created you in pairs.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxi{%
And We have made your sleep as a rest.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxii{%
And We have made the night a covering.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxiii{%
And We have made the day for seeking livelihood.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxiv{%
And We have builded over you seven strong heavens.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxv{%
And We have set therein lamps glowing.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxvi{%
And We have sent down from the rain-clouds water plenteous.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxvii{%
So that We bring forth thereby corn and vegetation.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxviii{%
And gardens thick with trees.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdclxxxix{%
Verily the Day of Decision is a time appointed.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxc{%
It is a Day whereon the trumpet will be blown, and ye will come in multitudes.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxci{%
And the heaven will have been opened, and it will have become doors.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcii{%
And the mountains will have been removed away, and they will have become as mirage.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxciii{%
Verily the Hell is an ambuscade:\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxciv{%
For the exorbitant a receptacle.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcv{%
They will tarry therein for ages.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcvi{%
They will not taste therein cool or any drink.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcvii{%
Save scalding water and corruption.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcviii{%
Recompense fitted!\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcxcix{%
Verily they were wont not to look for a reckoning.\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcc{%
And they belied Our revelations with strong belying.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcci{%
And everything We have recorded in a book.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccii{%
Taste therefore. We shall not increase you in aught but torment.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcciii{%
Verily for the God-fearing is an achievement.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcciv{%
Gardens enclosed and vineyards,\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccv{%
And full-breasted maidens of equal age.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccvi{%
And a cup overflowing.\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccvii{%
They will hear therein no babble nor falsehood:\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccviii{%
A recompense from thy Lord-a gift sufficient -\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccix{%
From the Lord of the heavens and the earth and of whatsoever is in bet-ween them, the Compassionate with Whom they can demand not audience.\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccx{%
On the Day whereon the spirits and the angels will stand arrayed, they will not be able to speak save him whom the Compassionate giveth leave and who speaketh aright.\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxi{%
That is the Sure Day. Whosoever therefore willeth, let him betake Unto his Lord a resort.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxii{%
Verily We! We have warned you of a torment nigh at hand, a Day whereon a man shall behold that which his hands have sent forth, and the infidel will say: would that I were dust!\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxiii{%
\basmalahen By the angels who drag forth vehemently.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxiv{%
By the angels who release with gentle release.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxv{%
By the angels who glide swimmingiy,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxvi{%
And then they speed with foremost speed.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxvii{%
And then they manage the affair,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxviii{%
A Day shall come whereon the quaking will quake,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxix{%
And there will follow it the next blast.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxx{%
Hearts on that Day will be throbbing;\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxi{%
Their looks will be downcast.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxii{%
They say: shall we indeed be restored to the first state,\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxiii{%
When we have become bones decayed!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxiv{%
They say: that then shall be a losing return.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxv{%
It will be only one scaring shout,\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxvi{%
And lo! they all shall appear on the surface.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxvii{%
Hath there come Unto thee the story of Musa!\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxviii{%
Recall what time his Lord called Unto him in the holy vale of Tuwa.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxix{%
Saying:'go thou Unto Fir'awn; verily he hath waxen exorbitant.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxx{%
Then say thou: 'wouldst thou to be purified?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxi{%
Then shall guide thee Unto thy Lord so that thou shalt fear.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxii{%
Then he shewed him the great sign.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxiii{%
Yet he belied and disobeyed.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxiv{%
Then he turned back striving.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxv{%
Then he gathered and cried aloud,\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxvi{%
And he said: I am Your Lord, most high.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxvii{%
Wherefore Allah laid hold of him with the punishment of the Hereafter and of the present.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxviii{%
Verily herein is lesson for him who feareth.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxxxix{%
Are ye harder to create or the heaven which He hath builded?\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxl{%
He hath raised the height thereof and perfected it.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxli{%
And He made dark its night, and brought forth its sunshine.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlii{%
And the earth!- thereafter He stretched it out.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxliii{%
And he brought forth therefrom its water, and its pasture.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxliv{%
And the mountains! - He established them firm:\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlv{%
A provision for you and your cattle.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlvi{%
Then when the Grand Calamity shall come\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlvii{%
The Day whereon man shall rember whatsoever he had striven for.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlviii{%
And the Scorch will be made apparent to any one who beholdeth.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxlix{%
Then as for him who waxed exorbitant,\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccl{%
And who chose the life of the world,\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccli{%
Verily the Scorch! that shall be his resort.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclii{%
And as for him who dreaded standing before his Lord, and restrained his soul from lust,\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccliii{%
Verily the Garden! -that shall be his resort.\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccliv{%
They question thee of the Hour:'when will its arrival be?\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclv{%
Wherein art thou concerred with the declaration thereof!\qt@no{(43)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclvi{%
Unto thy Lord is the Knowledge of the limit fixed therefor.\qt@no{(44)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclvii{%
Thou art but a warner Unto him who feareth.\qt@no{(45)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclviii{%
On the Day whereon they behold it, it will appear to them as though they had not tarried save an evening or the morn thereof.\qt@no{(46)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclix{%
\basmalahen He frowned and turned away.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclx{%
Because there came Unto him a blind man.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxi{%
How canst thou know, whether haply he might be cleansed,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxii{%
Or be admonished, so that the admonition might have profited him?\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxiii{%
As for him who regardeth himself self-sufficient-\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxiv{%
Unto him thou attendest.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxv{%
Whereas it is not on thee that he is not cleansed.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxvi{%
And as for him who cometh Unto thee running,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxvii{%
And he feareth'-\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxviii{%
Him thou neglectest!\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxix{%
By no means! Verily it is an admonition.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxx{%
So whosoever willeth-let him be admonished therewlth.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxi{%
Inscribed in Writs honoured,"\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxii{%
Exalted, Purified,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxiii{%
By the hands of scribes.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxiv{%
Honourable and virtuous.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxv{%
Perish man! how ungrateful he is!\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxvi{%
Of what thing hath He created him?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxvii{%
Of a drop of seed. He created him and formed him according to a measure.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxviii{%
Then the way He made easy.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxix{%
Then He caused him to die and made him to be buried.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxx{%
Then when He listeth, He shall raise him to life.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxi{%
By no means He performed not that which He had commanded him.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxii{%
Let man look at his food:\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxiii{%
It is We Who pour forth water, pouring,\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxiv{%
Thereafter We cleave the earth in clefts,\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxv{%
Then We cause therein the grain to grow,\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxvi{%
And grapes and vegetables\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxvii{%
And olives and palms\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxviii{%
And enclosed gardens luxuriant.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcclxxxix{%
And fruits and herbage:\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxc{%
A provision for you and for your cattle.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxci{%
Then when cometh the Deafening Cry-\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcii{%
On the Day whereon a man shall flee from his brother,\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxciii{%
And his mother and his father,\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxciv{%
And his wife and his sons;\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcv{%
For every one of them on that Day shall be business enough to occupy\qt@no{(37)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcvi{%
Faces on that Day shall be beaming,\qt@no{(38)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcvii{%
Laughing, rejoicing.\qt@no{(39)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcviii{%
And faces on that Day! upon them shall be gloom.\qt@no{(40)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccxcix{%
Dust shall cover them\qt@no{(41)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccc{%
Those! they are the infidels, the ungodly.\qt@no{(42)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccci{%
\basmalahen When the sun shall be wound round,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccii{%
And when the stars shall dart down,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccciii{%
And when the mountains shall be made to pass away,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccciv{%
And when the she-camels big with young shall be abandoned,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccv{%
And when the wild beasts shall be gathered together,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccvi{%
And when the seas shall be filled,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccvii{%
And when the souls he paired,\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccviii{%
And when the girl buried alive shall be asked:\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccix{%
For what sin she was slain.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccx{%
And when the Writs shall be lain open,\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxi{%
And when the heaven shall be stripped,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxii{%
And when the Scorch shall be made to blaze,\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxiii{%
And when the Garden shall be brought nigh,\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxiv{%
Then every soul shall know that which it: hath presented.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxv{%
I swear by the receding stars.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxvi{%
Moving swiftly and hiding themselves,\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxvii{%
And by the night when it departeth,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxviii{%
And by the morning when it shineth forth,\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxix{%
Verily it is a Word brought by a messenger honoured,\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxx{%
Owner of strength, of established dignity with the Lord of the Throne.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxi{%
Obeyed one there; trustWorthy.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxii{%
Nor is your companion distracted.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxiii{%
Assuredly he beheld him in the horizon manifest.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxiv{%
And he is of the unseen not a tenacious concealer.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxv{%
Nor is it the word of a Satan accursed.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxvi{%
Whither then go ye?\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxvii{%
This is naught but an Admonition Unto the worlds-\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxviii{%
Unto whomsoever of you willeth to walk straight.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxix{%
And ye shall not will unless it be that Allah, the Lord of the worlds, willeth.\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxx{%
\basmalahen When the heaven shall be cleft,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxi{%
And when the stars shall be scattered,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxii{%
And when the seas are flowed out,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxiii{%
And when the graves are ransacked,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxiv{%
Each soul shall know that which it sent afore and that which it left behind.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxv{%
O man! what hath beguiled thee concerning thy Lord, the Bountiful,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxvi{%
Who created thee, then moulded thee, then proportioned thee?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxvii{%
In whatsoever form He listed He constructed thee.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxviii{%
By no means! Aye, ye belie the the Requital.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxxxix{%
Verify there are for you guardians,\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxl{%
Honourablel scribes.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxli{%
They know whatsoever ye do.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlii{%
Verily the pious shall be in Delight.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxliii{%
And verily the ungodly shall be in a Scorch.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxliv{%
Roasted they shall be therein on the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlv{%
And thence they shall not be allowed to be absent.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlvi{%
And what shall make thee know whatsoever the Day of Requital is?\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlvii{%
Again, what shall make thee know whatsoever the Day of Requital is?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlviii{%
It is a Day whereon no soul shall own aught of power for any soul; and the command on that Day will be Allah's.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxlix{%
\basmalahen Woe Unto the scrimpers:\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccl{%
Those who, when they take by measure from mankind, exact the full,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccli{%
And who, when they measure Unto them or weigh for them, diminish.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclii{%
Imagine such men not that they shall be raised up?\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccliii{%
On a mighty Day.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccliv{%
A Day whereon mankind shall stand before the Lord of the worlds?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclv{%
By no means! Verily the record of the ungodly is in Sijjin.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclvi{%
And what will make thee know whatsoever the record in Sijjin is?\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclvii{%
A record of misdeeds written.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclviii{%
Woe on that Day unto the belviers-\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclix{%
Those who belie the Day of Requital.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclx{%
And none belieth it save each trespasser, sinner.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxi{%
And when Our revelations are rehearsed Unto him, she saith:'fables of the ancients!\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxii{%
By no means!' Aye! encrusted upon their hearts is that which they have been earning.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxiii{%
By no means! Verily on that Day from their Lord they will be shut Out.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxiv{%
Then verily they will be roasted into the Scorch.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxv{%
Then it will be said: 'this is that which ye were wont to belie.'\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxvi{%
By no means! Verily the record of the virtuous shall be in 'Illiyun.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxvii{%
And what will make thee know whatsoever the record in Illiyun is?\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxviii{%
A record of good deeds written.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxix{%
To which bear witness those brought nigh.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxx{%
Verily the virtuous shall be in Delight,\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxi{%
Reclining on couches, looking on.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxii{%
Thou wilt recognize in their faces the brightness of delight.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxiii{%
They will be given to drink of pure wine, sealed.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxiv{%
The seal thereof will be of musk and to this end let the aspirers aspire -\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxv{%
And admixture thereof will be Water of Tasnim:\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxvi{%
A fountain whereof will drink those brought nigh.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxvii{%
Veriiy those who have sinned were wont at those who had believed to laugh,\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxviii{%
And, when they passed them, to wink at each other,\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxix{%
And when they returned to their household they returned jesting.\qt@no{(31)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxx{%
And when they saw them, they said: verily these are the strayed ones.\qt@no{(32)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxi{%
Whereas they were not sent over them as watchers.\qt@no{(33)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxii{%
Wherefore Today, those who believed at the infidels are laughing,\qt@no{(34)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxiii{%
Reclining on couches, looking on.\qt@no{(35)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxiv{%
The infidels have indeed been rewarded for that which they had been doing.\qt@no{(36)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxv{%
\basmalahen When the heaven is sundered.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxvi{%
And it hearkeneth to its Lord, and is duteous,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxvii{%
And when the earth shall be stretched forth.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxviii{%
And shall cast forth that which is therein, and shall become empty.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdccclxxxix{%
And it hearkeneth to its Lord, and is duteous.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxc{%
O man! verily thou art toiling toward thy Lord a painful toiling, and art about to meet Him.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxci{%
Then as to him who shall be given his book in his right hand -\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcii{%
His account shall presently be taken by an easy reckoning.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxciii{%
And he shall return Unto his people joyfully.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxciv{%
And as to him who shall be given his book from behind his back-\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcv{%
He shall presently call for death,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcvi{%
And he shall roast into a Blaze.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcvii{%
Verily he was among his people joyous.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcviii{%
Verily he imagined that he would not be back.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmdcccxcix{%
Yea! his Lord had ever been beholding him.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcm{%
I swear by the afterglow of sunset,\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmi{%
And by the night and that which it driveth together,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmii{%
And by the moon when she becometh full.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmiii{%
Surely ye shall ride layer upon layer.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmiv{%
What aileth them then, that they believe not,\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmv{%
And that, when the Qur'an is read Unto them, they prostrate not them-selves!\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmvi{%
Yea those who disbelieve belie.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmvii{%
Whereas Allah knoweth best that which they cherish.\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmviii{%
Wherefore announce thou Unto them a torment afflictive.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmix{%
But those who believe and work righteous works, theirs shall be a hire unending.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmx{%
\basmalahen By the heaven adorned with big stars.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxi{%
And by the Day promised,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxii{%
And by the Day witnessing and the Day witnessed,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxiii{%
Perish the fellows of the ditch,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxiv{%
Of fire fuel-fed,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxv{%
When they sat by it\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxvi{%
And to that which they did to the believers were witnesses.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxvii{%
And they persecuted them for naught save that they believed in Allah, the Mighty, the Praiseworthy\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxviii{%
Him, Whose is the dominion of heavens and the earth. And Allah is over everything a Witness.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxix{%
Verily those who affected the believing men and the believing women, and then repented not, theirs shall be the torment of Hell, and theirs shall be the torment of burning.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxx{%
Verily those who believed and worked righteons works, theirs shall be Gardens whereunder the rivers flow; that is the supreme achievement.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxi{%
Verily the grip of thine Lord is severe.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxii{%
Verily He! He it is who beginneth and repeateth it.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxiii{%
And He is the Fogiving, the Loving,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxiv{%
Lord of the Throne, the Glorious,\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxv{%
Doer of whatsoever He intendeth.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxvi{%
Hath there come Unto thee the story of the hosts-\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxvii{%
Of the Fir'awn and the Thamud?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxviii{%
But those who disbelieve are engaged in denial.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxix{%
Whereas Allah is, from behind them, Encompassing.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxx{%
Aye! it is a Recitation glorious,\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxi{%
Inscribed in a tablet preserved.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxii{%
\basmalahen By the heaven and the night-comer\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxiii{%
And what shall make thee know that which the night-comer is?-\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxiv{%
It is the star shing brightly.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxv{%
No soul is there but hath over it a watcher.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxvi{%
So let man look - from what is he created.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxvii{%
He is created from a water drip-ping,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxviii{%
That issueth from between the loins and the breast-bones.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxxxix{%
Verily He is Able to restore him,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxl{%
On a Day whereon secrets shall be out.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxli{%
Then he shall have no power nor any helper.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlii{%
By the heaven which returneth,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxliii{%
And by the earth which splitteth,\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxliv{%
Verily, it is a discourse distinguishing.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlv{%
And it is not a frivolity.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlvi{%
Verily they are plotting a plot.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlvii{%
And I am plotting a plot.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlviii{%
So respite thou the infidels - respite them gently,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxlix{%
\basmalahen Hallow thou the name of thine Lord, the Most High,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcml{%
Who hath created and then proportioned,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmli{%
And Who hath disposed and then guided,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlii{%
And Who bringeth forth the pasturage,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmliii{%
Then maketh it to stubble dusky.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmliv{%
We shall enable thee to recite, and then thou shalt not forget,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlv{%
Save that which Allah may will. Verily He knoweth the public and that which is hidden.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlvi{%
And We shall make easy Unto thee the easy way.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlvii{%
Wherefore admonish thou; admonition hath surely profited,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlviii{%
Admonished is he indeed who feareth,\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlix{%
And the wretched shunneth it-.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlx{%
He Who shall roast into the Great Fire,\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxi{%
Wherein he shall neither die nor live,\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxii{%
He indeed hath attained bliss who hath cleansed himself,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxiii{%
And who remembereth the name of his Lord, and then prayeth.\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxiv{%
But ye prefer the life of this world,\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxv{%
Whereas the Hereafter is better and more lasting.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxvi{%
Verily this is in Writs ancient\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxvii{%
Writs of Ibrahim and Musa.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxviii{%
\basmalahen Hath there come Unto thee the story of the Enveloping Event?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxix{%
Faces on that Day shall be downcast,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxx{%
Travailing, worn.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxi{%
They shall roast into the scalding Fire,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxii{%
Given to drink of a spring fiercely boiling.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxiii{%
No food shall be theirs save bitter thorn,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxiv{%
Which shall neither nourish nor avail against hunger.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxv{%
Faces on that Day shall be de lighted,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxvi{%
With their endeavour well pleased.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxvii{%
They shall be in a Garden lofty:\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxviii{%
They shall hear therein no vain discourse;\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxix{%
Therein shall be a spring running!\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxx{%
Therein shall be couches elevated!\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxi{%
And goblets ready placed!\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxii{%
And cushions ranged!\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxiii{%
And carpets ready spread,\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxiv{%
Look they not at the camels, how they are created?\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxv{%
And at the heaven, how it is raised?\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxvi{%
And at the mountains, how they are rooted?\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxvii{%
And at the earth, how it is outspread?\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxviii{%
Admonish thou then; thou art but an admonisher.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmlxxxix{%
Thou art not over them a warden.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxc{%
But whosoever will turn back and disbelieve -\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxci{%
Him Allah shall torment with the greatest torment.\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcii{%
Verily Unto us is their reckoning.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxciii{%
Then verily on us is their reckoning.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxciv{%
\basmalahen By the dawn,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcv{%
And by ten nights,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcvi{%
And by the even and the odd,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcvii{%
And by the night when it departeth,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcviii{%
Indeed in that there is an oath for a man of sense.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmcmxcix{%
Bethinkest thou not in what wise thy Lord did with the 'A'ad:\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmm{%
The people of many-columned lram.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmi{%
The like of which was not built in the cities,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmii{%
And With Thamud who hewed out rocks in the vale,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmiii{%
And with Fir'awn, owner of the stakes -\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmiv{%
Who all waxed exorbitant in the cities,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmv{%
And multiplied therein corruption.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmvi{%
Wherefore thy Lord poured on them the scourge of His torment.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmvii{%
Verily thy Lord is in an ambuscade,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmviii{%
As for man - when his Lord proveth him and so honoureth him and is bounteous Unto him, then he saith: 'my Lord hath honoured me,\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmix{%
And when He proveth him, and so stinteth Unto him his provision, he saith: 'my Lord hath despised me.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmx{%
By no means! But ye honour not the orphan,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxi{%
Nor urge upon each other the feeding of the poor,\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxii{%
And devour the inheritance devouring greedily,\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxiii{%
And ye love riches with exceeding love.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxiv{%
By no means! when the earth shall be ground with grinding, grinding,\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxv{%
And thy Lord shall come and the angels, rank on rank.\qt@no{(22)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxvi{%
And the Hell on that Day shall be brought nigh. On that Day man shall remember, but how will remembrance avail him?\qt@no{(23)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxvii{%
He will say. 'would that I had sent before for this life of mine!\qt@no{(24)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxviii{%
Wherefore on that Day none shall torment with His torment.\qt@no{(25)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxix{%
Nor shall any bind with His bond.\qt@no{(26)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxx{%
O thou peaceful soul!\qt@no{(27)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxi{%
Return Unto thine Lord well pleased and well-pleasing.\qt@no{(28)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxii{%
Enter thou among My righteous bondmen!\qt@no{(29)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxiii{%
And enter thou My Garden.\qt@no{(30)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxiv{%
\basmalahen I swear by yonder city\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxv{%
And thou shalt be allowed in yonder city -\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxvi{%
And by the begetter and that which he begat,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxvii{%
Assuredly We have created man in trouble.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxviii{%
Deemest he that none will overpower him?\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxix{%
He saith: 'I have wasted riches plenteous.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxx{%
Deemest he that none beholdeth him?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxi{%
Have We not, made for him two eyes\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxii{%
And a tongue and two lips,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxiii{%
And shown Unto him the two highways?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxiv{%
Yet he attempteth not the steep,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxv{%
And what shall make thee understand that which the steep is?\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxvi{%
It is freeing the neck,\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxvii{%
Or, feeding, in a day of privation,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxviii{%
An orphan, of kin,\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxxxix{%
Or a poor man cleaving to the dust.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxl{%
Then he became of those who believed and enjoined on each other steadfastness and enjoined on each other compassion.\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxli{%
These are the fellows of the righthand.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlii{%
And those who disbelieve Our signs - they are the fellows of the lefthand.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxliii{%
Over them shall be Fire closing round.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxliv{%
\basmalahen By the sun and his morning bright-ness,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlv{%
By the moon, when she followeth him,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlvi{%
By the day when it glorifieth him.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlvii{%
By the night; when it envelopeth him,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlviii{%
By the heaven and Him Who builded it,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxlix{%
By the earth and Him Who spread it forth,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmml{%
By the soul and Him Who propertioned it,\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmli{%
And inspired it with the wickedness thereof and the piety thereof,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlii{%
Surely blissful is he who hath cleansed, it,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmliii{%
And miserable is he who hath buried it.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmliv{%
Thamud belied in their exorbitance.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlv{%
What time the greatest wretch of them rose up.\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlvi{%
Then the apostle of Allah said Unto them: beware of the she-camel of Allah and her drink.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlvii{%
Then they belied him, and they hamstrung her; wherefore their Lord overwhelmed them for their crime, and made it equal.\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlviii{%
And He feared not the consequence thereof\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlix{%
\basmalahen By the night when it envelopeth,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlx{%
By the day when it appeareth in glory,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxi{%
By Him Who hath created the male and the female,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxii{%
Verily your endeavour is diverse.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxiii{%
Then as for him who giveths and feareth Him.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxiv{%
And testifieth to the Good,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxv{%
Unto him therefore We shall indeed make easy the path to ease.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxvi{%
And as for him who stinteth and is heedless,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxvii{%
And who belieth the Good,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxviii{%
Unto him therefore We shall Indeed make easy the path to hardship.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxix{%
And his substance will avail him not when he perisheth.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxx{%
Verify on us is the guidance\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxi{%
And verify Ours is both the Hereafter and the life present.\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxii{%
Wherefore have warned you of Fire flaming,\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxiii{%
None shall roast therein but the most wretched,\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxiv{%
Who belieth and turneth away.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxv{%
And avoid it shall the most pious,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxvi{%
Who giveth away his substance that he may be cleansed,\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxvii{%
And who hath no favour from anyone to recompense.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxviii{%
But only seeking the Countenance of his Lord the Most High.\qt@no{(20)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxix{%
And presently he shall become wellpleased.\qt@no{(21)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxx{%
\basmalahen By the morning brightness,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxi{%
By the night when it darkeneth,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxii{%
Thy Lord hath not forsaken thee, nor is He displeased.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxiii{%
And the Hereafter is indeed better Unto thee than the life present.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxiv{%
And presently thy Lord shall give Unto thee so that thou shalt be be well-pleased.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxv{%
Found He not thee an orphan, so He sheltered thee?\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxvi{%
And He found thee wandering, so He guided thee,\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxvii{%
And He found thee destitute, so He enriched thee.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxviii{%
Wherefore as to the orphan, be thou not Unto him overbearing.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmlxxxix{%
And as to the beggar, chide thou him not.\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxc{%
And as to the favour of thine Lord discourse thou thereof.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxci{%
\basmalahen Have We not opened forth for thee thy breast?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcii{%
And We have taken off from thee thy burthen,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxciii{%
Which weighed down thy back.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxciv{%
And We have upraised for thee thy renown.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcv{%
Then verily along with every hardship is ease.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcvi{%
Verily along with every hardship is ease.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcvii{%
Then when thou becometh relieved, toil;\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcviii{%
And Unto thine Lord, attend.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmxcix{%
\basmalahen By the fig, by the olive,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmc{%
By Mount Sinai,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmci{%
By the yonder secure city,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcii{%
Assuredly We have created man in goodliest mould,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmciii{%
Thereafter We cause him to return to the lowest of the low,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmciv{%
Save those who believe and work righteous Works. Theirs shall be hire unending.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcv{%
What hencefort shall make thee belie the Requital?\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcvi{%
Is not Allah the Greatest of the rulers?\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcvii{%
\basmalahen Recite thou in the name of thy Lord Who hath created -\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcviii{%
Hath created man from a clot!\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcix{%
Recite thou: And thy Lord is the Most Bounteous,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcx{%
Who hath taught mankind by the pen -\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxi{%
Hath taught man that which he knew not.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxii{%
By no means: Verily man exorbitateth.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxiii{%
As he bethinkest himself selfsufficient.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxiv{%
Verily Unto thy Lord is the return.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxv{%
Bethinkest thou him who forbiddeth,\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxvi{%
A bondman of Ours when he prayeth *\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxvii{%
Bethinkest thou, if he is himself guided,\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxviii{%
Or he commandeth piety?\qt@no{(12)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxix{%
Bethinkest thou, if he belieth and turneth away?\qt@no{(13)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxx{%
Knoweth he not that Allah beholdeth?\qt@no{(14)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxi{%
By no means! If he desist not We shall seize and deal him by the forelock -\qt@no{(15)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxii{%
A forelock, lying, sinning.\qt@no{(16)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxiii{%
Then, let him call his assembly,\qt@no{(17)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxiv{%
We also shall call the infernal guards.\qt@no{(18)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxv{%
By no means! Obey not thou him. Continue to adore, and continue to draw nigh.\qt@no{(19)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxvi{%
\basmalahen Verily We! We have sent it down on the night of Power.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxvii{%
And what shall make thee know that which the night of Power is?\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxviii{%
The night of Power is better than a thousand months.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxix{%
The angels and the spirit descend therein by the command of their Lord with His decrees for every affair.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxx{%
It is all peace, until the rising of the dawn.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxi{%
\basmalahen Those who disbelieved from among the People of the Book and the associaters could not break off, until there had come Unto them the evidence.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxii{%
An apostle from Allah rehearsing Writs cleansed.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxiii{%
Wherein are discourses eternal.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxiv{%
And those who are vouchsafed the Book divided not save after there had come Unto them the evidence.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxv{%
And they were commanded not but that they should worship Allah, keeping religion pure for him, as upright men, and that they should establish prayer and give the poor-rate, And that is the right religion.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxvi{%
Verily those who disbelieve from among the people of the Book and the associaters shall be cast into the Hell-fire, as abiders therein. These! they are the worst of the creation.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxvii{%
Verily those who believe and work righteous works - these! they are the best of the creation.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxviii{%
Their recompense with their Lord shall be Gardens Everlasting, whereunder rivers flow - as abiders therein for evermore. Well-pleases will be Allah with them and well-pleased will be they with Him, That is for him who feareth his Lord.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxxxix{%
\basmalahen When the earth is shaken by the shaking thereof,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxl{%
And the earth bringeth forth her burthens,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxli{%
And man saith: what aileth her?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlii{%
On that Day she will tell out the tidings thereof.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxliii{%
Because thy Lord will inspire her.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxliv{%
On that Day mankind will proceed in bands, that they may be shewn their works.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlv{%
Then whosoever hath worked good of an atom's weight shall behold it\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlvi{%
And whosoever hath worked ill Of an atom's weight shall behold it.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlvii{%
\basmalahen By the chargers panting,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlviii{%
And striking off fire by dashing their hoofs.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxlix{%
And raiding at dawn\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcl{%
And therein raising dust.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcli{%
And cleaving their way therein into the host,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclii{%
Verily man is Unto his Lord ungrateful.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcliii{%
And verily to that he is witness.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcliv{%
And verily in the love of wealth he is vehement,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclv{%
Knoweth he not - when that which is in the graves, shall be ransacked?\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclvi{%
And there shall be brounht to light that which is in the breasts?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclvii{%
Verily their Lord on that Day will be of them Aware.\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclviii{%
\basmalahen The Striking!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclix{%
What is the Striking?\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclx{%
What shall Make thee know that which the Striking is?\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxi{%
A Day whereon mankind shall become as moths scattered,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxii{%
And the mountains shall become as wool carded,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxiii{%
Then as for him whose balances are heavy,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxiv{%
He shall be in a lifewell-pleasing.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxv{%
And as for him whose balances are light,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxvi{%
His dwelling shall be the Abyss.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxvii{%
And what shall make thee know that which she is?\qt@no{(10)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxviii{%
A Fire vehemently hot!\qt@no{(11)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxix{%
\basmalahen The emulous desire of abundance engrosseth you,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxx{%
Until ye visit the graves.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxi{%
Lo! presently ye shall know.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxii{%
Again lo! presently ye shall know.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxiii{%
Lo! would that ye knew now with the surety of knowledge!\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxiv{%
Surely ye shall behold theScorch.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxv{%
Then ye shall surely beholdwith the surety of vision.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxvi{%
Then, on that Day, ye shall surely be asked of the delights.\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxvii{%
\basmalahen By the time,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxviii{%
Verily man is in loss,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxix{%
But not those who themselves believe and work righteous works, and enjoin upon each other the truth, and enjoin upon each other endurance.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxx{%
\basmalahen Woe Unto every slanderer, traducer,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxi{%
Who amasseth wealth; and counteth it.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxii{%
He bethinketh that his wealth shall abide for him.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxiii{%
By no means! He shall surely be cast into the Crushing Fire.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxiv{%
And what shall make thee know that which the Crushing Fire is?\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxv{%
Fire of Allah, Kindled,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxvi{%
Which mounteth up to the hearts.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxvii{%
Verily it shall close upon them,\qt@no{(8)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxviii{%
In pillars stretched forth.\qt@no{(9)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmclxxxix{%
\basmalahen Hast thou not observed what wise thy Lord dealt with the fellows of the elephant?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxc{%
Put He not their stratagem to straying.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxci{%
And He sent against them birds in flocks.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcii{%
They hurled upon them stones of baked clay;\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxciii{%
Then He rendered them as stubble devoured.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxciv{%
\basmalahen For the keeping of the Quraish\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcv{%
For their keeping to the journey in the winter and the summer-\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcvi{%
Let them worship the Lord of this House,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcvii{%
Who hath fed them against hunger; and hath rendered them secure from fear.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcviii{%
\basmalahen Beholdest thou him who belieth the Requital?\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcxcix{%
It is he who pusheth away the orphan,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcc{%
And urgeth not the feeding of the poor,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcci{%
Woe, therefore, Unto such performers of prayer.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccii{%
As are of their prayer careless.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcciii{%
They who would be seen,\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmcciv{%
And who withholds even common necessaries.\qt@no{(7)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccv{%
\basmalahen Verily We! We have given thee Kauthar.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccvi{%
Wherefore pray thou Unto thy Lord, and sacrifice.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccvii{%
Verily it is thy traducer who shall be tail-less.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccviii{%
\basmalahen Say thou: O ye infidels!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccix{%
I worship not, that which ye worship.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccx{%
Nor are ye the worshippers of that which I worship.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxi{%
And I shall not be a worshipper of that which ye have worshipped,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxii{%
Nor will ye be worshippers of that which I worship,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxiii{%
Yours shall be your requital, and mine shall be my requital.\qt@no{(6)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxiv{%
\basmalahen When there cometh the succour of Allah and the victory,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxv{%
And thou beholdest mankind entering the religion of Allah in crowds,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxvi{%
Then hallow the praise of thy Lord, and ask forgiveness of Him. Verily He is ever Relenting.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxvii{%
\basmalahen Perish the two hands of Abu Lahab, and perish he!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxviii{%
His substance availed him not, nor that which he earned.\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxix{%
Anon he shall roast into Fire having flame.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxx{%
And his wife also: the firewood carrier;\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxi{%
On her neck shall be a cord of twisted fibre.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxii{%
\basmalahen Say thou: He is Allah, the One!\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxiii{%
Allah, the Independent,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxiv{%
He begetteth not, nor Was He begotten.\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxv{%
And there hath never been co-equal with Him anyone.\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxvi{%
\basmalahen Say thou; I seek refuge with the Lord of the daybreak.\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxvii{%
From the evil of that which He hath created,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxviii{%
And from the evil of the darken when it cometh,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxix{%
And from the evil of the women blowers upon knots,\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxx{%
And from the evil of the envier when he envieth.\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxi{%
\basmalahen Say thou: I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind,\qt@no{(1)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxii{%
The King of mankind,\qt@no{(2)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxiii{%
The God of mankind,\qt@no{(3)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxiv{%
From the evil of the sneaking whisperer\qt@no{(4)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxv{%
Who whispereth Unto the breasts of mankind,\qt@no{(5)}}%
\qt@newcmd\qurantrans@en@mmmmmmccxxxvi{%
Whether of Jinn or of mankind.\qt@no{(6)}}%
